In the Night Room is a 2004 horror - thriller novel by American author Peter Straub and a sequel to his 2003 book Lost Boy , Lost Girl .
The Elephant Calf ( Das Elefantenkalb ) , also known as The Baby Elephant , is an early one - act surrealistic prose farce written by the German modernist playwright Bertolt Brecht .
The Wedding of Zein ( Arabic : عرس الزين ) is a contemporary Arabic novel written in 1969 by late Sudanese author Tayeb Salih .
Marked by Fire ( 1982 ) is a novel by Joyce Carol Thomas .
Sjöwall and Wahlöö , during the 1960s and 1970s , conceived and wrote a series of ten novels ( police procedurals ) about the exploits of detectives from the special homicide commission of the Swedish national police in which the character of Martin Beck was the protagonist .
The Universe Versus Alex Woods ( 2013 ) is the debut novel by Gavin Extence .
The Road of Winds ( a.k.a . Gobi Notes ) is a non - fiction book by Ivan Yefremov about his three years ' travel in Mongolia ( 1946 - -1949 ) when he was the head of the Joint Soviet - Mongolian Paleontology Expedition .
Published in 1921 , Memoirs of a Midget is a surrealistic novel , told in the first person , by English poet , anthologist , and short story writer Walter de la Mare , best known for his tales of the uncanny and poetry for children .
Personal Recollections of Joan of Arc , by the Sieur Louis de Conte is an 1896 novel by Mark Twain that recounts the life of Joan of Arc .
The Penguin Dictionary of Curious and Interesting Numbers is a reference book for recreational mathematics and elementary number theory written by David Wells .
Wings of Wrath ( ISBN 0756405351 ) is a fantasy novel by Celia S. Friedman .
That Eye , the Sky is a 1986 novel by award - winning Australian author Tim Winton .
Teacher Man is a 2005 memoir written by Frank McCourt which describes and reflects on his teaching experiences in New York high schools and colleges .
Sartoris is a novel , first published in 1929 , by the American author William Faulkner .
The Wardstone Chronicles , published as The Last Apprentice series in the USA , is a dark fantasy series of books written by British author Joseph Delaney and published in the UK by The Bodley Head division of Random House Publishing .
Twilight 's Child was written in 1992 by V. C. Andrews .
The Crystal World is a novel by English author J. G. Ballard , published in 1966 .
The Trumpet - Major is a novel by Thomas Hardy published in 1880 , and his only historical novel .
Servant of the Bones ( 1996 ) is a historical horror novel by Anne Rice .
The Emergence of Modern Turkey is a 1961 book written by historian Bernard Lewis , an expert in the history of Middle East and Islam .
Born Blue is a 2001 young adult novel by award winning author Han Nolan .
Venus in Furs ( German : Venus i m Pelz ) is a novella by the Austrian author Leopold von Sacher - Masoch , and the best known of his works .
The Chemical History of a Candle was the title of a series of six lectures on the chemistry and physics of flames given by Michael Faraday at the Royal Institution .
The Invention of Hugo Cabret is an American historical fiction book written and illustrated by Brian Selznick and published by Scholastic .
Alex Cross , Run is the 20th novel in the Alex Cross series written by American author James Patterson .
Half a Wing , Three Engines and a Prayer , is a book about B-17 crews and missions in World War II , written by Brian D. O'Neill .
London Blues is a novel by Anthony Frewin first published in 1997 about Soho in the late 1950s and early 1960s and in particular about the early days of pornographic movie production in Britain .
Cosmonaut Keep ( 2000 ; US paperback ISBN 0 - 7653 - 4073 - 9 ) , a science fiction novel by Ken MacLeod .
The Trial ( original German title : Der Process , later Der Prozess , Der Proceß and Der Prozeß ) is a novel written by Franz Kafka from 1914 to 1915 and published in 1925 .
Son of Rosemary is a 1997 horror novel by Ira Levin , and is the sequel to Rosemary 's Baby .
`` Frogs and Scientists '' is a short short story by science fiction author Frank Herbert .
Trangviksposten is a satirical newspaper parody created by Jacob Hilditch .
101 Philosophy Problems ( 1999 ) is a philosophy book for a general audiences by Martin Cohen published by Routledge .
Yakari is a Franco - Belgian comic book series , aimed at a younger audience , written by Job and illustrated by Derib , both from Switzerland .
The Castle of Crossed Destinies ( Italian : Il castello dei destini incrociati ) is a 1973 novel by the Italian writer Italo Calvino .
Alchemical Studies is Volume 13 in The Collected Works of C. G. Jung , a series of books published by Princeton University Press in the U.S. and Routledge & Kegan Paul in the U.K. It consists of five long essays that trace Carl Jung 's developing interest in alchemy from 1929 onward .
`` Not Meant to Be '' is the fifth overall single ( first American mainstream single , third Canadian mainstream single and fourth American & Canadian single ) by Theory of a Deadman from the album Scars & Souvenirs .
The Journey of Ibn Fattouma is an intermittently provocable fable written and published by Nobel Prize - winning author Naguib Mahfouz in 1983 .
Duties Beyond Borders ( full title : Duties Beyond Borders : On the Limits and Possibilities of Ethical International Politics ) is a book by Stanley Hoffmann published in 1981 which focuses on the application of ethical principles to international relations .
Nine Tomorrows is a collection of nine short stories and two pieces of comic verse by Isaac Asimov .
The Christmas Train is a fiction novel written by David Baldacci .
Lady Connie is a novel by Mary Augusta Ward , first published in 1916 .
In Golden Blood is the third science - fiction alternate history novel by Stephen Woodworth featuring the `` Violet '' detective Natalie Lindstrom .
A Spot of Bother is the second adult novel by Mark Haddon , who is best known for his prize - winning first novel The Curious Incident of the Dog in the Night - Time .
The `` Vexilla Regis '' is a Latin hymn in long metre by the Christian poet Venantius Fortunatus , Bishop of Poitiers .
The Titan 's Curse is a 2007 fantasy - adventure novel based on Greek mythology written by Rick Riordan .
El Orinoco ilustrado y defendido ( The Orinoco illustrated and defended ) , is a book written by the Jesuit missionary Joseph Gumilla .
A Dragon at Worlds ' End ( 1997 ) is a fantasy novel written by Christopher Rowley .
Ghost / Hellboy is a DC Comics / Dark Horse Comics two - issue crossover comic book mini - series written by Mike Mignola with art by Scott Benefiel published May to June 1996 featuring fictional heroes Ghost and Hellboy .
2666 is the last novel by Roberto Bolaño .
Test of the Twins is a fantasy novel by Margaret Weis and Tracy Hickman .
Jeffrey Bernard is Unwell is a play by Keith Waterhouse about real - life journalist Jeffrey Bernard .
The Genius of Christianity ( French : Génie du christianisme ) is a work by the French author François - René de Chateaubriand , written during his exile in England in the 1790s as a defense of the Catholic faith , then under attack during the French Revolution .
New Arabian Nights by Robert Louis Stevenson , first published in 1882 , is a collection of short stories previously published in magazines between 1877 and 1880 .
The Affirmation is a 1981 science fiction novel by Christopher Priest .
The Final Four of Everything is a 2007 book written by Mark Reiter and Richard Sandomir on the subject of bracketology .
Gerald 's Game is a 1992 suspense novel by Stephen King .
The Man Whose Teeth Were All Exactly Alike is a realist , non - science fiction novel authored by Philip K. Dick .
`` The Married Couple '' ( `` Das Ehepaar '' ) is a 1922 short story by Franz Kafka .
In the First Circle ( Russian : В круге первом , V kruge pervom ; also published as The First Circle ) is a novel by Aleksandr Solzhenitsyn released in 1968 .
Anarchism and Other Essays is a book by anarchist Emma Goldman , first published in 1910 by Mother Earth Publishing Association .
Outerbridge Reach is a 1992 novel by American novelist Robert Stone .
Fortune and Glory is an Eisner Award -- nominated 3-issue American comic book limited series by Brian Michael Bendis , telling the story of his attempts to break into Hollywood by writing screenplays for his noir comics .
The Unquiet Earth is Denise Giardina 's third novel .
Family Happiness ( Russian : Семейное счастье ( Semeynoye Schast'ye ) ) is an 1859 novella written by Leo Tolstoy , first published in The Russian Messenger .
Shakespeare 's Villains is a one - man play , created and performed by Steven Berkoff .
The Irregular at Magic High School , known in Japanese as Mahōka Kōkō no Rettōsei ( 魔法科高校の劣等生 , lit . `` The Poor Performing Student of a Magic High School '' ) , is a Japanese web novel series by Tsutomu Satō .
Buried Thunder is a young adult novel written by British author Tim Bowler .
Der Fall Deruga ( The Deruga Case ) is a novel by Ricarda Huch first published in German in 1917 about a physician charged with killing his ex - wife .
Anne Frank and Me is a 2001 novel by husband - wife writing team Cherie Bennett and Jeff Gottesfeld .
The Book of Abramelin tells the story of an Egyptian mage named Abramelin , or Abra - Melin , who taught a system of magic to Abraham of Worms , a Jew in Worms , Germany , presumed to have lived from c.1362 - -c.1458 .
The Secret Texts , is a fantasy book series by Holly Lisle .
The Stone of Laughter ( Arabic : حجر الضحك ) is a Lebanese novel , written in 1990 by author Hoda Barakat set during the Lebanese Civil War .
What Was Lost is the 2007 début novel by Catherine O'Flynn .
The Story of B is a 1996 novel written by Daniel Quinn and published by Bantam Publishing .
Freddy and Simon the Dictator ( 1956 ) is the 24th book in the generally humorous children 's series Freddy the Pig written by American author Walter R. Brooks and illustrated by Kurt Wiese .
Niourk ( published 1957 ) is a science fiction novel by the French writer Stefan Wul .
Courtship Rite is a science fiction novel by American writer Donald Kingsbury , originally serialized in Analog magazine in 1982 .
Pictures from an Institution is a 1954 novel by American poet Randall Jarrell .
If You Liked School You 'll Love Work is a collection of short stories from novelist Irvine Welsh .
Choper , Coffee , Gilson refers to the casebook entitled Cases and Materials on Corporations , edited by Jesse H. Choper , John C. Coffee , Jr. , and Ronald J. Gilson .
The De Inventione is a handbook for orators that Marcus Tullius Cicero composed when he was still a young man .
Ingenious Pain is the first novel by English author , Andrew Miller , published in 1997 .
Rameau 's Nephew , or the Second Satire ( or The Nephew of Rameau , French : Le Neveu de Rameau ou La Satire seconde ) is an imaginary philosophical conversation by Denis Diderot , written predominantly in 1761 - 2 and revised in 1773 - 4 .
Tempest - Tost , published in 1951 by Clarke Irwin , is the first novel in The Salterton Trilogy by Canadian novelist Robertson Davies .
The Begum 's Fortune ( French : Les Cinq cents millions de la Bégum ) , also published as The Begum 's Millions , is an 1879 novel by Jules Verne , with some elements which could be described as utopian and others which seem clearly dystopian .
A Place Called Freedom is a work of historical fiction by Ken Follett .
Some Luck is a 2014 novel by Jane Smiley .
Tunes for Bears to Dance To is a young adult novel written by American author Robert Cormier that discusses themes of morality from the perspective of an 11-year - old named Henry .
Blood of Amber is the Locus Award nominated second book in the second Chronicles of Amber series by Roger Zelazny , and the seventh book overall .
Celebration of Life is a one - hour English play written and directed by Sachin Gupta .
Claudine at School ( French : Claudine à l'école ) is a 1900 novel by the French writer Colette .
Report to the Principal 's Office is a 1991 young adult novel by the American author , Jerry Spinelli .
`` You Needed Me '' is a song written by Randy Goodrum , who describes it as being about `` unconditional undeserved love . ''
The Girl in the Tangerine Scarf is a novel written by American author Mohja Kahf and published in 2006 .
Beyond the Barrier ( original title : `` The Tree of Time '' ) is a science fiction novel by Damon Knight .
Blake and Mortimer is a Belgian comics series created by the Belgian writer and comics artist Edgar P. Jacobs .
God Bless You , Mr. Rosewater , or Pearls Before Swine , is a novel written by Kurt Vonnegut , published in 1965 .
The Story of a Modern Woman is a novel written by English author Ella Hepworth Dixon .
Duma Key is a novel by American novelist Stephen King published on January 22 , 2008 by Scribner .
The Invention of Everything Else is a novel written by American author Samantha Hunt , published in 2008 .
Tuf Voyaging is a 1986 science fiction fix - up novel by George R. R. Martin , first published in hardcover by Baen Books .
The Great Indian Novel is a satirical novel by Shashi Tharoor .
The Sun , My Father ( Northern Sami : Beaivi , áhčážan ) is a 1991 poetry collection by Finnish Sami author Nils - Aslak Valkeapää .
Henry IV , Part 1 is a history play by William Shakespeare , believed to have been written no later than 1597 .
Etidorhpa , or , the end of the earth : the strange history of a mysterious being and the account of a remarkable journey is the title of a scientific allegory or science fiction novel by John Uri Lloyd , a pharmacognocist and pharmaceutical manufacturer of Cincinnati , Ohio .
Christie Malry 's Own Double - Entry ( 1973 ) is the penultimate novel by the late British avant - garde novelist B. S. Johnson .
The Swiss Family Robinson ( German : Der Schweizerische Robinson ) is a novel by Johann David Wyss , first published in 1812 , about a Swiss family shipwrecked in the East Indies en route to Port Jackson , Australia .
Around the Moon ( French : Autour de la Lune , 1870 ) , Jules Verne 's sequel to From the Earth to the Moon , is a science fiction novel which continues the trip to the moon which was only partially described in the previous novel .
My Driver is a novel by English author Maggie Gee , and is the sequel to My Cleaner .
Introduction to Kant 's Anthropology ( French : Introduction à l'Anthropologie ) is an introductory essay to Michel Foucault 's translation of Immanuel Kant 's 1798 book Anthropology from a Pragmatic Point of View -- a textbook deriving from lectures he delivered annually between 1772/73 and 1795/96 .
The Roving Shadows ( French : Les Ombres errantes ) is a 2002 fiction book by the French writer Pascal Quignard .
The Blood Crows , published in 2013 is the twelfth volume of the Eagle Series by Simon Scarrow .
The Great Mathematical Problems is a 2013 book by Ian Stewart .
`` The System of Doctor Tarr and Professor Fether '' is a dark comedy short story by the American author Edgar Allan Poe .
The Sacred Art of Stealing is a satirical crime novel by the Scottish writer Christopher Brookmyre .
One of Those Hideous Books Where the Mother Dies ( 2004 ) is a novel in verse by Sonya Sones .

This Night 's Foul Work is a crime - novel by French author Fred Vargas , an entry in her Commissaire Adamsberg series .
The Adventures of Cyclops and Phoenix was a four - issue comic book mini - series written by Scott Lobdell , drawn by Gene Ha , and published by American company Marvel Comics in 1994 .

The Gas Heart or The Gas - Operated Heart ( French : Le Cœur à gaz ) is a French - language play by Romanian - born author Tristan Tzara .

Thomas Carnacki is a fictional occult detective created by English fantasy writer William Hope Hodgson .

The Ultimate Alphabet ( ISBN 1 - 85145 - 050 - 5 ) is a best - selling book by Mike Wilks .
Good Natured is a book by primatologist Frans de Waal on animal behavior and the evolution of ethics .
Welcome to Temptation is a contemporary romance written by Jennifer Crusie and released in 2000 .
It 's a Matter of Survival is a 1991 book by Anita Gordon and David Suzuki .
Monkeewrench ( released later in the United Kingdom as Want to Play ? ) , is the first novel by author team P. J. Tracy .
A Luneta Mágica ( English : The Magical Glasses ) is a 1869 novel written by Brazilian Romantic writer Joaquim Manuel de Macedo .
`` The Vale of Lost Women '' is one of the original short stories about Conan the Cimmerian , written by American author Robert E. Howard , but not published during his lifetime .
Animal Farm is an allegorical and dystopian novella by George Orwell , first published in England on 17 August 1945 .
The Unfinished Memoirs ( Bengali : অসমাপ্ত আত্মজীবনী ) is the autobiography by Sheikh Mujibur Rahman .
Steal Like an Artist : 10 Things Nobody Told You About Being Creative is a book on coming up with creative ideas , by Austin Kleon , published in 2012 from Workman Publishing .
Metaphysical Foundations of Natural Science ( German : Metaphysische Anfangsgründe der Naturwissenschaft ) is a 1786 book by Immanuel Kant .
Belchamber is a 1904 novel by Howard Sturgis .
Tales of Common Insanity ( Czech : Příběhy obyčejného šílenství ) ( 2001 ) is a play by Petr Zelenka which won the Alfréd Radok Award for Best Play .
Busting Vegas ( stylized as Busting Vega$ ) is a 2005 book by Ben Mezrich about a group of MIT card counters and blackjack players commonly known as the MIT Blackjack Team .
Ring Round the Moon is a 1950 adaptation by the English dramatist Christopher Fry of Jean Anouilh 's Invitation to the Castle ( 1947 ) .
Hygiene and the Assassin ( French : Hygiène de l'assassin ) is the first novel of the Belgian novelist Amélie Nothomb .
The Fires of Spring ( 1949 ) is the second novel published by American author James A. Michener .
The Rolling Years is the first novel by the American writer Agnes Sligh Turnbull ( 1888 - -1982 ) and it is set in Westmoreland County , Pennsylvania , just east of Pittsburgh .
Mastering the Art of French Cooking is a two - volume French cookbook written by Simone Beck and Louisette Bertholle , both of France , and Julia Child of the United States .
Labyrinths ( 1962 ) is a collection of short stories and essays by Jorge Luis Borges translated into the English - language .
The Patron Saint of Butterflies is a young - adult novel by author Cecilia Galante .
Blue / Orange is a play written by English dramatist , Joe Penhall .
Canne al vento ( ( ˈkanne al ˈvɛnto ) ; Italian for `` Reeds in the wind '' ) is a novel by the Italian author and Nobel Prize winner Grazia Deledda .
Emily 's Quest is a novel and the last of the Emily trilogy by Lucy Maud Montgomery .
An Universal Biographical and Historical Dictionary ( London , 1800 ) was a landmark book written and published by British author John Watkins .
Edge of Eternity is a historical and family saga novel by Welsh - born author Ken Follett , published in 2014 .
Midnight and Jeremiah ( OCLC 9091853 ) is a 1943 children 's book by Sterling North , which was the basis for the 1948 Disney film So Dear to My Heart .
Ceremonies in Dark Old Men is a play by Lonne Elder III that premiered Off Broadway at St. Mark 's Playhouse in a production by the Negro Ensemble Company in 1969 .
Latin ! or Tobacco and Boys is a play by Stephen Fry , written in 1979 .
Hecyra ( English : The Mother - in - Law ) is a comedic Latin play by the early Roman playwright Terence .
The House of Dies Drear by Virginia Hamilton is a children 's mystery novel , with sinister goings - on in a reputedly haunted house .
A Truce , and Other Stories is a collection of six short stories by Mary Tappan Wright .
`` The Black Stranger '' is one of the stories by Robert E. Howard about Conan the Cimmerian , it was produced in the 1930s but not published in his lifetime .
Abaddón el exterminador is the last novel by Argentine author Ernesto Sabato .
Dream Jungle is a novel by Jessica Hagedorn , a Filipino American author .
Lucky Luke contre Phil Defer is a Lucky Luke adventure in French , written and illustrated by Morris it was the eighth title in the original series and was published by Dupuis in 1956 .
Rear Admiral Charles Davis Lucas VC ( 19 February 1834 -- 7 August 1914 ) was an Irish recipient of the Victoria Cross .
Vasif Durarbayli ( Azerbaijani : Vasif Durarbəyli ; born February 24 , 1992 ) is an Azerbaijani Grandmaster who was born on February 24 , 1992 and won that title at the World Youth Chess Championship for boys under 18 .
Niranjan Bhagat , ( Gujarati : નિરંજન ભગત Hindi : निरंजन भगत ) ; born May 18 , 1926 in Ahmedabad ) , full name Niranjan Narhari Bhagat , is a Gujarati poet and commentator who won the 1999 Sahitya Akademi Award for Gujarati language for his critic Gujarati Sahiyta - Purvardha Uttarardha .
In 2006 , Thích Quảng Độ was awarded the Thorolf Rafto Memorial Prize , in recognition of `` personal courage and perseverance through three decades of peaceful opposition against the communist regime in Vietnam , and as a symbol for the growing democracy movement '' .
Semyon Kosberg was awarded the Lenin Prize ( 1960 ) , Order of Lenin , three other orders and different medals .
Swati Ghate ( Marathi : स्वाती घाटे ) ( born 16 January 1980 ) is an Indian chess player and a Woman Grandmaster .
Aleksandr Alov ( Russian : Александр Александрович Алов ) ( September 26 , 1923 -- December 12 , 1983 ) was a Soviet film director and screenwriter , he was granted the honorary title of People 's Artist of the USSR in 1983 ( together with Vladimir Naumov ) .
Cpl . Oliver Hughes ( 1844 - -1911 ) of the Union Army 's 12th Kentucky Infantry was awarded the Medal of Honor for action , which culminated in his 20 February 1865 capture of the Confederate States Army 's 11th South Carolina 's flag .
Harry Cator VC , MM ( 24 January 1894 -- 7 April 1966 ) was an English recipient of the Victoria Cross , the highest and most prestigious award for gallantry in the face of the enemy that can be awarded to British and Commonwealth forces .
On March 27 , 1997 , Yad Vashem recognized Johan Benders and Gerritdina Letteboer as Righteous Among the Nations .
Prince Claus Awards named Sami Ben Gharbia in 2012 for his innovative cyber - activism works mainly through social media .

The Doors were inducted into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame in 1993 .
Joanna Majdan - Gajewska ( née Majdan ; born 9 June 1988 in Koszalin ) is a Polish chess player with the title of Woman Grandmaster ( WGM ) .
Georg Kieninger ( 5 June 1902 in Munich -- 25 January 1975 in Düsseldorf ) was a German chess player and International Master ( IM ) .
Rūdolfs Gaitars ( 1907 - -1945 ) was a Waffen - Obersturmführer in the Waffen SS during World War II . He was the first Latvian to be awarded the German Cross in Gold .
Lieutenant General Charles Augustus Goodfellow VC CB ( 29 November 1836 -- 1 September 1915 ) was an English recipient of the Victoria Cross , the highest and most prestigious award for gallantry in the face of the enemy that can be awarded to British and Commonwealth forces .
Mijo Udovčić ( September 11 , 1920 - September 8 , 1984 ) was a Yugoslavian chess player , who became the first Croatian Grandmaster in 1962 .
Steve Rotfeld is an American television producer and Emmy Award - winning writer .
Kyung - Chik Han ( December 29 , 1902 - -April 19 , 2000 ) was a Korean pastor and church planter and the recipient of the 1992 Templeton Prize for Progress in Religion .

Archibald Mathies ( June 3 , 1918 -- February 20 , 1944 ) posthumously received the Medal of Honor as an enlisted member of the U.S. Army Air Forces during World War II .
Nigel Thomson ( 1945 - -1999 ) is an Australian artist who won the Archibald Prize twice .
Heinrich Ochs ( 19 April 1915 -- 21 October 1943 ) was a highly decorated Oberleutnant in the Wehrmacht during World War II . He was also a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves ( German : Ritterkreuz des Eisernen Kreuzes mit Eichenlaub ) .
Harold Ackroyd VC , MC ( 18 July 1877 -- 11 August 1917 ) was an English recipient of the Victoria Cross , the highest and most prestigious award for gallantry in the face of the enemy that can be awarded to British and Commonwealth forces .
Ustad Moinuddin Khan has performed his solo programmes under National programme of music on Tuesday as well as Saturday Night on All India Radio a number of times In 2014 , Government of India conferred upon him its fourth - highest civilian award the Padma Shri .
Frederick Gugenheim Gregory ( 22 December 1893 - -27 November 1961 ) was a British botanist , plant physiologist and winner of the Royal Medal .
Archibald Freeman ( August 13 , 1847 -- January 26 , 1918 ) was an American soldier who received the Medal of Honor for valor during the American Civil War .
Violet Tendencies is a 2010 romantic comedy film directed by Casper Andreas , written by Jesse Archer , and starring Mindy Cohn and Marcus Patrick .
Dariya Dil is a 1988 Hindi family drama film directed by K. Ravi Shankar and starring Govinda , Kimi Katkar , Roshni and Raj Kiran .

Where East Is East is a 1929 silent movie starring Lon Chaney as an animal trapper in Laos .
McGlusky the Sea Rover is a 1935 British comedy action film directed by Walter Summers and starring Jack Doyle , Tamara Desni and Henry Mollison .

Nee Sukhame Ne Korukunna is a Telugu movie ( 2008 ) with Raja and Sneha in the lead roles . Giribabu had earlier produced and directed several hit films including Devatalara Deevinchandi , Simha Garjana , Merupu Dadi and Muddu Muchata .

The Vicar of Dibley received multiple British Comedy Awards ( including a Best TV Comedy Actress Award for Emma Chambers ) , two International Emmys , and was a multiple British Academy Television Awards nominee .

Amelia and Michael is a 2007 British drama short film directed by Daniel Cormack , starring Anthony Head and Natasha Powell and executive produced by Richard Johns .
The Girl from Missouri ( originally called Born to Be Kissed ) is a 1934 American romantic comedy - drama film starring Jean Harlow and Franchot Tone .
Colossus of the Arena ( Italian : Maciste il gladiatore più forte del mondo , also known as Death on the Arena ) is a 1962 Italian peplum film directed by Michele Lupo and starred by Mark Forest .

Dheiva Thaai ( English : Divine Mother ) is a Tamil language film starring M. G. Ramachandran in the lead role .
Der Ladenprinz ( The Shop Prince ) is a 1928 German silent film directed by Erich Schönfelder , starring Harry Halm , La Jana and Paul Henckels and also with La Jana , Sig Arno and Hermine Sterler .

The Sheepman is a tongue - in - cheek 1958 Western film directed by George Marshall and starring Glenn Ford , Shirley MacLaine and Leslie Nielsen .
Billy 's Love Making is a 1915 American silent romantic drama directed by and starring William Garwood and Violet Mersereau .
Majaa is a 2005 Tamil film directed by Shafi , starring Vikram , Asin , Vadivelu , Pasupathy , Anu Prabhakar , Vijayakumar , Manivannan , Sindhu Tolani , Murali and Biju Menon .
Felix on the Job is a 1916 silent comedy film directed by George Felix and starring Lon Chaney .

Who Killed Lamb ? is a 1974 TV film starring Stanley Baker as a detective investigating a murder .
I Start Counting is a British thriller film released in 1970 , directed by David Greene and starring Jenny Agutter in one of her first major roles .
Requiem for a Gunfighter is a 1965 American western film , the last picture directed by Spencer Gordon Bennet , produced by Alex Gordon , and starring Rod Cameron , Stephen McNally , Mike Mazurki , Dick Jones , and Olive Sturgess .
The Dark Corner is a 1946 black - and - white film noir directed by Henry Hathaway starring Lucille Ball , Mark Stevens and Clifton Webb .
La Biblia en pasta ( Spanish for `` The Bible in pulp paper '' , a Spanish idiom for something hard and difficult ) is a 1984 Spanish comedy film directed by Manuel Summers .
Maayi is a South Indian Tamil film released in 2000 which stars Sarath Kumar and Meena in lead roles wherein Vadivelu 's comedy performance was critically acclaimed .
Getawarayo is a 1964 Sri Lankan drama film starring Gamini Fonseka .

Atom Man vs. Superman ( 1950 ) , Columbia 's 43rd serial and the second live - action Superman screen appearance , both featuring Kirk Alyn as Superman , finds Lex Luthor ( Lyle Talbot ) , secretly the Atom Man , blackmailing the city of Metropolis by threatening to destroy the entire community .
Lucky 13 is a 2005 American - Colombian romantic comedy film directed by Chris Hall and starring Brad Hunt , Harland Williams , Lauren Graham , Sasha Alexander , Debra Jo Rupp , John Doe , Kaley Cuoco and Taryn Manning .
Bourbon Street Beat is a private detective series which aired on the ABC network from 1959 - 1960 and featured Richard Long as Rex Randolph , Andrew Duggan as Cal Calhoun , Van Williams as Kenny Madison , and Arlene Howell as Melody Lee Mercer , the secretary at the New Orleans detective agency in which they worked .
Bang Bang Kid is a 1967 western film produced by Sidney W. Pink and starring Tom Bosley .
The Death and Life of Bobby Z , also known as Bobby Z and Let 's Kill Bobby Z , is a 2007 American / German action film , directed by John Herzfeld , and starring Paul Walker , Laurence Fishburne , Olivia Wilde and Joaquim de Almeida .
Praanam is a Telugu film starring Allari Naresh and Sadha in the Lead directed by Malli .
Star Gazers ( formerly known as Jack Horkheimer : Star Hustler and later Jack Horkheimer : Star Gazer ) is a five - minute astronomy show on American public television previously hosted by Jack Foley Horkheimer , executive director of the Miami Space Transit Planetarium .
Extraordinary Measures is a 2010 medical drama film starring Brendan Fraser , Harrison Ford , and Keri Russell .
Abu Hassan Penchuri ( Abu Hassan The Thief ) is a 1955 Malaysian romantic film directed by B. Narayan Rao , and starring Malaysian silver - screen legend P. Ramlee .
Lady Blue Shanghai is a 16-minute internet promotion motion picture for Dior starring Marion Cotillard , Gong Tao , Emily Stofle , Cheng Hong , Lu Yong and Nie Fei .
Pyar Kiye Jaa ( English : Carry on Loving ) is a 1966 Hindi language movie directed by C. V. Sridhar starring Kishore Kumar , Shashi Kapoor , Mehmood , Om Prakash , Mumtaz , Kalpana and Rajasree .
Black Ransom is a 2010 Hong Kong action thriller film directed by Wong Jing and Venus Keung and starring Simon Yam , Michael Miu and Fala Chen .
Lalach is 1983 Indian Hindi film directed by Shankar Nag starring Vinod Mehra , Bindiya Goswami , Ranjeet , Pran , Kajal Kiran , Anant Nag .
Love the Beast is a 2009 documentary film directed by Eric Bana , and featuring Bana , Jay Leno , Jeremy Clarkson , and Phil McGraw .
Cheggers Plays Pop was a British children 's game show broadcast on BBC1 from 10 April 1978 to 7 November 1986 hosted by Keith Chegwin , who is commonly known to the British public as `` Cheggers '' .
Ils étaient cinq is a French comedy film from 1952 , directed by Jack Pinoteau , written by Roland Laudenbach , starring Marcel André and Louis de Funès .
Give a Girl a Break is a 1953 musical comedy film directed by Stanley Donen , starring Debbie Reynolds and the dance team of Marge and Gower Champion .
Kızın Varmı Derdin Var is a 1973 Turkish film , directed by Halit Refiğ and starring Ayhan Işık , Perihan Savaş and Öztoprak Ünsal .

Hi I 'm Tony is a Malayalam psychological thriller film directed by Lal Jr. The film stars Lal in the title role alongside Asif Ali and Miya .
Double Bunk is a 1961 British black - and - white comedy set on a houseboat , that stars Ian Carmichael and Sid James .

Der Herzensphotograph ( The Heart Photographer ) is a 1928 German silent film directed by Max Reichmann starring Harry Liedtke and Robert Garrison and also with La Jana and Betty Bird .

Too Many Winners is a 1947 American crime film directed by William Beaudine and starring Hugh Beaumont , Trudy Marshall and Ralph Dunn .

Rises Over Japan is a concert film by the Mark IV of Deep Purple , directed by Tony Klinger and released in 1985 .

The Mind Cure is a 1912 silent short film starring Pearl White .
The Castaway Cowboy is a 1974 adventure film released by Walt Disney Productions starring James Garner , Vera Miles , Eric Shea , and Robert Culp about a Texas rancher who gets shanghaied , then jumps ship and finds himself washed ashore in Hawaii .

The Miracle Woman is a 1931 American pre - Code drama film directed by Frank Capra and starring Barbara Stanwyck , David Manners , and Sam Hardy .

The Woman on Trial is a 1927 American silent film directed by Mauritz Stiller , starring Pola Negri , and based on the play Confession by Erno Wajda ( aka Ernest Vajda ) .

The Plainsman is a 1936 American Western film directed by Cecil B. DeMille and starring Gary Cooper and Jean Arthur .

The Half - Naked Truth is a 1932 American Pre - Code comedy film directed by Gregory LaCava and featuring Lee Tracy as a carnival pitchman who finagles his girlfriend , a fiery hoochie dancer played by Lupe Vélez , into a major Broadway revue under the auspices of an impresario portrayed by Frank Morgan .

Liu Shouwen 's assistants Lü Yan ( 呂兗 ) and Sun He ( 孫鶴 ) initially supported Liu Shouwen 's son Liu Yanzuo as his successor and put up a defense , and the defense held , even after Liu Shouguang took Liu Shouwen to the city to show the troops that Liu Shouwen had been captured .
Theodor Krancke ( 30 March 1893 -- 18 June 1973 ) was an admiral with the Kriegsmarine during World War II and a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves .
The 28th Rifle Division was a rifle division in the Soviet Red Army during the Russian Civil War , World War II and the Cold War .
George Mahoney ( born January 15 , 1865 ) was a fireman first class serving in the United States Navy during the Spanish-- American War who received the Medal of Honor for bravery .
Henry Bohlen ( October 22 , 1810 -- August 22 , 1862 ) was an American Civil War Union Brigadier General .
Wacław Sieroszewski ( 1858 -- 1945 ) was a Polish writer , Polish Socialist Party activist , and soldier in the World War I - era Polish Legions ( decorated with the Virtuti Militari ) .
He served in the Tank Corps during World War I and in the Special Operations Executive , SOE , in World War II . In his SOE role , `` Captain '' Selwyn Jepson was recruiting officer for F section , the independent French section .
Paul Lacombe de La Tour was a French army officer who served from 1910 to 1940 through both World War I and World War II . He eventually rose to the rank of Lieutenant - colonel and led the 97th Reconnaissance Group of the Infantry Division into combat during the Battle of France .
Charles H. Marsh ( 1840 -- January 25 , 1867 ) was a Union Army soldier in the American Civil War and a recipient of the United States military 's highest decoration , the Medal of Honor , for his actions during a skirmish in the Valley Campaigns of 1864 .
Gotfred Jensen ( November 20 , 1872 in Denmark -- December 26 , 1945 ) was a United States Army soldier who received the Medal of Honor for actions during the Philippine - American War .
During World War II , the destroyer escort USS Paul G. Baker ( DE-755 ) was named for Baker .
Christos Palaskas ( Greek : Χρήστος Παλάσκας , Gotista , Ioannina , 1788 -- Drakospilia , Parnassos , 1822 ) was a Greek chieftain during the Greek War of Independence .
Nathan Kimball ( November 22 , 1822 -- January 21 , 1898 ) was a physician , politician , postmaster , and military officer , serving as a general in the Union army during the American Civil War .
Alix Pasquet ( unknown--1958 ) was a World War II fighter pilot , one of only five Haitian members of the Tuskegee Airmen , a soccer star , and a political revolutionary . He was killed while leading a coup attempt against Haitian President Francois Duvalier in 1958 .
A Starr revolver ( Starr DA ) is a double - action revolver which was used in the western theater of the American Civil War until the U.S. Ordnance Department persuaded the Starr Arms Co. to create a single - action variant after discontinuation of the Colt .
Frank Tolan ( May 1854 -- 1899 ) was an American private in the U.S. Army who served with the 7th U.S. Cavalry during the Great Sioux War of 1876 - -77 .
The 3rd Alpine Division Julia was a World War II light Infantry division of the Italian Army , specializing in Mountain Combat .
Robert Cowdin ( September 18 , 1805 -- July 9 , 1874 ) was a businessman , a field officer in the Union Army during the American Civil War and a local politician in Massachusetts .
Gustav Altmann ( 13 April 1912 -- 20 February 1981 ) was a member of the Fallschirmjäger during World War II and recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross ( Ritterkreuz des Eisernen Kreuzes ) for his actions during the Battle of Fort Eben - Emael .
Sottotenente de Vascello Umberto Calvello was a World War I fighter ace credited with five victories .
Eduard Florus Harald Auffarth ( also Auffahrt ) ( ? ? -- 12 October 1946 ) Royal House Order of Hohenzollern , Iron Cross , Silver Wound Badge , Hanseatic Cross , was a World War I German fighter ace credited with 29 victories .
Vice Admiral Richard Bell Davies VC CB DSO AFC ( 19 May 1886 -- 26 February 1966 ) , also known as Richard Bell - Davies , was a British Royal Navy officer and World War I fighter pilot .
Leland Francis Norton ( Mar. 12 , 1921 San Bernardino , California to May 27 , 1944 , France ) was a captain in the US Army Air Corp who died heroically during a bombing mission in World War II in Europe .
Heinrich Holk ( also Holke or Henrik Holck ) ( 1599 - -1633 ) was a Danish - German mercenary in both Christian IV of Denmark 's and Albrecht von Wallenstein 's service during the Thirty Years ' War .
William H. Horsfall ( March 3 , 1847 -- October 22 , 1922 ) was one of the youngest men to receive the Medal of Honor during the American Civil War .
Omicron Velorum ( ο Vel , ο Velorum ) is a star in the constellation Vela .
HD 118203 is a K - type subgiant star located in the Ursa Major constellation 289 light years away from Earth .
Gamma Persei ( Gamma Per , γ Persei , γ Per ) is a binary star system in the constellation Perseus .
Kepler-40 , formerly known as KOI-428 , is an F - type star in the constellation Cygnus .
HD 93833 is an orange giant star in Sextans that shines with a vmag of 5.85 from its approximate position of RA 10h 49.7 m , Dec -9 ° 51 ' .
HD 167042 is a 6th magnitude K - type giant star located approximately 163 light - years away in Draco constellation .
Messier 34 ( also known as M 34 or NGC 1039 ) is an open cluster in the constellation Perseus .
20 Monocerotis ( 20 Mon ) is a star in the constellation Monoceros .
MACS J0717.5 + 3745 ( MACS J0717 or MACS 0717 for short ) is a large galaxy cluster located 5.4 billion light years away in the constellation Auriga , appearing in the MAssive Cluster Survey ( MACS ) .
HD 181720 b is an extrasolar planet which orbits the G - type main sequence star HD 181720 , located approximately 190 light years away in the constellation Sagittarius .
NGC 5087 is an elliptical galaxy located in the constellation Virgo .
HD 167965 is a 6th magnitude star in the constellation Lyra , approximately 590 light years from Earth .
HD 175541 is an intermediate - mass subgiant star in the constellation Serpens .
NGC 1483 is a barred spiral galaxy located in the southern constellation of Horologium and member of the Dorado Group .
HD 72659 is a yellow dwarf star in the Hydra constellation .
Messier 83 ( also known as the Southern Pinwheel Galaxy , M83 or NGC 5236 ) is a barred spiral galaxy approximately 15 million light - years away in the constellation Hydra .
HD 185269 is a seventh magnitude star approximately 153 light - years away in the constellation Cygnus .
NGC 1232 is an intermediate spiral galaxy about 60 million light - years away in the constellation Eridanus .
V373 Scuti was a nova , which appeared in 1975 in the constellation Scutum and reached magnitude 6 .
HD 173780 is a 5th magnitude star in the constellation Lyra , approximately 250 light years away from Earth .
HD 1461 ( 32 G. Ceti ) is a G0V class star slightly more massive than the Sun ( G2V ) , and located about 76 light - years away in the constellation of Cetus .
Kampekalven Mountain ( 71 ° 56′S 7 ° 46′E ) is a mountain , 2,200 metres ( 7,200 ft ) high , forming the northeast end of the Filchner Mountains in Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Marble Point is a rocky promontory on the coast of Victoria Land , Antarctica , located at 77 ° 26 ' S latitude and 163 ° 50 ' E longitude .
Ustra Peak ( Vrah Ustra \'vr&h ' us - tra\ ) is a rocky peak of 195 m on the coast of Walker Bay , Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Ménier Island ( 64 ° 59′S 63 ° 37′W ) is an island , the largest in a small island group lying in the mouth of Flandres Bay , 4 nautical miles ( 7 km ) northeast of Cape Renard , off the west coast of Graham Land , Antarctica .
Pavie Ridge or Cap Pavie or Île Pavie is a rocky ridge located at 68 ° 34′S 66 ° 59′W in Antarctica which rises over 500 m. It extends south and west from Martin Glacier to Moraine Cove , and forms the southeastern limit of the Bertrand Ice Piedmont , on the west coast of Graham Land .
Kent Plateau ( 80 ° 44′S 157 ° 50′E ) is an ice - covered plateau , 12 nautical miles ( 22 km ) long and 4 nautical miles ( 7 km ) wide , extending northward from Mount Egerton and Kiwi Pass to the vicinity of Mount Hamilton , in the Churchill Mountains of Antarctica .
The Keystone Cliffs ( 71 ° 35′S 68 ° 13′W ) are a set of cliffs , 610 metres ( 2,000 ft ) high , marking the east face of the sedimentary ridge between Mercury Glacier and Venus Glacier , on the east coast of Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Dream Island is an island lying 0.7 km ( 0.43 mi ) south - east of Cape Monaco , off the south - west coast of Anvers Island in Wylie Bay , in the Palmer Archipelago of Antarctica .
Irvine Glacier ( 74 ° 42′S 63 ° 15′W ) is a glacier , 40 miles ( 64 km ) long , draining southeast between the Guettard Range and the Rare Range into the northern part of Gardner Inlet , Antarctica .
Manning Massif ( 70 ° 42′S 67 ° 50′E ) is a large rock massif between Loewe Massif and McLeod Massif in the eastern part of the Aramis Range , Prince Charles Mountains , Antarctica .
Good Glacier ( 84 ° 12′S 177 ° 50′E ) is a wide glacier draining the eastern slopes of the Hughes Range in Antarctica between Mount Brennan and Mount Waterman and flowing northeast to enter the Ross Ice Shelf to the east of Mount Reinhardt .
Potter Peninsula is a low ice - free peninsula between Potter Cove and Stranger Point in south - west King George Island , in the South Shetland Islands of Antarctica .
Wrigley Gulf is an embayment about 115 miles wide along the coastline of Antarctica , lying seaward of the Getz Ice Shelf .
Kitano - ura Cove ( 69 ° 0′S 39 ° 36′E ) is a cove indenting the northern side of East Ongul Island , Antarctica .
Gatson Ridge ( 79 ° 43′S 158 ° 51′E ) is a jagged ridge , 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) long , that runs east from the southern part of Bowling Green Plateau in the Brown Hills of the Cook Mountains , Antarctica .
The Ross Ice Shelf is the largest ice shelf of Antarctica ( an area of roughly 487,000 square kilometres ( 188,000 sq mi ) and about 800 kilometres ( 500 mi ) across : about the size of France ) .
Tirizis Island ( Bulgarian : остров Тиризис , `` Ostrov Tirizis '' \'os - trov ti-'ri - zis\ ) is the rocky island off the east coast of Robert Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica extending 1.05 km in east - west direction and 350 m wide .
Eurus Ridge ( 77 ° 26′S 162 ° 59′E ) is a ridge between Cerberus Valley and Clio Glacier in the Olympus Range of the McMurdo Dry Valleys of Antarctica .
Mount Judd ( 85 ° 4′S 170 ° 26′E ) is a prominent bare rock mountain , over 2,400 metres ( 7,900 ft ) high , surmounting the ridge running north from Mount White in the Supporters Range in Antarctica .
Mintz Peak ( 76 ° 53′S 126 ° 3′W ) is a small peak rising above the southeast corner of Mount Hartigan in the Executive Committee Range , Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
Melfjellet ( 68 ° 21′S 59 ° 12′E ) is a prominent rock outcrop in the eastern part of the Hansen Mountains , Antarctica , about 2 nautical miles ( 4 km ) southeast of See Nunatak .
Djibouti ( /dʒɪˈbuːti/ ji - BOO - tee ; Arabic : جيبوتي‎ Jībūtī , French : Djibouti , Somali : Jabuuti , Afar : Gabuuti ) , officially the Republic of Djibouti , is a country located in the Horn of Africa .
Zavadovskiy Island ( 66 ° 43′S 86 ° 24′E ) is an ice - covered island in the West Ice Shelf near Antarctica .
Guéguen Point ( 65 ° 9′S 64 ° 7′W ) is a point forming the south end of Hovgaard Island , in the Wilhelm Archipelago , Antarctica .
Kilifarevo Island ( Bulgarian : остров Килифарево , `` Ostrov Kilifarevo '' ' os - trov ki - li-'fa - re - vo ) is an ice - free island in the Aitcho group on the west side of English Strait in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Renier Point ( 62 ° 36′34``S 59 ° 48′21''W ) is a narrow point forming the east extremity of both Burgas Peninsula and Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Irving Island ( 66 ° 25′S 67 ° 4′W ) is a small island at the northeastern end of the Barcroft Islands , in the Biscoe Islands , Antarctica .
Molar Massif ( 71 ° 38′S 163 ° 45′E ) is a large mountain massif immediately east of the Lanterman Range in the Bowers Mountains of Antarctica .
Kardam Buttress ( Kardamov Rid \kar-'da - mov ' rid\ ) is a sloping buttress projecting 1 km northwards from St. Ivan Rilski Col into Huron Glacier on Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica , and has precipitous and partly ice - free western slopes .
Janulis Spur ( 85 ° 7′S 90 ° 27′W ) is a rock spur which extends eastward from the Ford Massif between Green Valley and Aaron Glacier , in the Thiel Mountains of Antarctica .
Altarduken Glacier is a small glacier just east of The Altar at the head of Grautskala Cirque , in the Humboldt Mountains of Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
The Flett Crags ( 80 ° 39′S 23 ° 35′W ) are rock crags on the north slope of the Read Mountains , 5 nautical miles ( 9 km ) north of Mount Wegener , in the Shackleton Range , Antarctica .
Halfmoon Bluff ( 85 ° 13′S 175 ° 38′W ) is a rock bluff overlooking the east side of Shackleton Glacier , rising immediately north of the mouth of Brunner Glacier , in the Cumulus Hills of Antarctica .
The Larson Nunataks ( 82 ° 45′S 48 ° 0′W ) are a small cluster of nunataks lying along the east side of the Forrestal Range , 1.5 nautical miles ( 3 km ) southeast of Mount Malville , in the Pensacola Mountains of Antarctica .
Iskollen Hill ( 72 ° 51′S 4 ° 9′W ) is a broad , snow - covered hill with a few rock outcrops at the summit , lying southwest of Raudberg Valley in the southwestern part of the Borg Massif , in Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Heuser Nunatak ( 72 ° 2′S 160 ° 38′E ) is a small nunatak that lies 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) south of Mount Phelan and marks the southern extremity of the Emlen Peaks in the Usarp Mountains of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Laclavère Plateau ( 63 ° 27′S 57 ° 47′W ) is a plateau , 10 nautical miles ( 19 km ) long and from 1 to 3 nautical miles ( 2 to 6 km ) wide , rising to 1,035 metres ( 3,400 ft ) between Misty Pass and Theodolite Hill , Trinity Peninsula , Antarctica .
Hockey Cirque ( 83 ° 17′S 156 ° 30′E ) is a glacial cirque 0.5 nautical miles ( 1 km ) wide along the east wall of Ascent Glacier in the Miller Range of Antarctica .
Landry Bluff ( 85 ° 16′S 175 ° 37′W ) is a rock bluff in the Cumulus Hills , Antarctica , standing just north of the mouth of Logie Glacier where the latter joins Shackleton Glacier .
Alberts Glacier ( 66 ° 52′S 64 ° 53′W ) is a heavily crevassed glacier in Antarctica .
Mason Inlet ( 72 ° 57′S 60 ° 25′W ) is an ice - filled inlet which recedes 28 kilometres ( 15 nmi ) southwest between Cape Mackintosh and the coastline south of Cape Herdman , along the east coast of Palmer Land , Antarctica .
Krivina Bay ( Bulgarian : залив Кривина , `` Zaliv Krivina '' \'za - liv ' kri - vi - na\ ) is a 5 km wide bay indenting for 3 km the west coast of Trinity Island in the Palmer Archipelago , Antarctica .
Magnis Ridge ( 80 ° 5′S 156 ° 12′E ) is a rock ridge 1.5 nautical miles ( 3 km ) west of Derrick Peak , forming the divide between Magnis Valley and Metaris Valley in the Britannia Range , Antarctica .
The Harold Byrd Mountains ( 85 ° 26′S 146 ° 30′W ) are a group of exposed mountains and nunataks which extend in an east -- west direction between the lower part of Leverett Glacier and the head of the Ross Ice Shelf in Antarctica .
Rezen Knoll ( Bulgarian : Vrah Rezen \'vr&h ' re - zen\ ) is a knoll rising to 433 m in eastern Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Megalestris Hill is a rocky hill , 35 m ( 115 ft ) high , in the south part of Petermann Island in the Wilhelm Archipelago , Antarctica .
Mount Grytøyr ( 72 ° 0′S 4 ° 31′E ) is a broad ice - topped mountain , 2,695 metres ( 8,840 ft ) high , between Flogeken Glacier and Stuttflog Glacier in the Mühlig - Hofmann Mountains of Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Lizotte Creek ( 77 ° 42′S 162 ° 29′E ) is a meltwater stream , 2,000 metres ( 2,200 yd ) long , flowing southeastwards from the extreme southwestern tip of Matterhorn Glacier to the northeast end of Lake Bonney in Taylor Valley , Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Rigonce ( pronounced ( ˈɾiːɡɔntsɛ ) ) is a settlement in the Municipality of Brežice in eastern Slovenia .
Lapinlahti Airfield is an airfield in Lapinlahti , Finland , about 3 nautical miles ( 5.6 km ; 3.5 mi ) northeast of Lapinlahti municipal centre .

The South - west Corner Commonwealth Marine Reserve is a marine reserve on the lower south west and southern coast of Western Australia , one of 14 in the South - west Commonwealth Marine Reserves Network .
