Mingyi Swa of Prome ( Burmese : မင်းကြီးစွာ , pronounced : ( mɪ́ɴdʑíswà ) ; c. 1435 - -1482 ) was viceroy of Prome from 1446 to 1482 during the reigns of kings Narapati I , Thihathura I and Minkhaung II of Ava .
Andrew of Saint Victor ( died October 1175 ) was an Augustinian canon of the abbey of Saint Victor in Paris , a Christian Hebraist and biblical exegete .
Leslie Hubricht ( born 11 January 1908 in Los Angeles , California , died 16 September 2005 in Meridian , Mississippi ) was an American biologist and malacologist .
Sir Richard Hoghton , 1st Baronet ( 28 September 1570 -- 1630 ) was a politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1601 and 1611 .
Emile Brichard ( Arsimont , 20 December 1899 -- Villers - Poterie , 8 July 2004 ) was a Belgian cyclist .
Yasuji Kiyose ( 清瀬保二 Kiyose Yasuji , 13 January 1900 -- 14 September 1981 ) was a Japanese composer .
Yu Zhining ( 于志寧 ) ( 588 - -665 ) , courtesy name Zhongmi ( 仲謐 ) , formally Duke Ding of Yan ( 燕定公 ) , was a chancellor of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , during the reigns of Emperor Taizong and Emperor Gaozong .
Malcolm Webster Ford ( 1862 - 1902 ) was an American athlete and journalist .
Reynold Pympe ( c.1371 - 1426 ) , of Nettlestead and Pympe 's Court in East Farleigh , Kent , was an English politician .
The Reverend Alexander Petrie Campbell OBE ( 4 June 1881 - 13 December 1963 ) was an Australian - born Congregational church minister and chairman of the Congregational Union of Australia and New Zealand from 1937 until 1939 .
John Sutton , 1st Baron Dudley , KG ( 25 December 1400 -- 30 September 1487 ) was an English nobleman .
Wilhelm Wilmers ( b. at Boke in Westphalia , 30 January 1817 ; d. at Roermond , Netherlands , 9 May 1899 ) was a German Jesuit Professor of philosophy and theology .
Harry Brearley ( 18 February 1871 -- 14 July 1948 ) was an English metallurgist , usually credited with the invention of `` rustless steel '' ( later to be called `` stainless steel '' in the anglophone world ) .
Medet Serhat ( 1943 , Iğdır -- 12 December 1994 , Istanbul ) was a Turkish lawyer of Kurdish descent , from an aristocratic family of Igdir branch of widely spread Retkan tribe .
Pei Songzhi ( 372 - -451 ) , courtesy name Shiqi , was a historian and politician who lived in the late Eastern Jin dynasty and the Liu Song dynasty .
Peter Winter ( baptized 28 August 1754 -- 17 October 1825 ) was a German opera composer who followed Mozart and preceded Weber , acting as a bridge between the two in the development of German opera .
Toki Jurozayemon Mitsuchika ( died 1582 ) was a retainer of the Akechi clan and relative of Akechi Mitsuhide .
Paula Preradović ( 12 October 1887 -- 25 May 1951 ) , known professionally as Paula von Preradović or by her married name as Paula Molden , was an Austrian writer and poet .
Cao Juru ( Chinese : 曹菊如 ) ( May 1901 -- January 1981 ) was the 2nd governor of the People 's Bank of China ( 1954 - -1964 ) .
Herbert W. Armstrong ( 31 July 1892 -- 16 January 1986 ) founded the Radio Church of God which was incorporated 21 October 1933 and was renamed Worldwide Church of God 1 June 1968 , as well as starting Ambassador College ( later Ambassador University ) 8 October 1947 .
George Charles of Hesse - Kassel ( 8 January 1691 in Kassel -- 5 March 1755 ) was a prince of Hesse - Kassel and a Prussian General .
Clemens Scheitz ( 2 September 1899 -- 24 October 1980 ) was a German musician and actor who appeared in the Werner Herzog films The Enigma of Kaspar Hauser ( 1974 ) , Heart of Glass ( 1976 ) , Stroszek ( 1977 ) and Nosferatu the Vampyre ( 1979 ) .
Premchand ( pronounced ( mʊnʃi preːm t͡ʃənd̪ ) ) ( 31 July 1880 -- 8 October 1936 ) , better known as Munshi Premchand , Munshi being an honorary prefix , was an Indian writer famous for his modern Hindustani literature .
George Seawright ( c. 1951 - 3 December 1987 ) was a controversial unionist politician and paramilitary in Northern Ireland who was assassinated by the Irish People 's Liberation Organisation ( IPLO ) during the Troubles .
Saint Paulinus of Trier ( died 358 ) was bishop of Trier and a supporter of Athanasius in the conflict with Arianism .
Jean de Liège , ( c.1330 - 1381 ) was a 14th - century sculptor of Flemish origin , mainly active in France , who specialized in funerary sculptures .
Max Grünhut ( 7 July 1893 -- 6 February 1964 ) was a German - British legal scholar and criminologist .
Anna Cheyne ( 1926 - 2002 ) was an artist and sculptor was born and educated in England but moved to Northern Ireland after her marriage to architect Donald Cheyne .
Zhang Zongcang ( Chinese : 张宗苍 ; 1686 - -1756 ) , courtesy name as Mocun , is a famed Chinese landscape painter in the Qing Dynasty .
Mervyn Hamilton Rylance ( 1906 - -1983 ) was a rugby union player and architect in Brisbane , Queensland , Australia .
Alfred Woodroffe ( 1 September 1918 -- 23 July 1964 ) was an English cricketer active in first - class cricket from 1947 - -1948 .
Guy Sircello ( 1936 - -1992 ) was an American philosopher best known for his analytic approach to philosophical aesthetics .
Tanchelm ( died 1115 ) , also known as Tanchelm of Antwerp , Tanchelijn , Tanquelin or Tanchelin , was a heretical itinerant preacher , critical of the established Roman Catholic church , active in the Low Countries around the turn of the 11th and 12th centuries .
Benjamin Mandel ( 1887-August 8 , 1973 ) AKA `` Bert Miller '' was a New York city school teacher and activist who later became a director of research for the House Un - American Activities Committee and the Senate Internal Security Subcommittee .
Reuben Sturman ( 1924 -- October 27 , 1997 ) was an American pornographer and businessman from Ohio .
Giuseppe Leggiadri Gallani ( 1516 - -1590 ) was an Italian poet and dramatist .
Raymond Furnell ( 18 May 1936 -- 10 July 2006 ) was the Dean of York Minster from 1994 to 2003 .
Cassius Chaerea ( died 41 ) served as a centurion in the army of Germanicus and in the Praetorian Guard under the emperor Caligula , whom he eventually assassinated in January 41 .
William A. Mathews ( 1800 - -1856 ) was a 19th - century Texas colonist , soldier , courier and quartermaster in the Texas Revolution .
Samyeongdang ( 1544 - -1610 ) , also known by his dharma name Yujeong , was a Korean Buddhist monk during the Joseon era .
Sim Var ( Khmer : ស៊ឹម វ៉ា ; 2 February 1906 -- October 1989 ) was a Cambodian politician .
Edward Bertram Johnston ( 11 January 1880 -- 6 September 1942 ) , known as Bertie Johnston , was the Western Australian Legislative Assembly member for Williams - Narrogin from 1911 to 1928 , and a Senator from 1929 until 1942 .
Johannes Hermanus Michiel Kock ( Graaf - Reinet , 1835 - Elandslaagte 1899 ) was a Boer general and soldier .
Pere Salvatge or Peire / Peyre Salvagge was a Catalan troubadour of the late thirteenth century ( fl . 1280 - -1287 ) .
Joseph - Édouard Barès ( 27 November 1872 -- 27 August 1954 ) was a French general and a pioneer of military aviation .
Benjamin Booth ( 1732 - -1806 ) was an English director of the East India Company and art collector .
George Manners - Sutton ( 1 August 1751 -- 15 February 1804 ) was a British politician , the eldest son of Lord George Manners - Sutton .
Edmund Schuster ( 7 September 1851 -- 5 July 1932 ) was a German engineer and mathematician who contributed to the field of special functions and complex analysis being a pioneer in the field of harmonic analysis .
Joseph Jenkins ( 27 February 1818 -- 26 September 1898 ) , was an educated tenant farmer from Tregaron , Ceredigion , mid - Wales who , when aged over 50 , suddenly deserted his home and large family to seek his fortune in Australia .
Rodger Head ( 20 June 1939 -- 8 July 2012 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for St Kilda in the Victorian Football League during the 1960s .
Thomas Butler , 1st Baron Cahir or Caher ( died 1558 ) was an Irish peer .
Francis Edward Paget ( 1806 - -1882 ) was an English clergyman and author .
Christopher Nyholm Shawcross , KC ( 20 June 1905 -- 18 August 1973 ) was a British lawyer and Labour politician .
Gerhard Alois Westrick ( 1889 - -1957 ) was a German lawyer and businessman who represented several major American companies in Germany before World War II . He was known for his efforts during a trip to New York in 1940 to gain support for the Nazi government .
Andrey Aleksandrovich Gershun ( Russian : Андре́й Алекса́ндрович Ге́ршун , 22 October 1903 -- 6 December 1952 ) was a Soviet physicist , well known for his works in Photometric and Optics , one of the founders of Vavilov State Optical Institute Hydrooptics Science School .
Yeh Ming - hsun ( 25 September 1913 -- 21 November 2009 ) , was a Chinese journalist and newspaper editor .
Yohanan Levi ( Hebrew : יוחנן לוי‎ ; born 1901 , died 20 July 1945 ) was a Hebrew linguist and historian , specialising in the Second Temple period .
Eric Meadus ( 1931 - -1970 ) was an English artist whose work was exhibited in the Royal Academy and Paris Salon .
Captain Thomas Harwood ( died 1652 ) was a Virginia soldier , landowner and politician .
Paul Yuzyk ( 24 June 1913 -- 9 July 1986 ) was a Canadian historian and Senator remembered as the `` father of multiculturalism . ''
Bhulabhai Desai ( 13 October 1877 -- 6 May 1946 ) was an Indian independence activist and acclaimed lawyer .
Joseph Victor Viviand - Morel ( 1843 , born near Lons - le - Saunier -- 28 December 1915 , Lyon ) was a French horticulturist and gardener .
Jan Frans van Dael or Jean - François van Dael ( 27 May 1764 -- 20 March 1840 ) was a Flemish painter and lithographer specializing in still lifes of flowers and fruit .
William Holme Van Buren ( born in Philadelphia , 5 April 1819 ; died in New York , 25 March 1883 ) was an American surgeon .
Jack Hood ( 17 December 1902 -- 1 July 1992 ) was a British boxer who was British and European welterweight champion in the 1920s and 1930s .
The Blessed Hugh Faringdon O.S.B. ( died 1539 ) , earlier known as Hugh Cook , later as Hugh Cook alias Faringdon and Hugh Cook of Faringdon , was a Benedictine monk who presided as the last Abbot of Reading Abbey in the English town of Reading .
Gonzalo , Duke of Aquitaine ( 5 June 1937 -- 27 May 2000 ) ( Gonzalo Víctor Alfonso José Bonifacio Antonio María y Todos los Santos de Borbón y Dampierre , was a grandson of King Alfonso XIII of Spain .
Gino D'Auri ( 1937 -- 26 January 2007 ) was an Italian flamenco , fusion and classical guitarist .
Helaman Pratt ( 31 May 1846 -- 26 November 1909 ) was an early leader of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter - day Saints in the U.S. states of Nevada and Utah and later in Mexico .
Maurice Wilk was a well - known American violinist who performed as a member of the Alma Trio from 1953 until his sudden death in 1963 .
Halla Pai Huhm ( alternately , Halla Huhm or Pai Halla ; 1922 - -1994 ) was a Korean - American dancer and the most well - known teacher of Korean dance in Hawaii .
George Francis Stewart PC ( 1 November 1851 -- 12 August 1928 ) , known as G. F. Stewart , was an Irish land agent and public servant .
Jin Xuan ( died 209 ) , courtesy name Yuanji ( 元機 ) , was a minor warlord and Administrator of Wuling Commandery in the late Eastern Han Dynasty .
Sir John Anstruther , 4th Baronet and 1st Baronet PC ( 27 March 1753 -- 26 January 1811 ) was a Scottish politician .
Charles Steffen ( 1927 - 1995 ) was a self - taught artist from Chicago , Illinois .
Sidney Bradshaw Fay ( 13 April 1876 in Washington , D.C. -- 29 August 1967 in Lexington , Massachusetts ) was an American historian , whose examination of the causes of World War I , The Origins of the World War ( 1928 ; revised edition 1930 ) remains a classic study .
Mischa Auer ( 17 November 1905 -- 5 March 1967 ) was a Russian - born American actor who moved to Hollywood in the late 1920s .
Noah Buxton ( 6 November 1876 -- 26 May 1967 ) was an English cricketer who played first - class cricket for Derbyshire between 1902 and 1911 .
Antonio Circignani ( 1560 - -1620 ) was an Italian painter of the late - Renaissance ( Mannerism ) period and early Baroque .
James Grainger ( c. 1721 - -1766 ) Scottish doctor , poet and translator , is well - known figure in 18th - century English literature .
Alby O'Connor ( 23 October 1893 -- 28 August 1944 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
James Rivers ( 1603 -- 8 June 1641 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1640 .
Laura Gardin Fraser ( 1889 - -1966 ) was an American sculptor and the wife of sculptor James Earle Fraser .
Aed mac Donn Ó Sochlachain ( died 1226 ) was Erenagh of Cong and an Irish musician .
Kasinather Saunthararajah S.C. , P.B.M. ( 3 March 1930 -- 17 June 2010 ) , known professionally as K. S. Rajah , was a Senior Counsel and Judicial Commissioner of the Supreme Court of Singapore .
Thomas de Thelwall ( died 1382 ) was an English judge and Crown official who spent part of his career in Ireland , where he held office as Master of the Rolls in Ireland and clerk to the Privy Council of Ireland .
Henry A. G. Lee ( c. 1818 -- 1851 ) was a soldier and politician in Oregon Country in the 1840s .
Hans Lewy ( 20 October 1904 -- 23 August 1988 ) was a German born American mathematician , known for his work on partial differential equations and on the theory of functions of several complex variables .
Harry Iauko ( died 10 December 2012 ) was a ni - Vanuatu politician .
Dagobert Friedländer ( 19 February 1826 -- 27 June 1904 ) was a banker and one of only two Jewish members of the House of Lords of Prussia .
Eiríkur Benedikz ( 1907 - 1988 ) was an Icelandic scholar , diplomat and book collector .
Sir John Eldon Bankes GCB PC KC LLD ( 17 April 1854 - 31 December 1946 ) was a Welsh judge of the King 's Bench Division of the High Court of Justice , and later the Lord Justice of Appeal .
Eleanor of Sicily ( 1325 - -1375 ) was Queen of Aragon from 1349 until 1375 as the third wife of King Peter IV .
John H. Dessauer , also known as Hans Dessauer , ( 13 May 1905 -- 12 August 1993 ) was a German - American chemical engineer and an innovator in developing xerography .
Jean - Albert Dinkespiler ( 1927 - 2014 ) was a French engineer and former Chief of the European Joint Research Centre .
Andrey Tissin ( Russian : Андрей Тиссин ; 5 July 1975 -- 1 March 2008 ) was a Russian sprint canoer who competed in the late 1990s and early 2000s ( decade ) .
Alfred Métraux ( 5 November 1902 -- 11 April 1963 ) was a Swiss anthropologist , ethnologist and human rights leader .
Bernard Holden MBE ( 15 March 1908 -- 4 October 2012 ) was a twentieth century railway engineer and manager with Southern and British Railways and a founding father of standard gauge railway preservation in the United Kingdom .
Conall mac Máele Coba , called Conall Cóel , ( died 654 ) was an Irish king and is said to have been High King of Ireland .
Suhita or Soheeta was a Javanese queen regnant and the sixth monarch of the Majapahit empire , ruling from 1429 to 1447 .
Cyrus Nutt ( 4 September 1814 Trumbull County , Ohio - 23 August 1875 Bloomington , Indiana ) served as the fifth president of Indiana University .
Emanuel Ninger ( 1845 -- 1924 ) , known as `` Jim the Penman '' , was a counterfeiter in the late 1880s .
Nicholas of Ilok ( Bosnian and Croatian : Nikola Iločki , Hungarian : Újlaki Miklós ; 1410 - -1477 ) was Ban of Croatia , Slavonia , Dalmatia and Macsó , Voivode of Transylvania and titular King of Bosnia from 1471 until his death .
Eleanor Ambrose ( 1718 - -1816 ) was a celebrated beauty and Catholic heiress .
Rededi , Rededia , Rededya or Ridada ( died 1022 ) was a legendary leader of the Kassogians , a Circassian tribe from the North Caucasus .
Enrique Serrano ( 1891 - -1965 ) was an Argentine actor and comedian in the 1940s and 1950s .
Bernard N. Fields ( March 24 , 1938 -- January 31 , 1995 ) was an American microbiologist and virologist .
Moedomo Soedigdomarto , also spelled Mudomo Sudigdomarto , ( 29 November 1927 , Magetan -- 5 November 2005 , Bandung ) was an Indonesian mathematician , educator and professor at the Bandung Institute of Technology , of which he was president ( rektor , for explanation , see Rector ( academia ) ) .
Nathan Cohn ( 2 January 1907 -- 16 November 1989 ) was an American electrical engineer , who was best known for his contributions to the control of interconnected electric power systems .
James Stawpert ( c1775 - 1814 ) was a Newcastle based brewer 's clerk / songwriter of the early 19th century .
Otis Ruel Redinger ( December 31 , 1896 -- September 1969 ) was a professional football player who played 1 season in the National Football League , with the Canton Bulldogs .
Jean de Gribaldy ( 18 July 1922 -- 2 January 1987 ) was a French road cyclist and directeur sportif .
Hermann Görtz ( 15 November 1890 -- 23 May 1947 ) was a German spy in Britain and Ireland before and during World War II .
Ibrahim El - Gohary ( died 31 May 1795 ) is a famous Copt who was Egypt 's prime minister during the second half of the 18th century .
Prof William Fisher Cassie ( usually referred to simply as Fisher Cassie in his field and as Bill Cassie by his friends ) FRSE CBE LLD ( 1905 - 1985 ) was a British civil engineer and academic .
Baron Johann Rudolf de Steiger ( or de Steiguer ) ( 1778- † 1834 ) was a Swiss nobleman who immigrated to the United States in the 19th century .
Edgar Tolson ( 1904 - -1984 ) was a woodcarver from Kentucky who became a well - known folk artist .
Ernest Favenc ( 21 October 1845 -- 14 November 1908 ) was an explorer of Australia , a journalist and historian .
Georg Braun ( also Brunus , Bruin ; 1541 -- 10 March 1622 ) was a topo - geographer .
Julia Severance ( 1877 - 1972 ) was an artist mainly known for her contributions in transforming the College Seal for Oberlin College .
Dr Gavin Brown Clark ( 1846 - 5 July 1930 ) was the MP for Caithness from 1885 to 1900 .
Hendrik Lodewijk Drucker ( Amsterdam , 11 August 1857 -- The Hague , 5 September 1917 ) was a Dutch liberal politician of the Free - thinking Democratic League .
Nell Martin ( 1890 - -1961 ) was an American author from Illinois specializing in light - hearted mysteries and short stories .
John Shene ( January 17 , 1901 -- January 1968 ) was an American bobsledder who competed in the 1930s .
Olive Price ( 1903 - -1991 ) was an American writer of books and plays for children .
Arthur Sanger ( 26 March 1918 -- 3 December 1999 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Hanne Kjærholm ( 24 May 1930 , Hjørring -- 22 June 2009 ) was a Danish architect who also taught at the Danish Academy , where she became a professor in 1989 .
Albert von Kölliker ( born Rudolf Albert Kölliker ; 6 July 1817 -- 2 November 1905 ) was a Swiss anatomist , physiologist , and histologist .
Zhang Miao ( died 195 ) , courtesy name Mengzhuo , was an official who lived in the late Eastern Han dynasty .
Sahib I Giray , Sahib Khan Girai ( 1501 - -1551 ) -- a khan of the Crimean Khanate in 1532 --1551 .
Francesco da Urbino ( 1545 - -1582 ) was an Italian painter and artist .
Sylvia Lynd ( née Dryhurst ) ( 1888 -- 21 February 1952 ) was a poet , essayist , short story writer and novelist .
William Broughton Carr ( 1836 - -1909 ) , was a British author and beekeeper .
Father John Ikataere Rarikin , MSC ( 5 January 1944 − 8 February 2014 ) was a Roman Catholic priest who served as the Ecclesiastical Superior of the Mission Sui Iuris of Funafuti since 2010 to 2002 .
Albert Pike Lucas ( 1862 - -1945 ) was an American landscape , figure , and portrait painter ; also a sculptor .
James Brome ( died 1719 ) was an English clergyman and travel writer .
John Alexander Scott Coutts ( 9 December 1902 -- 5 August 1962 ) , better known by the pseudonym John Willie , was the artist , fetish photographer , editor , and publisher of the soft - porn cult magazine Bizarre .
Harry Angelman ( 13 August 1915 -- 8 August 1996 ) was a British consultant paediatrician who identified Angelman Syndrome .
Blessed Giovanni Battista Mazzucconi ( 1 March 1826 -- 7 September 1855 ) was an Italian priest from the Pontifical Institute for Foreign Missions .
Ulderico Carpegna ( 24 June 1595 -- 24 January 1679 ) was an Italian jurist and Cardinal .
Zheng Lücheng ( Chinese 郑律成 , Korean 정률성 , Kwangju ; 13 August 1918 -- 7 December 1976 ) was a Korea - born Chinese composer .
John Hodgkins DD ( died 1560 ) was an English suffragan bishop .
Bernardo Schiaffino ( 1678 -- 6 May 1725 ) was an Italian sculptor of the Baroque period , active mainly in his natal city of Genoa .
Hugh de Mapenor ( or Hugh de Mapenore ; died April 1219 ) was a medieval Bishop of Hereford .
Gustafva Sofia Hjärne ( 4 July 1780 -- 6 December 1860 ) , was a Finnish baroness , writer and salon holder .
William Willoughby , 1st Baron Willoughby of Parham ( c.1515 -- 30 July 1570 ) was an English nobleman and soldier who in 1547 was made an hereditary peer of the House of Lords .
Galan Erilich was a king of the Picts from 510 to 522 .
Giuseppe Aonzo ( 1887 - 1954 ) was an Italian sailor famous for his involvement in the Battle of Premuda .
John Evelyn Denison , 1st Viscount Ossington PC ( 27 January 1800 -- 7 March 1873 ) was a British statesman .
Pieter de Ring , or Ryng ( 1615/1620 -- 22 September 1660 ) was a Dutch Golden Age painter of still lifes .
William Gerard Barry ( 1864 in Ballyadam , Carrigtwohill -- 9 September 1941 ) was an Irish painter .
David McCheyne Newell ( 23 March 1898 -- 1986 ) was an American journalist , novelist , and children 's writer perhaps most famous for his books regarding early twentieth century rural life in western central Florida .
Du Bois Agett ( 1796 - -1866 ) was an early settler in Western Australia .
James Henry Young ( 15 May 1834 -- 9 May 1908 ) was an Australian colonial businessman and politician and Speaker of the New South Wales Legislative Assembly .
William Moise ( 1922 - -1980 ) was a visual artist , primarily an abstract impressionist painter , working in a regionalist style .
Sir James Perrot ( 1571 -- 4 February 1636 ) was a Welsh writer and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1597 and 1629 .
Pieter Arnout Dijxhoorn ( 1810 - -1839 ) , a Dutch marine painter , was born at Rotterdam in 1810 .
Richard Brydges Beechey ( 1808 -- 14 March 1895 ) was an Anglo - Irish painter and Admiral in the Royal Navy .
Ram Niwas Mirdha ( 24 August 1924 -- 29 January 2010 ) was an Indian politician from Rajasthan .
Richard Henry Williams ( June 13 , 1852 -- 1924 ) was a Canadian lumber merchant and political figure in the province of Saskatchewan .
Moses Hull ( 1836 - -1907 ) was a minister for the Seventh - day Adventist Church in the 19th century , who later became a Spiritualist lecturer and author .
James Thomason ( born 3 May 1804 , Great Shelford , near Cambridge , Cambridgeshire , England died 27 September 1853 , Bareilly , India ) was a British colonial governor .
Joe Cockroft ( 20 June 1911 - -February 1994 ) was an English footballer .
Achille Eugène Finet ( 1863 , Argenteuil -- 1913 , París ) was a French botanist best known for his study of orchids native to Japan and China .
William Bedell Stanford ( 16 January 1910 -- 30 December 1984 ) was an Irish classical scholar and senator .
Rajesh Pilot died on 11 June 2000 in a car accident near Jaipur .
Liu Yuxi ( Wade - Giles : Liu Yü - hsi ; simplified Chinese : 刘禹锡 ; traditional Chinese : 劉禹錫 ; pinyin : Liú Yǔxī ) ( 772 - -842 ) was a Chinese poet , philosopher , and essayist , active during the Tang Dynasty .
Alfred M. Moen ( 27 December 1916 -- 17 April 2001 ) was an American inventor and founder of Moen , Inc. He invented the single - handed mixing faucet .
Joshua Brookes ( 24 November 1761 -- 10 January 1833 ) was a British anatomist and naturalist .
Alexander Sauli , C.R.S.P. ( 15 February 1534 -- 11 October 1592 ) , was an Italian priest , who is called the `` Apostle of Corsica '' .
Waman Raghunath Shennoi Varde Valaulikar ( 23 June 1877 -- 9 April 1946 ) known popularly as Shenoi Goembab was a noted Konkani writer and activist .
Osborne Reynolds FRS ( /ˈrɛnəldz/ ; 23 August 1842 -- 21 February 1912 ) was a prominent innovator in the understanding of fluid dynamics .
Amédée Galzin ( 1 May 1853 , Parrinet , Aveyron -- 14 February 1925 , Parrinet ) was a French veterinarian and mycologist .
George Kovalenko , SJ ( born in 1900 , Russian Empire - died on 5 November 1975 , Rome , Italy ) was a Russian Jesuit , a priest of the Catholic Church and a member of Russian apostolate .
Pedro Eugênio de Castro Toledo Cabral ( 29 March 1949 -- 20 April 2015 ) was a Brazilian politician who was an MP from 1998 to 2014 .
William Wriothesley or Wrythe ( pronunciation uncertain : /ˈraɪzli/ RYE - zlee ( archaic ) , /ˈrɒtsli/ ROTT - slee ( present - day ) and /ˈraɪəθsli/ RYE - əths - lee have been suggested ) ( died 1513 ) was an officer of arms at the College of Arms in London .
Gaero of Baekje ( ? --475 , 455 - -475 ) was the 21st king of Baekje , one of the Three Kingdoms of Korea .
Mao Wenlong ( 1579 - -1629 ) , courtesy name Zhennan , was a Chinese military general of the Ming dynasty .
Anglurah Agung ( died 31 October 1686 ) was a king of Gelgel , the paramount kingdom on Bali , who ruled at a time when the political unity of the island began to break down .
Lorne Kidd Smith ( 1880 -- c. 1966 ) was a Canadian painter best known for his scenes from the War of 1812 .
John Wallop , 2nd Earl of Portsmouth ( 29 June 1742 -- 16 May 1797 ) , styled Hon . John Wallop from 1743 to 1749 and Viscount Lymington from 1749 to 1762 , was a British nobleman .
Wei Yuanzhong ( 魏元忠 ) ( died 707 ) , né Wei Zhenzai ( 魏真宰 ) , formally Duke Zhen of Qi ( 齊貞公 ) , was an official of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty and Wu Zetian 's Zhou Dynasty , serving as chancellor during the reigns of Wu Zetian and her son Emperor Zhongzong .
John Netterville , 2nd Viscount Netterville ( c.1603 - 1659 ) was an Irish peer , soldier and statesman .
Charles Mulford Robinson ( 1869 - -1917 ) was a journalist and a writer who became famous as a pioneering Urban Planning theorist .
Gendün Druppa ( Tibetan : དགེ་འདུན་གྲུབ་པ། , Wylie : dge ' dun grub pa , 1391 - -1474 ) was considered posthumously to be the 1st Dalai Lama .
Nat Langham ( 20 May 1820 -- 1 September 1871 ) was an English middleweight bare - knuckle prize fighter .
Eloise Jelinek ( February 2 , 1924 , Dallas - December 21 , 2007 , Tucson ) was an American linguist specializing in the study of syntax .
Bryan Ranft ( 14 July 1917 -- 14 April 2001 ) was an historian of the Royal Navy , who served as Professor of History and International Affairs at the Royal Naval College , Greenwich , 1967 - 1977 .
Mauritius Renninger ( 8 June 1905 - 22 December 1987 ) was a German theoretical physicist noted for his work on crystallography and x - ray optics .
Francesco Zucchi ( Italian pronunciation : ( franˈtʃesko ˈdzukki ) ; Venice , 1692 - 1764 ) , was an Italian engraver , active mainly in Northern Italy .
Étienne de Carheil ( 20 November 1633 -- 27 July 1726 ) was a French Jesuit priest who became a missionary to the Iroquois and Huron Indians in the New World .
Nathaniel Penistone Davis ( 1895 - 1973 ) was an American career diplomat .
Ivo Perović ( 1882 − 1958 ) was Regent of Yugoslavia for the underage Peter II from 1934 to 1941 .
Edward England , born Edward Seegar ( c.1685 - -1721 ) was a famous African coast and Indian Ocean pirate captain from 1717 to 1720 .
Ivor Lloyd Tuckett ( 1873 - -1942 ) was a British professor of physiology , physician , and author .
Ovitigala Vithanage Samantha aka Samantha Vithanage ( died 2002 ) was a third year Management student of the University of Sri Jayewardenepura , Sri Lanka , who pioneered an anti - ragging campaign , and was killed on 7 November 2002 while in a discussion to stop the brutal practice of ragging in the faculty .
Sir Charles Eyre ( died 1729 ) was an administrator of the British East India Company and founder of Fort William , Calcutta .
Josip Vandot ( 15 January 1884 -- 11 July 1944 ) was a Slovene writer and poet who wrote mainly for young readers .
Alexis Korner ( 19 April 1928 -- 1 January 1984 ) was a British blues musician and radio broadcaster , who has sometimes been referred to as `` a founding father of British blues '' .
David Arugete ( 3 April 1921 -- 1 December 1968 ) , commonly known under his pseudonym Darío Moreno , was a Turkish polyglot singer , an accomplished composer , lyricist , and guitarist .
Avraham Deutsch ( Hebrew : אברהם דויטש‎ , born 1889 , died 25 May 1953 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for Agudat Yisrael between 1951 and 1953 .
Pierre - Paulin Gourrège ( Bordeaux , 9 June 1749 -- near Cadiz , 27 October 1805 ) was a French Navy officer and captain .
Petru Giovacchini ( 1 February 1910 - 29 September 1955 ) was a Corsican activist , born in Canale - di - Verde to an old noble Corsican family with deep - rooted pro - Italian feelings .
Boris ( Hungarian : Borisz ; c. 1114 -- c. 1154 ) , also known as Boris Kalamanos ( Greek : Βορίσης Καλαμάνος , Russian : Борис Коломанович ) was a claimant to the Hungarian throne in the middle of the 12th century .
Denis - Nicolas Le Nourry ( 18 February 1647 -- 24 March 1724 ) was a French Benedictine scholar of the Congregation of St - Maur , an ecclesiastical writer .
Sir Bartholomew Shower ( 1658 - -1701 ) was an English lawyer and politician , Recorder of London and a prominent High Tory .
Ubalda García de Cañete ( 1807 - -1890 ) was the eldest daughter of the Paraguayan dictator José Gaspar Rodríguez de Francia .
Jean - Baptiste Pillement ( 24 May 1728 -- 26 April 1808 ) was a painter and designer , known for his exquisite and delicate landscapes , but whose importance lies primarily in the engravings done after his drawings , and their influence in spreading the Rococo style and particularly the taste for chinoiserie throughout Europe .
Harutyun Hanesyan ( Armenian : Յարութիւն Հանէսեան ; 1911 -- 1987 ) was an Armenian violist and composer .
Miyoko Ito ( 27 April 1918 - 1983 ) was a Chicago artist known for her watercolor and abstract oil paintings and prints .
Nguyễn Trọng Xuyên ( 1926 - -2012 ) was a Việt Cộng , and later Vietnamese People 's Army , general .
Wilma Montesi ( 3 February 1932 -- 9 April 1953 ) was an Italian woman whose body was discovered near Rome .
Dattatreya Balkrushna Kalelkar ( Devanagari : दत्तात्रेय बाळकृष्ण कालेलकर ) ( 1 December 1895 -- 21 August 1981 ) , popularly known as Kaka Kalelkar , was an Indian independence activist , social reformer and journalist .
Richard de Morville ( died 1189 ) , succeeded his father Hugh de Morville ( died 1162 ) as Constable of Scotland and in his Scottish estates and English lands at Bozeat in Northamptonshire , and Rutland , as well as a number of feus of the Honour of Huntingdon .
Alfred Rosling Bennett ( 1850 in Islington , London -- 24 May 1928 in Matlock , Derbyshire ) was an English electrical engineer .
Dom Pedro Álvares Pereira ( 13 ? ? -- 14 August 1385 ) was a Portuguese noble of the 14th century .
Frank Dalby Davison ( 23 June 1893 - 24 May 1970 ) , also known as F.D. Davison and Freddie Davison , was an Australian novelist and short story writer .
Lee Rutland Scarborough ( 1870 - -1945 ) was an American Baptist pastor , evangelist , denominational leader and professor at the Southwestern Baptist Theological Seminary .
Fu Zhensong ( Fu Chen - sung ) or Fu Qiankun ( 1872 - -1953 ) was a grandmaster of Wudangquan martial arts .
( Samuel Victor ) Alberto Zelman ( 15 November 1874 -- 3 March 1927 ) was an Australian musician and conductor , and founder of the Melbourne Symphony Orchestra .
Berit Erbe ( 4 September 1923 -- 13 May 2009 ) was a Danish - Norwegian actress and theatrical historian .
Pribislaw II ( died : after 21 June 1316 ) was a prince from the Parchim - Richenberg line of the House of Mecklenburg .
Hálfdan Narfason ( died 1568 ) , was an Icelandic priest and Galdrmaster .
Frederick Roy Goodall ( 31 December 1902 -- 19 January 1982 ) was a professional footballer , who played for Huddersfield Town for 16 years and played 25 games for England , 12 as captain .
Garci Lasso de la Vega II , also known as `` El Joven '' ( ? - Burgos , 1351 ) was the son of Garci Lasso de la Vega `` El Viejo '' with his first wife , Juana de Castañeda .
Arnaldo Orfila Reynal ( 1897 - -1997 ) was an Argentine - Mexican publisher .
Hans Jacobs ( 30 April 1907 - 24 October 1994 ) was a German sailplane designer and pioneer .
Aaron Solomon Gumperz ( December 10 , 1723 -- 1769 ) was a Jewish German scholar and physician .
Orlando Norie ( 1832 - -1901 ) , artist of military subjects , perhaps the most prolific painter of the British army in the 19th century along with Richard Simkin .
Adam Johnston Fergusson Blair , PC ( 4 November 1815 -- 30 December 1867 ) , known prior to 1862 as Adam Johnston Fergusson , was a Canadian lawyer and politician .

Kamekichi Tokita ( 1897 - -1948 ) was a Japanese American painter and diarist .

Charles Newton Little ( 1858 - -1923 ) was an American mathematician and civil engineer .
James Hamilton , 1st Duke of Hamilton KG PC ( 19 June 1606 -- 9 March 1649 ) was a Scottish nobleman and influential political and military leader during the Thirty Years ' War and the Wars of the Three Kingdoms .
Asher Hassin ( Hebrew : אשר חסין‎‎ , 7 July 1918 -- 27 March 1995 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for Mapai and its successors between 1959 and 1969 .
Carsten Tank - Nielsen ( 16 September 1877 -- 2 August 1957 ) was a Norwegian naval officer , submarine pioneer and Rear admiral .
Vasilije Matić ( 12 June 1906 -- 20 August 1981 ) was a forestry expert from Yugoslavia .
Alice Betteridge ( 1901 at Sawyers Gully , near Maitland , New South Wales -- 1966 , Woollahra ) is known as the first deafblind child to be educated in Australia .
Addison Clark ( 1842 - -1911 ) was a co - founder and the first president of Texas Christian University ( TCU ) .
Humphrey Middlemore , O.Cart , ( died 19 June 1535 ) was an English Catholic priest and Carthusian hermit , who was executed for treason during the Tudor period .
Mobhí Clárainech ( also Berchan ; died 544 ) was an early monastic saint of Ireland , counted as one of the Twelve Apostles of Ireland .
Thomas Fane , 6th Earl of Westmorland PC ( 3 October 1681 -- 4 June 1736 ) , styled The Honourable Thomas Fane from 1691 to 1699 , was a British peer and member of the House of Lords .
Though he protested his innocence during his staged group trial with 4 other ' co - conspirators , ' and despite the protests of Western nations , Nikola Petkov was hanged on 23 September 1947 and buried in an unknown grave .
Meyer Mishkin ( d 1999 ) was a Hollywood agent .
Jack Sharpley ( 18 February 1906 -- 30 September 1968 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Hawthorn in the VFL .
Reginald H. Jones ( 11 July 1917 - 30 December 2003 ( aged 86 ) ) was the chairman and CEO of General Electric from 1972 to 1981 .
Cecil J. Allen ( 1886 - - 5 February 1973 ) was a British railway engineer and technical journalist and writer .
Jeremiah Haralson ( April 1 , 1846 -- 1916 ) , was among the first ten African - American Congressmen in the United States .
Emmott Robinson ( 16 November 1883 -- 17 November 1969 ) was an English first - class cricketer , who played for Yorkshire County Cricket Club from 1919 to 1931 .
Mary Jennifer Guinness ( née Hollwey ; 22 August 1937 -- 23 January 2016 ) , was an English - born Irish socialite and member of the Guinness family .
Gaspar Torrente Español , ( 3 October 1888 in Campo , Ribagorza , Aragon - 21 March 1970 in Barcelona , Catalonia ) , was one of the early 20th century leaders and a founding father of Aragonese nationalism .
Matilda of Frisia ( died in 1044 ) was the first queen of Henry I , King of the Franks .
Richard Teece ( 29 April 1847 -- 13 December 1928 ) was an Australian actuary , general manager and actuary of the Australian Mutual Provident Society .

Maxtla ( Nahuatl pronunciation : MASH - LAH ) was a Tepanec ruler ( tlatoani ) of Azcapotzalco from 1426 to his death in 1428 .
Amalia Küssner Coudert ( March 26 , 1863 -- May 1932 ) was an American miniaturist known for her portraits of prominent figures of the late 19th century including Caroline Astor , King Edward VII , Czar Nicholas II of Russia and Cecil Rhodes .
Niall MacGinnis ( 29 March 1913 -- 6 January 1977 ) was an Irish actor who made 80 screen appearances .
Moses de León ( c. 1250 -- 1305 ) , known in Hebrew as Moshe ben Shem - Tov ( משה בן שם - טוב די - ליאון ) , was a Spanish rabbi and Kabbalist who is considered the composer or redactor of the Zohar .
Vilmos Hellebronth ( 24 February 1895 -- 20 May 1971 ) was a Hungarian soldier during World War II , after 16 October 1944 , minister in Ferenc Szálasi 's government .
Sir Charles Malcolm Barclay - Harvey , KCMG ( 2 March 1890 -- 17 November 1969 ) was a British politician and Governor of South Australia from 12 August 1939 until 26 April 1944 .
Charles Edward Long ( 28 July 1796 -- 25 September 1861 ) , was an English genealogist and antiquary .
William Clubbe ( or Clubb ) ( 1745 - -1814 ) was an English clergyman and poetical writer .
Serena Lake ( née Thorne ) ( 28 October 1842 -- 9 July 1902 ) was an English Australian suffragist and evangelical preacher in South Australia .
John F. Carroll ( 1932 -- 1969 ) is one of 17 known people in medical history to have reached a height of 8 feet ( 2.4 m ) or more .
Aluf Aharon Remez ( Hebrew : אהרן רמז‎ , born 8 May 1919 , died 3 April 1994 ) was an Israeli civil servant , politician and diplomat , and the second commander of the Israeli Air Force .
Barry Ono ( 1876 - -1941 ) was a British variety theatre performer , collector of penny dreadfuls and benefactor of the British Library .
Jakob Hassler ( 18 December 1569 -- 1 January 1622 ) was a German Renaissance composer .
Eugen Ray ( 26 July 1957 , Gebstedt , Hebbstedt , Germany -- 18 January 1986 , Leipzig ) was a former East German sprinter who ran in the 100 metres and 200 metres .
James Colleton ( d. c. 1706 ) was a governor of the English proprietary Province of Carolina from 1686 to 1690 .
Sir Christopher Staughton , PC ( 24 May 1933 - 15 October 2014 ) was a British barrister and judge , who sat as a justice of the High Court of Justice , Court of Appeal of England and Wales and President of the Court of Appeal of Gibraltar .
Norman Reilly Raine ( 23 June 1894 -- 19 July 1971 ) was the creator of `` Tugboat Annie '' and a prolific screenwriter who won an Oscar for the screenplay of The Life of Emile Zola ( 1937 ) .
Gustav Hahn ( 27 July 1866 -- 1 December 1962 ) was a German Canadian painter , muralist and interior decorator who pioneered the Art Nouveau style in Canada .
Yehoshua Hankin ( Hebrew : יהושע חנקין‎ , 1864 -- 11 November 1945 ) was a Zionist activist who was responsible for most of the major land purchases of the Zionist Organization in Ottoman Palestine and Mandatory Palestine .
Merziye Feriqi ( or Marziya Fariqi ; Kurdish : مه‌رزیه فه‌ریقی‎ , Merziye Ferîqî ; Persian : مرضیه فریقی‎‎ ) ( 1958 -- 18 September 2005 ) was a Kurdish singer .
Shmuel Merlin ( Hebrew : שמואל מרלין‎ , 1910 -- 4 October 1994 ) was a Revisionist Zionist activist , Irgun member and Israeli politician .
Lyle Saxon ( 1891 - -1946 ) was a respected New Orleans writer and journalist who reported for The Times - Picayune .
Viktor Ferdinand Brotherus ( 28 October 1849 , Sund , Åland -- 9 February 1929 ) , Finnish botanist who studied the mosses ( Bryophyta ) , best known for authoring the treatment of ' Musci ' in Engler and Prantl 's Die Naturlichen Pflanzenfamilien .
Thomas J. Valentino ( died August 4 , 1986 ) was an American businessman of Italian descent being amongst the first to develop libraries of sound effects and taped music .
Charles Gough Howell ( born Cardiff , Wales , 1894 ; died Taiwan Camp , Formosa ( now Taiwan ) , 12 September 1942 ) was a Welsh lawyer and British colonial official , who served as Attorney General of Fiji from 1931 to 1933 , and as Attorney - General of Singapore from 1936 to 1942 .
David Gordon Allen d'Aldecamb Lumsden of Cushnie , FSAL , FSAS ( 25 May 1933 , in Quetta , Baluchistan , Empire of India ( now Pakistan ) -- 29 August 2008 , in Fort William , Scotland ) was a Scottish businessman , nationalist and sometime Baron of Cushnie - Lumsden ( in Aberdeen ) .
Chauncey Northrop Pond ( 1841 - 1920 ) was a Congregational minister ( ordained in 1866 ) devoted to missionary efforts in China prior to , and around the time of , the Boxer Rebellion .
James Fintan Lalor ( in Irish , Séamas Fionntán Ó Leathlobhair ) ( 10 March 1807 -- 27 December 1849 ) was an Irish revolutionary , journalist , and `` one of the most powerful writers of his day . ''
Thomas Perks ( 2 October 1883 - -15 January 1953 ) was an English cricketer who played one first - class match , for MCC against London County at Crystal Palace Park in August 1902 .
Vernon Dixon ( died 14 June 2009 ) was a British set decorator .
Eliseo Arredondo de la Garza ( 5 May 1870 -- 18 October 1923 ) was a Mexican politician and diplomat who briefly served as secretary of the Interior in the government of President Venustiano Carranza ; his cousin and father - in - law .
Roswell George Mills ( 1896 - 1966 ) was a Canadian journalist , poet and magazine publisher .
Neil Heywood ( 20 October 1970 -- 14 November 2011 ) was an English businessman who worked in China .
Priscus of Epirus ( c. 305 -- c. 395 AD ) was a Neoplatonist philosopher and theurgist , a colleague of Maximus of Ephesus , and a friend of the emperor Julian .
Josef Emanuel Hilscher ( 22 January 1806 -- 2 November 1837 ) was an Austrian soldier , poet and translator of other 's poetry .
Kevin F. McCready ( January 30 , 1957 -- December 5 , 2004 ) was a clinical psychologist in Fresno , California .

Werner Theunissen continued to write songs until his death due to a cardiac arrest in a restaurant in England on 18 January 2010 .
Princess Louisa of Great Britain ( Louise Anne ; 19 March 1749 -- 13 May 1768 ) was a grandchild of George II and sister of George III .
Sigmund Zeisler ( 1860 - 1931 ) was a German - Jewish U.S. attorney born in Austria and known for his defense of radicals in Chicago in the 1880s .
Álvaro Lloreda Caicedo ( 15 October 1903 -- 10 April 1985 ) was a Colombian industrialist , newspaper publisher , and politician .

John Ellis Williams ( 20 August 1924 -- 7 December 2008 ) was a novelist and writer , writing in both English and Welsh .
Hon . John Henry Brooke MLA ( 15 May 1826 -- 8 January 1902 ) , was a colonial Victorian politician .
Abraham Sternhartz ( 1862 - -1955 ) , also known as Avraham Shternhartz , was an Orthodox rabbi in Ukraine and a unique and unsurpassed figure in the chain of transmission of Breslover teachings from the early generations of the movement to the latter ones .
Lucien Rouzet ( 23 March 1886 -- 4 March 1948 ) was a French physicist and inventor , who , in 1912 , created a wireless telegraph system .
Jean - François Tartu ( Recouvrance , 11 October 1751 -- Uranie , off Gascogne , 24 October 1793 ) was a French Navy officer , and hero of the French Revolution .
Johann Ludwig von Wolzogen ( 1599 - -1661 ) was an Austrian nobleman and Socinian theologian .
S. L. Shakdhar ( died 2002 ) was a Chief Election Commissioner of India and former Secretary - General of 3rd Lok Sabha , 4th Lok Sabha and 5th Lok Sabha ( Lower House of Parliament of India ) .
Nachume Miller ( 1949 - -1998 ) was an Israeli artist who immigrated to New York City in 1973 , where he made a name for himself in the American Modern Art scene .
Ronnie Carroll ( 18 August 1934 -- 13 April 2015 ) was a Northern Irish singer , entertainer , and political candidate .
Charles Frederick Worth ( 13 October , 1825 -- 10 March , 1895 ) was an English fashion designer who founded the House of Worth , one of the foremost fashion houses of the 19th and early 20th centuries .
Thomas Tlou ( 1 June 1932 -- 28 June 2010 ) was a Botswana academic and historian , and former representative of Botswana at the United Nations .
Douglas Syphax ( 1842 - 4 February 1890 ) or Douglass Syphax was a member of the African - American aristocracy , from a wealthy land - owning family .
Sir Richard FitzLewis or FitzLowys ( by 1453 - 1528 ) , of Bardwell , Suffolk and West Horndon , Essex , was an English politician .
Samuel Halkett ( 1814 - -1871 ) was a Scottish librarian , now known for his work on anonymous publications .
James Boaden ( 1762 - -1839 ) was an English biographer , dramatist , and journalist .
Thomas Paul ( 1773 - -1831 ) was a Baptist minister in Boston , Massachusetts , affiliated with the African Meeting House and the Education Society for the People of Colour .
Reidar Ødegaard ( 24 November 1901 -- 11 April 1972 ) was a Norwegian cross country skier who competed in the 1920s .
Rama Mehta ( 1923 - -1978 ) was an Indian sociologist and writer who is remembered above all for her novel Inside the Haveli ( 1977 ) .
Barbro Östlihn ( b. 1930 - d. 1995 ) was a Swedish artist .
Richard Benese ( died 1546 ) , was a canon of the Augustinian priory of Merton .
Alvin Levin ( 1914 - -1981 ) was an American Jewish writer from Paterson , New Jersey who grew up in the Bronx .

Christmas Evans ( 25 December 1766 -- 19 July 1838 ) was a Welsh Nonconformist minister , regarded as one of the greatest preachers in the history of Wales .

Nicholas St. John ( by 1526 - 8 November 1589 ) , was an English politician .
Chimalpilli I was a tlatoani ( ruler ) of the Aztec altepetl ( city - state ) of Ecatepec from 1428 until his death in 1465 .

Amos Graham ( March 14 , 1816 - 1865 ) was the first Nodaway County , Missouri clerk .
Victor Reinganum ( 1907 - -1995 ) was an artist and illustrator , probably best known for his illustrations on book dustjackets , including the first editions of Muriel Spark 's The Ballad of Peckham Rye ( 1960 ) and The Prime of Miss Jean Brodie ( 1961 ) .
Filippo Perlo ( 8 February 1873 - 4 November 1948 ) was an Italian Catholic prelate , who was the Vicar Apostolic Emeritus of Kenya ( Archdiocese of Nyeri , Kenya ) and Bishop Titular of Maronea .

George Thomas Stokes ( 1843 - -1898 ) was an Irish ecclesiastical historian .

Thomas Mackay ( 1849 -- 1912 ) was a British wine merchant and classical liberal .
Robert John Braidwood ( 29 July 1907 -- 15 January 2003 ) was an American archaeologist and anthropologist , one of the founders of scientific archaeology , and a leader in the field of Near Eastern Prehistory .
Bervin Woods ( 9 January 1910 -- 13 January 2002 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for Collingwood in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) during the late 1930s .

José Romeo ( 1701 - -1772 ) was a Spanish painter of the Baroque period .

Margaret Godolphin ( 2 August 1652 -- 9 September 1678 ) was a British courtier .

Krystyna Ceynowa , also spelled as Cejnowa ( died 1836 ) , was an ethnic Polish victim of murder by lynching and an alleged witch in Germany .
William Emerton Heitland ( 21 December 1847 -- 23 June 1935 ) was an English Cambridge University based classicist .

Helen Foster Snow ( 1907 - -1997 ) was an American journalist who reported from China in the 1930s under the name `` Nym Wales '' on the developing revolution in China and the Korean independence movement .
Hans Kreissig ( May 23 , 1857 -- December 28 , 1929 ) was a German - born American pianist , music teacher , and conductor .

Ramesh Mantri ( Devanagari : रमेश मंत्री ) ( 1927 - -1997 ) was a Marathi writer primarily of humor from Maharashtra , India .
Peter Bruner ( 1845 - -1938 ) , was born a slave in Kentucky .
John Thomas Haines ( c.1799 - -1843 ) was a British actor and dramatist .

Carmine Gallone ( 18 September 1886 , Taggia -- 4 April 1973 ) was an early acclaimed Italian film director , screenwriter , and film producer .

Khalil al - Zahawi ( Arabic : خليل الزهاوي‎ ; 1946 - 25 May 2007 ) was one of Iraq 's most prominent calligraphers .

Anthony Kohlmann , S.J. ( 13 July 1771 -- 11 April 1836 ) , was an Alsatian Jesuit priest .
Donald Lines Jacobus , FASG ( 1887 - 1970 ) of New Haven , Connecticut , was widely regarded among genealogists as the dean of American genealogy during his lifetime .
Muhammad Sa'id al-'Ashmawi ( Arabic : محمد سعيد العشماوى‎ , IPA : ( mæˈħæmmæd sæˈʕiːd el.ʕæʃˈmæːwi ) ; 1932 -- 7 November 2013 ) was an Egyptian Supreme Court justice and former head of the Court of State Security .

Mikołaj Błociszewski ( Nicholas de Błociszewo ) of Ostoja coat of arms ( d. 1419 ) - the court knight and deputy of King Jogaila ( Władysław Jagiełło ) to negotiate with the Teutonic Knights .

John Douglas , 2nd Earl of Morton died 9 September 1513 at the Battle of Flodden .
Mihailo Dožić ( Serbian Cyrillic : Михаило Дoжић ; 1848 - -1914 ) was a Serbian Orthodox hierodeacon and archimandrite , who established an insurgent battalion in Potarje ( in Montenegro ) to fight against Ottoman rule in the region .

John Winstanley ( 1678 ? -- 1750 ) was an English Enlightenment figure and poet , probably born in Ireland .

John Warrington Rogers ( 1822 -- 10 February 1906 ) , M.A. , Q.C. , was a lawyer , member of parliament for the colony of Tasmania and judge of the County Court of Victoria .
Wilfred Lievesley ( born 6 October 1902 - 21 February 1979 ) was an English footballer .
Gnaeus Cornelius Lentulus Gaetulicus ( died 39 ) was a Roman general and politician .
John Edward Sowerby ( 17 January 1825 -- 28 January 1870 ) was a British botanical illustrator and publisher born in Lambeth , London on 17 January 1825 .
John Saris ( c. 1580 -- 1643 ) was the captain of the first English voyage to Japan , in 1613 , on board the Clove .
Alfred Gregory FBIPP , FRPS ( Hon ) ( 12 February 1913 -- 9 February 2010 ) was a British mountaineer , explorer and professional photographer .

Saadi Al Munla ( 1890 - 1975 ) was a Lebanese politician and one of the former Lebanese prime ministers .
Domenico Mona ( also called Moni , Monna , or Monio ) ( 1550 - -1602 ) was an Italian painter of the late - Renaissance period , born in Ferrara .
Maha Vidhwan Rao Sahib Mu Raghava Iyengar ( Tamil : மு ராகவ ஐயங்கார் ) ( 1878 - -1960 ) was a well known Tamil scholar and researcher of Tamil literature .
Alex McCracken ( died 25 August 1915 ) was the first president of the Victorian Football League .
Eric Louis Boetzel ( May 18 , 1884 - January 1958 ) was the deputy Attorney General of New York State , and a former Manhattan Assistant District Attorney .
Abbas Tyabji ( 1 February 1854 -- 9 June 1936 ) was an Indian freedom fighter from Gujarat , who once served as the Chief Justice of the ( Baroda ) Gujarat High Court .
Walter Reinhardt Sombre ( born as Walter Reinhardt or Reinert ; c. 1725 -- 1778 ) was an adventurer and mercenary in India from the 1760s .
Hubert Maurer ( 10 June 1738 -- 10 December 1818 ) was an Austrian painter , draughtsman , and teacher .
George Bean ( 7 March 1864 in Sutton - in - Ashfield , Nottinghamshire , England -- 16 March 1923 in Mansfield , Nottinghamshire , England ) was a cricketer who played first - class cricket for Sussex County Cricket Club between 1886 and 1898 .
Pierre - Nicolas Tourgueneff ( 4 April 1853 -- 21 March 1912 ) was a French animalier sculptor and painter of the late 19th century and early 20th century .
Honourable Wilfred Gilbert Thesiger , DSO ( 25 March 1871- 31 January 1920 ) was a British officer and diplomat , who was British Minister in Ethiopia from 1909 to 1919 .
Ivan Bezpaly ( Ukrainian Iван Безпалий , Russian Иван Беспалый died 1718 ) was a Cossack colonel of the Uman Regiment , and the leader of the pro - Russian faction in the Eastern Ukraine .
William Penhallow Henderson ( 1877 - 1943 ) was an American painter , architect , and furniture designer .
David Stewart Dawson ( 1849 -- 6 August 1932 ) , frequently referred to as Stewart Dawson , was an Australian manufacturing jeweller and property tycoon born in Aberdeenshire , Scotland .
Antonio Bertali ( probably March 1605 -- 17 April 1669 ) was an Italian composer and violinist of the Baroque era .
Felipe de León ( died 1728 ) was a Spanish painter of the Baroque period active in Seville .
Jan Miense Molenaer ( 1610 -- buried 19 September 1668 ) , was a Dutch Golden Age genre painter whose style was a precursor to Jan Steen 's work during Dutch Golden Age painting .
John Bradbury , 2nd Baron Bradbury , of Winsford in the County of Chester ( 7 January 1914 -- 31 March 1994 ) was a British peer and member of the House of Lords , the second holder of the title Baron Bradbury .
Albin Ström ( 1892 , Ånimskog -- 1962 ) was a Swedish socialist politician from Gothenburg .
William Chevir ( died 1446 ) was an Irish politician and judge , whose career was marked by accusations of oppression and corruption .
Fogartach mac Néill ( died 724 ) , sometimes called Fogartach ua Cernaich , was an Irish king who is reckoned a High King of Ireland .
Stephen Alfred Forbes ( 29 May 1844 -- 13 March 1930 ) was the first Chief of the Illinois Natural History Survey , a founder of aquatic ecosystem science and a dominant figure in the rise of American ecology .
Neville Usborne ( 27 February 1888 -- 21 February 1916 ) was a British naval officer who played a prominent part in British military lighter - than - air aviation before the First World War .
Philip Frowde ( died 1738 ) was an English poet and dramatist .
Akaki Khoshtaria ( Georgian : აკაკი ხოშტარია , Russian : Акакий Мефодьевич Хоштария , Akakiy Mefodievich Khoshtariya ) ( 1873 -- 1932 ) was a Georgian entrepreneur , socialite , and philanthropist .
Percy Verner Noble ( 18 December 1902 -- 19 June 1996 ) was a Canadian politician who served as a Progressive Conservative Member of Parliament .
Coramae Richey Mann ( 1931 - -2004 ) was a professor emeritus of criminal justice at the University of Illinois at Chicago .
John Guyse ( 1680 - 1761 ) was an English independent minister .
Mario Pretto ( 7 October 1915 -- 2 April 1984 ) was an Italian footballer turned coach who managed Bolivia in the 1950 FIFA World Cup .
Ioan Sterca - Șuluțiu ( 1796 - -1858 ) was an ethnic Romanian bureaucrat in the administration of Imperial Austrian Transylvania , owner of gold mines at Abrud , and the brother of Greek - Catholic Metropolitan Alexandru Sterca - Șuluțiu .
Yehiel Duvdevani ( Hebrew : יחיאל דובדבני‎ , born 1896 , died 30 April 1988 ) was a Zionist activist and politician .
Sir Owen Morgan Edwards ( 26 December 1858 -- 15 May 1920 ) was a Welsh historian , educationalist and writer .
Christopher David Allen ( 13 January 1938 -- 13 March 2015 ) , better known as Daevid Allen , sometimes credited as Divided Alien , was an Australian poet , guitarist , singer , composer and performance artist .
Jules Moriceau ( 2 January 1887 Nantes -- 20 June 1977 Garches ) was a French racecar driver .
Robert F. Howard ( 1883 - 1963 ) was an educator , pecan farmer , and cattle - rancher who founded the FarmHouse college fraternity .
Vespasiano Colonna ( c. 1485 - 13 March 1528 ) was an Italian nobleman and condottiero , a member of the Colonna family .
Anders Platou Wyller ( 24 April 1903 - 2 October 1940 ) was a Norwegian philologist and humanist .
Vincenzo Barboni ( 1802 - -1859 ) was an Italian painter , mainly depicting sacred subjects in a Neoclassical style .
Virginie Amélie Avegno Gautreau ( née Avegno , 29 January 1859 -- 25 July 1915 ) was born in New Orleans but grew up from the age of eight in France , where she became a Parisian socialite known for her beauty .
Ivan Lenković ( died 22 June 1569 ) was a Habsburg Croatian army general and the leader of the Uskoks .
Charles Evelyn Pierrepont , Viscount Newark MP ( 2 September 1805 - 23 August 1850 ) was a Member of Parliament for East Retford , and poet .
Richard E. Turner ( 1920 - -1986 ) was a fighter pilot with the 9th Air Force in the European Theater during World War II and early in the Korean War .
Avan Yuzbashi ( 1670 - -1735 ) was an 18th - century commander of Armenian armies in Nagorno Karabakh .
Sophie Watillon ( 7 December 1965 -- 31 August 2005 ) was a Belgian viol player who specialized in Baroque music .
Nikita Romanovich ( Russian : Никита Романович ; born ca . 1522 , died 23 April 1586 ) , also known as Nikita Romanovich Zakharyin - Yuriev , was a Muscovite boyar in 1563 .
William Vestey , 1st Baron Vestey , Bt ( 21 January 1859 -- 10 December 1940 ) was an English shipping magnate .
P. N. Mari Bhat ( 1951 - -2007 ) , distinguished Indian demographer , was a student of Samuel H. Preston at the University of Pennsylvania from where he received his Ph.D. in 1987 .
Jean - François Salvard ( or Salvart ) ( c. 1530 -- 1585 ) was a French - Swiss Reformed theologian , known as the editor of the Harmonia confessionum of 1581 .
Pierre Louis de Saffon ( 1724 , France - August 1784 , Demerara ) was a French duelist that escaped to exile in the Dutch colony of Demerara , now in Guyana , only to later become a wealthy land owner .
Kgosi Seepapitso IV ( died 24 March 2010 ) was a chief of the Ngwaketse tribe of Botswana .
Giacomo Appiotti ( 1873 -- 1948 ) was Lieutenant General of the Italian Army during the Second Italo - Abyssinian War .
Henry Standing Bear ( c.1874 - 1953 ) ( `` Mato Naji '' ) was an Oglala Lakota Chief .
Trần Quảng Vận , penname Trần Lâm ( 1922 - 2011 ) was a Vietnamese journalist .
Simon Burton , M.D. , F.R.C.P. ( c.1690 - -1744 ) , was an English physician .
Edward Samuel Ritchie ( 1814 - -1895 ) , an American inventor and physicist , is considered to be the most innovative instrument maker in nineteenth - century America , making important contributions to both science and navigation .
Gideon Joubert ( 4 September 1923 -- 27 October 2010 ) was a South African writer and journalist ( at Die Burger ) who was known for his Intelligent Design - opinions , especially present in his book , Die Groot Gedagte , which was his biggest success .
Sir Joshua Vanneck , 1st Baronet ( 1702 - died 6 March 1777 ) was a British - Dutch merchant .
The Hon . Octavius Duncombe ( 8 April 1817 -- 3 December 1879 ) was a British Conservative politician .
Lauritz Peter Holmblad ( 8 July 1815 -- 16 November 1890 ) , usually referred to as L. P. Holmblad , was a Danish industrialist and philanthropist .
Muhammad Asad ( pronounced ( ˈmoʊ̯hämæd ˈæsæd ) , Urdu : محمد أسد‎ , born Leopold Weiss ; 2 July 1900 -- 20 February 1992 ) was a Jewish - born Austro - Hungarian journalist , traveler , writer , linguist , thinker , political theorist , diplomat and Islamic scholar .
Edgar Vincent , 1st Viscount D'Abernon GCB GCMG PC FRS ( 19 August 1857 -- 1 November 1941 ) was a British politician , diplomat , art collector and author .
Louis Huth ( 22 March 1821 -- 12 February 1905 ) , was a British company director , merchant banker , art collector , art dealer and patron of Aesthetic movement artists .
Colonel John Tayloe II ( 28 May 1721 -- 18 April 1779 ) was among the richest plantation owners in colonial Virginia .
Stephen du Perche ( 1137/8 - -1169 ) was the chancellor of the Kingdom of Sicily ( 1166 - -68 ) and Archbishop of Palermo ( 1167 - -68 ) during the early regency of his cousin , Queen Margaret of Navarre ( 1166 - -71 ) .
Philip Wenman , 6th Viscount Wenman ( 23 November 1719 -- 16 August 1760 ) , was a British landowner and politician .
Ng Hon - tsz , JP ( 1877 -- 11 April 1932 ) was a Hong Kong businessman and member of the Legislative Council of Hong Kong .
Daniel Mornin ( 1956 - 2014 ) was an award winning playwright , screenwriter and novelist writing about contemporary Ulster .
Adam Ottley ( 1655 - -1723 ) was an English churchman , Bishop of St David 's from 1713 .
Arne Åkermark ( 1902 - -1962 ) was a Swedish art director who worked on around a hundred and eighty films during a thirty year career .
Friedrich Kurt Fiedler ( 8 March 1894 -- 11 November 1950 ) was a German graphic designer and a representative of the Social Democratic Party .
Osborne Gordon ( 1813 - 1883 ) was an influential Oxford college tutor and Church of England Clergyman .
John Glendwr Owen CB ( 1914 - 1977 ) was a senior British civil servant .
Sydney Edward Wright ( 3 June 1914 -- 7 October 1966 ) was an Australian academic , pacifist , pharmacist , pharmacy college head and technical / TAFE college teacher .
George Gordon Hoskins FRIBA ( 28 October 1837 -- 11 December 1911 ) , was an English architect responsible for the design of several public buildings in the North East of England .
Ronald Douglas Maxwell ( 1919 -- 23 December 1941 ) was a British soldier during World War II , serving in the Hong Kong Volunteer Defence Corps .
Richard Cragun ( 5 October 1944 -- 6 August 2012 ) was an American ballet dancer who rose to international fame with the Stuttgart Ballet in Germany .
Vice - Admiral Sir Henry Deacon Barry , KCVO ( 27 November 1849 - 14 November 1908 ) was a British Royal Navy officer who was Admiral superintendent at Portsmouth dockyard .
Hamiora Pere ( died 16 November 1869 ) was the only New Zealander ever to be executed for treason .
John Wodehouse , 2nd Baron Wodehouse ( 11 January 1771 -- 31 May 1846 ) , styled The Honourable John Wodehouse from 1797 to 1834 , was a British peer and Member of Parliament .
Cui Zhiwen ( 崔知溫 ) ( 627 -- April 27 , 683 ) , courtesy name Liren ( 禮仁 ) , was an official of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , serving as a chancellor during the reign of Emperor Gaozong .
Robert Kirkland Kernighan ( 25 April 1854 -- 3 November 1926 ) was a Canadian poet , journalist , and farmer .
Egnatius Lucillianus ( c. 210 -- aft . 244 ) was a Governor or Legatus of Britannia Inferior at Eboracum , a province of Britannia some time between 238 and 244 .
Carlos Cuarteron ( 1816 - -1880 ) , was a Spanish mariner who later became a priest and established the first Roman Catholic missions in northern Borneo .
Udo Jürgens ( born Udo Jürgen Bockelmann ; 30 September 1934 -- 21 December 2014 ) was an Austrian - Swiss composer and singer of popular music whose career spanned over fifty years .
Claud Carr ( 29 November 1905 -- 4 March 1948 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Kim Hyowon(김효원 , 金孝元 , 1532 -- 1 April 1590 ) was a Korean Joseon Dynastys politician and Writer , and a Neo Confucian scholar .
Sir John Lumsden KBE ( 14 November 1869 -- 3 September 1944 ) was an Irish physician and the founder of the St. John Ambulance Brigade of Ireland .
The Honourable Henry Grey Bennet ( 2 December 1777 -- 29 May 1836 ) was a British politician .
Arthur Sleith ( 22 December 1917 -- 17 December 2008 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Dr. Morton Shulman , OC ( 25 April 1925 -- 18 August 2000 ) was a Canadian politician , businessman , broadcaster , columnist , coroner , and physician .
Raja Sri Raghunatha Raya Tondaiman ( 1641 - 1730 ) was the ruler of the Pudukkottai kingdom from 1686 to 1730 .
Louis II , Cardinal of Guise ( 6 July 1555 , Dampierre -- 24 December 1588 , Château de Blois ) , was the third son of Francis , Duke of Guise , and Anna d'Este .
Frederick Augustus Voigt ( 1892 - -1957 ) , British journalist and author of German descent , most famous for his work with the Manchester Guardian and his opposition to dictatorship and totalitarianism on the European Continent .
Nevesinli Salih Pasha ( Bosnian : Salih - paša Nevesinjac ; Cyrillic : Салих-паша Невесињац , died 16 September 1647 ) was an Ottoman civil servant and grand vizier .
Sid Kuller ( 27 October 1910 New York , New York -- 16 September 1993 in Sherman Oaks , California ) was an American comedy writer , producer and lyricist / composer , who concentrated on special musical material , gags and sketches for leading comics .
Michael Birkett , 2nd Baron Birkett ( 22 October 1929 -- 3 April 2015 ) , was a British film producer / director , author and hereditary peer .
Charles Allen Duval , often spelled duVal or Du Val , ( 19 March 1810 -- 14 June 1872 ) , was a well - known Victorian portrait painter , photographer , literary critic , illustrator and writer .
Jacob Abbot Cummings ( 1773 - -1820 ) was a bookseller , publisher , schoolteacher and author in Boston , Massachusetts , in the early 19th - century .
Tuala Ainiu Iusitino ( 1936 -- 31 August 2010 ) was a Samoan politician and former Cabinet Minister .
Harry G. John , Jr. ( 1919 - -1992 ) was an American philanthropist , founder of the De Rance Foundation and heir to the Miller Brewing Company fortune through his grandfather , founder Frederick Miller .
William Wayne Paul ( 1939 - -1989 ) was an American martial artist , educator , psychologist and social / political activist .
William Blenkiron ( 1807?--1871 ) was an English breeder of racehorses .
Count Johan Gabriel Oxenstierna ( 19 July 1750 -- 29 July 1818 ) is considered one of the foremost Swedish poets of the Gustavian period .
John Fitzedmund Fitzgerald ( died 1589 ) was the hereditary Seneschal of Imokilly , an Irish nobleman of the Welsh - Norman FitzGerald dynasty in the province of Munster , who rebelled against the crown during the reign of Queen Elizabeth of England .
Tiny Winters ( Frederick Gittens , 24 January 1909 , London--7 February 1996 ) was an English jazz bassist and vocalist who worked in the bands of Roy Fox , Bert Ambrose , Lew Stone and Ray Noble .
May Wirth ( 6 June 1894 -- 18 October 1978 ) was an Australian circus and vaudeville performer famous for her ability to do somersaults forwards and backwards on a running horse .
Sir David de la Hay ( c. 1318 - -1346 ) was Lord High Constable of Scotland .
Ernesto Ambrosini ( 29 September 1894 -- 4 November 1951 ) was an Italian athlete who competed mainly in the 3000 metres steeplechase .
Balthasar Siberer ( 1679 - -1757 ) was an Austrian - born German gymnasium teacher , known for having been an early organ instructor of both Johann Ernst Eberlin and Leopold Mozart .
Reidar Haaland ( 21 February 1919 -- 17 August 1945 ) was a police officer and voluntary frontline soldier for the German forces .
Tarun Chandra Pamegam was born in the year 1928 and he died in the year 1986 .
John Lack O'Sullivan ( 1976 - -19 November 2002 ) was a Gaelic footballer and Australian rules footballer .
Horst Höltring ( 30 June 1913 -- 24 August 1943 ) was a German U - boat commander in World War II .
Andrew J. Kuehn ( September 24 , 1937 -- January 29 , 2004 ) is notable for revolutionizing the American film trailer in the early 1960s and for producing and directing featurette films for television like Lights , Camera , Annie !
Lorna Bingham ( 1912 -- July 1970 ) was an Australian actress writer best known for her work on radio and her children 's books .
Claus Pavels ( 8 January 1769 - -16 February 1822 ) was a Norwegian priest and diarist .
Thomas Henry Poole ( 1860 -- 31 July 1919 ) was British - born architect who designed numerous churches and schools in New York City .
Patrick Villiers Farrow ( 1942 - -2009 ) was an American sculptor and lifelong peace and environmental activist .
Boļeslavs Maikovskis ( 21 January 1904 -- 19 April 1996 ) was a Latvian and alleged Nazi collaborator who served as chief of police for the second precinct of Rēzekne while the Germans occupied Latvia in World War II . After the war Maikovskis went to Austria before reaching the United States in 1951 .
Strickland Kneass ( 29 July 1821 Philadelphia - 14 January 1884 Philadelphia ) was a United States civil engineer .
Louis Plaidy ( 28 November 1810 in Hubertusburg , Saxony -- 3 March 1874 in Grimma , Saxony ) was a celebrated German piano pedagogue and compiler of books of technical music studies .
Frits von der Lippe ( 1 June 1901 -- 5 September 1988 ) was a Norwegian journalist and theatre director .
Daniel Zwicker ( 22 January 1612 -- 10 November 1678 ) was a German physician from Danzig , and a Socinian theologian and controversialist of the Polish Brethren .
Barnett Cohen ( 1891 - -1952 ) was a Russian - born American bacteriologist who performed the first ultra - microscopic surgeries , including on amoeba .
Finan of Lindisfarne ( died 17 February 661 ) , also known as Saint Finan , was an Irish monk , trained at Iona in Scotland , who became the second Bishop of Lindisfarne from 651 until 661 .
James W. McLaughlin ( 1834 - -1923 ) was a Cincinnati , Ohio architect .
Albert Bird ( 17 August 1867 -- 16 June 1927 ) was an English cricketer : a right - arm off - break bowler and lower - order right - handed batsman who played for Worcestershire for the first ten years of their existence as a first - class county .
Henry Clegg ( 8 December 1850 -- 30 December 1920 ) was an English first - class cricketer , who played six matches for Yorkshire County Cricket Club in 1881 .
Gene Gutchë ( born Romeo Maximilian Eugene Ludwig Gutschë ; 3 July 1907 , Berlin -- 15 November 2000 , White Bear Lake , Minnesota ) was a German composer active primarily in America .
Mary Howard de Liagre , née Rogers ( 18 May 1913 -- 6 June 2009 ) was an American actress usually credited as Mary Howard .
Oskar Sala ( 18 July 1910 -- 26 February 2002 ) was a 20th - century German physicist , composer and a pioneer of electronic music born in Greiz .
Andrée Marlière ( born Andrée Isabelle Germaine Marlier , Antwerp 22 February 1934 -- Wilrijk , St - Augustinus hospital 10 January 2008 ) is a Belgian ballet dancer and painter .
William Dance ( 20 December 1755 -- 5 June 1840 ) was an English pianist and violinist .
Susan Williams - Ellis ( 6 June 1918 -- 26 November 2007 ) was an English pottery designer , who was best known for co - founding Portmeirion Pottery .
Lucy Wright ( February 5 , 1760 -- 1821 ) was the leader of the United Society of Believers in Christ 's Second Appearing , also known as the Shakers , from 1796 until 1821 .
Ernest Worrall ( 1898 - -1972 ) was an English artist and teacher .
Benjamin Flight ( 1767?--1847 ) , was an organ - builder .
Juan de Ugalde later also ( wrongly ) known by American settlers as Juan de Uvalde ( December 9 , 1729 -- 1816 ) was born in Cádiz , Spain .
William II , Lord of Béthune , nicknamed William the Red ( French : Guillaume le Roux de Bethune ; d. April 1214 ) was French nobleman .
Alex Chola ( 5 June 1956 -- 27 April 1993 ) was a Zambian footballer and coach .
António José da Silva Coutinho ( 8 May 1705 -- 18 October 1739 ) was a Brazilian dramatist , known as `` the Jew '' ( O Judeu ) .
Charles Tennyson d'Eyncourt ( 20 July 1784 -- 21 July 1861 ) , born Charles Tennyson , was a British politician , landowner and Member of Parliament ( MP ) for Stamford from 1831 to 1832 and for Lambeth from 1832 to 1852 .
Benjamin Wrench ( 1778 - -1843 ) , was an actor , born in 1778 in London , where his father occupied `` a lucrative appointment in the Exchequer . ''
Bentley Collingwood Hilliam , usually credited as B C Hilliam ( 1890 - -1968 ) , was a singer , song - writer and musician , and the first - named member of the comedy duo Mr. Flotsam and Mr. Jetsam ( Mr. Jetsam was Malcolm McEachern ) .
Sir James Leyburn ( c1490 - 20 August 1548 ) was MP for Westmorland in 1542 and 1545 .
Richard Eastcott ( baptised 1744 - -1828 ) was an English clergyman and writer on music .
Ranald George Macdonald ( 29 August 1788 -- 11 March 1873 ) was a Scottish clan chief and Member of Parliament .
Giovanni Picchi ( 1571 or 1572 -- 17 May 1643 ) was an Italian composer , organist , lutenist , and harpsichordist of the early Baroque era .
Francesco Vaccaro or Vicaro ( 24 September 1636 -- 13 December 1675 ) was an Italian painter and engraver of the Baroque period , who trained in his native Bologna under Francesco Albani .
Sir Patrick Lindesay , KCB , KCH ( 24 February 1778 -- 14 March 1839 ) was a military officer during the Napoleonic Wars and Peninsular War but is most noted as having served as Acting Governor of New South Wales , Australia in 1831 .
Liu Yiming ( 1734 - -1821 ) was one of the main representatives of Taoist Internal Alchemy , or Neidan .
Patricio Samper Gnecco ( 1 November 1930 -- 5 January 2006 ) was a Colombia architect , urbanist and politician .
Lionel Tollemache , 3rd Earl of Dysart ( 30 January 1649 -- 23 February 1727 n.s . )
Gruffydd Vychan ap Iowerth Goch ( 1150 - 1221 ) was a medieval British knight and Marcher lord .
Peter Graham Scott ( 27 October 1923 -- 5 August 2007 ) was an English film producer , film director , film editor and screenwriter .
Right Reverend Jacob Bastiampillai Deogupillai ( 9 April 1917 -- 25 April 2003 ) was a Ceylon Tamil priest and Roman Catholic Bishop of Jaffna .
Lithang Tulku Tenzin Delek Rinpoche or Tenzing Deleg ( Tibetan : བསྟན་འཛིན་བདེ་ལེགས་ , Wylie : Bstan ' dzin bde legs ) ( 1950 -- 12 July 2015 ) was a Tibetan Buddhist leader from Garze , Sichuan .
Rajkumari Singh ( October 13 , 1923 -- 1979 ) was an Indo - Caribbean , Guyanese writer , political activist , educator , and cultural leader .
Ernest Harry Vestine ( May 9 , 1906 -- July 18 , 1968 ) was an American geophysicist and meteorologist .
Philip Zec ( 25 December 1909 -- 14 July 1983 ) was a British political cartoonist and editor .
Lucia Anguissola ( 1536 or 1538 -- c. 1565 , before 1568 ) was an Italian mannerist painter of the late Renaissance .
Antonio Amurri ( 28 June 1925 -- 18 December 1992 ) was an Italian author , radio and television writer and lyricist .
Koh Eng Tong ( 1921 - 2006 ) was a Malaysian athlete , professional photographer and founder of Eng Tong System Sdn .
The Washington Post stated in 1909 shortly after his death that `` John Ericsson has for years monopolized all of the credit for inventing and building the Monitor , but as a matter of fact he was joint inventor with Theodore Timby . ''
Thomas St George ( 1615 - -1703 ) was an English officer of arms who rose to the rank of Garter Principal King of Arms ( 1686 - -1703 ) .
Maria Leopoldine of Austria - Tyrol ( 6 April 1632 -- 7 August 1649 ) was the second spouse of her first cousin , Holy Roman Emperor Ferdinand III . As such , she was empress of the Holy Roman Empire .
John Sheffield , 2nd Baron Sheffield , of Butterwick ( c. 1538 -- 10 December 1568 ) was the first son of Edmund Sheffield , 1st Baron Sheffield , and Lady Anne de Vere .

Esau de ' Buondelmonti ( Greek : Ησαύ Μπουοντελμόντ ) was the ruler of Ioannina and its surrounding area ( central Epirus ) from 1385 to his death in 1411 , with the Byzantine title of Despot .
Alex Barningham ( 22 August 1889 -- 4 January 1956 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .

Joseph Willard ( 29 December 1738 -- 25 September 1804 ) was an American Congregational clergyman and academic .

Bardhyl Çaushi ( 1936 - -1999 ) was a Kosovo Albanian human rights lawyer and activist .
