Philip Guthrie Hoffman ( 6 August 1915 -- 29 October 2008 ) was the fifth president of the University of Houston , and the first chancellor of the University of Houston System .
Richard Pearsall ( 29 August 1698 -- 10 November 1762 ) was an English Congregationalist minister and friend of Philip Doddridge .
Thomas Sewell Robins ( 1810 -- 1880 ) was a British painter of maritime themes .
William Arthur Evelyn ( 4 October 1860 -- 6 January 1935 ) was a distinguished historian of York , and the creator of The Evelyn Collection .
Charles Hamilton , 8th Earl of Haddington DL ( 5 July 1753 -- 17 March 1828 ) was a Scottish nobleman .
William Henry James Weale ( 8 March 1832 -- 1917 ) was a British art historian who lived and worked most of his life in Bruges and was one of the first to research the Early Netherlandish painting ( then better known as `` Flemish Primitives '' ) extensively .
Foster Moverley McRae , commonly known as Peter McRae ( 12 February 1916 -- 25 February 1944 ) was an English cricketer who played 25 first - class matches for Somerset County Cricket Club between 1936 and 1939 .
Mitchell Goodman ( 1923 - -1997 ) was an American writer , teacher , and activist .
George Salter ( 5 October 1897 -- 31 October 1967 ) , born Georg Salter , was an originally German , and from 1940 onwards US - American book cover designer .
Joseph Jay Deiss ( 1912 - -1999 ) , an American author , businessman , historian and archaeologist was born in Twin Falls , Idaho and graduated from the University of Texas , where he also received his Masters .
Sir Archibald Alison , 1st Baronet , GCB , FRSE ( 29 December 1792 -- 23 May 1867 ) was a Scottish advocate and historian .
Lwandile Zwelenkosi Matanzima ( 1970/71 -- 22 May 2010 ) was a South African clan leader and ruler as king of Western Thembuland .
Anne Macnaghten , CBE ( 9 August 1908 -- 31 December 2000 ) was a British classical violinist and pedagogue .
William of Wykeham ( 1320 or 1324 -- 27 September 1404 ) was Bishop of Winchester and Chancellor of England .
Richard Louis Dugdale ( 1841 -- 23 July 1883 ) was an American merchant and sociologist , best known for his 1877 family study , The Jukes :
Thomas Exley ( 9 December 1774 -- 17 February 1855 ) was an English schoolmaster and schoolkeeper , who taught and occasionally published on mathematics , but was better known for advancing controversial scientific theories and for theological discussions , with special reference to Methodism .
Kevin John Hewitt 1957 - 2001 ( died aged 44 ) was involved with many circuses throughout his life , most notably the world famous Blackpool Tower Circus , where he was the ringmaster throughout 1996 and 1997 , before moving to Ireland .
Piotr Fergusson Tepper ( 1713 - 1794 ) was a Polish banker of German burgher origin , merchant and industrial entrepreneur .
Horace Wass ( 26 August 1903 -- 14 January 1969 ) was an English sportsman , who made over 400 Football League appearances playing football for Chesterfield from 1920 to 1937 and for Southport in 1937 .
Francis Martin Sewell Stokes ( 16 November 1902 , London -- 2 November 1979 , London ) was an English novelist , biographer , playwright , screenwriter , broadcaster and prison visitor .
Arun Thapa ( born January 1952 -- 22 July 1999 ) was a famous Nepali singer and songwriter .
Scroop Egerton , 1st Duke of Bridgewater ( 11 August 1681 -- 11 January 1744 ) , known as Viscount Brackley from 1687 to 1701 and as the Earl of Bridgewater from 1701 to 1720 , was a British peer and courtier from the Egerton family .
Etuate Tavai ( died 1999 ) served as Attorney General of Fiji from 1996 to 1999 .
Fanny Parkes ( née Frances Susannah Archer ) ( 1794 - -1875 ) was a Welsh travel writer .
Sir John Pelham , 3rd Baronet ( 1623 - -1703 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons of England variously between 1644 and 1698 .
Philip Gale ( 1978 - -1998 ) was an American pioneering Internet software developer , computer prodigy , and sophomore student at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology ( MIT ) .
Jiří Nigrin ( Černý ) z Černého Mostu , since about 1590 titled z Nigropontu ( died 1606 ) was an important printer in Prague between 1572 and 1606 .
Ahmad Rahi ( 12 November 1923 -- 2 September 2002 ) was a Punjabi poet and writer from Pakistan .
Sir Mark Oldroyd ( 30 May 1843 -- 5 July 1927 ) was a British woollen manufacturer and Liberal Party politician from West Yorkshire .
Charlie Meadway ( 16 October 1879 -- 1 January 1962 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton and Collingwood in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Sir Richard Symons , 1st Baronet ( c. 1743 -- 4 July 1796 ) , was a British politician .
The Right Reverend Thomas Casady ( June 6 , 1881 -- 1958 ) was the third missionary bishop of Oklahoma and the first diocesan bishop of the Diocese of Oklahoma of the Episcopal Church , USA .
James William Edmund Doyle ( 22 October 1822 -- 3 December 1892 ) was an antiquary and illustrator .
Josiah Ogden Watson ( 24 September 1784 -- 12 June 1852 ) was an American planter , physician , and statesman from North Carolina .
Rejabhad , or Rejab bin Had , ( 23 August , - 14 November 2002 ) , was a Malaysian cartoonist .
Clayton Valli ( 1951 - -2003 ) was a prominent deaf linguist and American Sign Language ( ASL ) poet whose work helped further to legitimize ASL and introduce people to the richness of American Sign Language literature .
John Edward Jennings ( 1906 - -1973 ) was an American historical novelist , author of many best - selling novels of American history and seagoing adventure .
Saint Fergus ( also Fergustian ) ( died c. 730 AD ) was a bishop who worked in Scotland as a missionary .
Sir George Buchan - Hepburn , 1st Baronet ( 1739 - -1819 ) was a Scottish lawyer and judge .
Herbert Bolt ( 1893 - -1916 ) was a pioneer Australian rugby league player , a state representative centre and soldier who served and fell in World War I. He is one of 75 Australian soldiers whose remains were identified by name in 2010 by the Commonwealth War Graves Commission as part of the Fromelles Military Cemetery project .
Leonard Max Gumpel ( 23 April 1890 -- 3 August 1965 ) was a Swedish building contractor and Olympic swimmer and water polo player .
José Antonio Momeñe Campo ( 15 August 1940 -- 23 December 2010 ) was a Spanish professional road bicycle racer , who finished 4th place in the general classification of the 1966 Tour de France .
W. A. Silva ( 16 January 1890 -- 3 May 1957 ) was a best - selling author of Sinhala literature .
Rybka is a computer chess engine designed by International Master Vasik Rajlich .
Darklight Conflict is a space combat simulator video game developed by Rage Software and published by Electronic Arts in 1997 for PCs running MS - DOS or versions of Microsoft Windows before Windows 2000 , and the Sega Saturn and Sony PlayStation game consoles .
Jeremy McGrath Supercross World is a Racing video game released in 2001 by Acclaim Entertainment .
JumpStart 1st Grade ( known as Jump Ahead Year 1 in the United Kingdom ) is a personal computer game created by Knowledge Adventure in 1994 intended to teach a 1st grade curriculum .
8-Bit Sampled Voice ( 8SVX ) is an audio file format standard developed by Electronic Arts for the Commodore - Amiga computer series .
Windows Phone ( WP ) is a family of mobile operating systems developed by Microsoft for smartphones as the replacement successor to Windows Mobile and Zune .
Tizen is a project within the Linux Foundation and is governed by a Technical Steering Group ( TSG ) composed of Samsung and Intel among others .
Developed by TikGames and published by Square Enix , Scarygirl was released on January 18 , 2012 with an ESRB rating of 10 + .
The first SHMEM library , libsma , was created by Cray in 1993 .
X - Note is an otome game based on Adobe Flash , therefore it can be played on multiple platforms such as Windows , Linux and Mac OS . The game was developed and published by Zeiva Inc and was released on March 8 , 2011 .
Google AdSense is a program run by Google that allows publishers in the Google Network of content sites to serve automatic text , image , video , or interactive media advertisements , that are targeted to site content and audience .
Empire of Sports is an online multiple - sport MMORPG developed by the French company F4 , that advertises itself as the first ever of that style .
Supreme Commander 2 is a real - time strategy ( RTS ) video game developed by Gas Powered Games and published by Square Enix .
Toy Racer is a racing game for the Dreamcast made by No Cliché and published by Sega .
Dungeon Hero was to have been a hack - and - slash role - playing video game developed by Firefly Studios and published by Gamecock Media Group .
Unreal Championship is a first - person shooter video game co - developed by Epic Games and Digital Extremes .
Grand Theft Auto V is an open world , action - adventure video game developed by Rockstar North and published by Rockstar Games .
Mutant Storm Reloaded is a multi - directional shoot 'em up developed by PomPom Games .
Madden NFL Football ( sometimes mislabeled as Madden NFL 3D ) is a sports video game for the Nintendo 3DS which was developed by EA Sports .
Panzer Strike is a 1987 tactical level simulation of small unit actions game set in World War II . It was made for Apple II and Commodore 64 and was released by Strategic Simulations , Inc. The game included an editor as well as over 250 weapon types ; single scenarios can last up to 2 hours .
Action 52 is an unlicensed multicart video game compilation developed by Active Enterprises for the NES , and Farsight Technologies for the Sega Genesis .
Quake Live is a first - person shooter video game by i d Software .
Eliminate Pro ( also known as Eliminate ) was a first - person shooter developed for iOS by Ngmoco .
Down in the Dumps is a 1996 computer adventure game developed for MS - DOS and Microsoft Windows , by the French Haiku Studios and published by Philips Media .
Critter Round - Up ( Saku Saku Animal Panic in Japan ) is a puzzle video game developed by Epicenter Studios and Konami for the Wii .
Countdown to Doom is a text adventure computer game , more recently termed interactive fiction , written in 1982 by Peter Killworth .
Battles in Time was a PC video game and was the only product co - developed by Quantum Quality Productions and American Laser Games .
Chip 's Challenge is a top - down tile - based puzzle video game originally published in 1989 by Epyx as a launch title for the Atari Lynx .
Crystal Mines II is a puzzle video game designed by Ken Beckett ( who also served as lead programmer ) for Color Dreams and licensed to Atari , who published it as a cartridge for their Atari Lynx color handheld game console .

Szczecin Voivodeship ( 1 ) ( Polish : województwo szczecińskie ) was a unit of administrative division and local government in Poland in the years 1975 - -1998 , superseded by West Pomeranian Voivodeship .

The Friends of Herculaneum Society is an Oxford - based British charity founded in 2004 to promote research into the archaeological site of Herculaneum at Ercolano , near Naples , Italy .
The Austin Motor Company Limited was an English manufacturer of motor vehicles , founded in 1905 by Herbert Austin .
The Frink School opened in 1996 in Longton , moving to Tunstall in 1999 .
Created in April 1996 for the AB Sat package , Chasse et Pêche is a channel dedicated to hunting and fishing for sport , and those who enjoy them .
ITC Sangeet Research Academy ( ITC - SRA ) was established in 1978 with the objective of preserving and promoting Hindustani Classical Music .
MTV Greece was the Greek version of MTV , launched on September 1 , 2008 .
The Midnight Ramblers were founded in 1998 by Jon Huang , then a sophomore at the University of Rochester .
The Object Data Management Group ( ODMG ) was conceived in the summer of 1991 at a breakfast with object database vendors that was organized by Rick Cattell of Sun Microsystems .
The Taiwan Intellectual Property Office ( TIPO ) is the patent , trademark , and copyright office of Taiwan , established in 1999 .
The WNBA Finals has been played at the conclusion of every WNBA season in history , the first being held in 1997 .
WFMX went on the air March 17 , 1990 as a satellite fed oldies format under the call letters WHQO ( Standing for `` Headquarters for Oldies '' ) changing a few years later to a community based AC format as `` The Light at the end of the dial '' .
Trepan Records is a pioneering independent English record label and promotions company , founded in London in 2007 .
Velocity Girl was an American indie rock band formed in 1989 in College Park , Maryland , although it was generally known as a Washington , DC - area band .
KMFM Shepway and White Cliffs Country launched on 29 September 1997 as Neptune Radio , broadcasting on 96.4 and 106.8 FM after a month - long trial concluded earlier that same morning .
Buckinghamshire University Technical College ( or Buckinghamshire UTC ) is a university technical college ( UTC ) which opened in September 2013 in Aylesbury , Buckinghamshire , England .
The Tamil Nadu Uniformed Services Recruitment Board ( TNUSRB ) was constituted by the Government of Tamil Nadu in November 1991 vide G.O. Ms. No . 1806 , Home ( Ser . F ) Department , dated 29.11.1991 for the recruitment of personnel for the Uniformed Services like Police , Prison and Fire and Rescue Services .
Lincoln UTC is a University Technical College in Lincoln , England which opened in 2014 and specialises in science and engineering skills .
CLS Communication was created in 1997 as a spin - off from Swiss Bank Corporation ( now UBS ) and Zurich Financial Services .
After receiving an extension to its original permit , KSJE received its license to cover from the FCC on December 9 , 1992 .

WLBB Carrollton , Georgia , moved to 1330 kHz and the 1100 kHz signal moved to Hapeville and changed calls to WWWE on August 30 , 1996 .
4 Runner was an American country music vocal group founded in 1993 by lead singer Craig Morris , baritone Billy Crittenden , tenor Lee Hilliard , and bass Jim Chapman .
The University of Priština ( Serbian : Универзитет у Приштини/Univerzitet u Prištini ) is the name of the Serbian - language higher education institution that emerged after the disestablishment of the University of Pristina ( 1969 - -1999 ) as a result of the Kosovo War .
Invitrogen was founded in 1987 by Lyle Turner , Joe Fernandez , and William McConnell and was incorporated in 1989 .
Atlantic Television was founded in 1997 by former BBC producer Howard Gibbins .
Ruffhouse Records is a record label founded in 1989 by Chris Schwartz and Joe Nicolo as a joint venture with Columbia Records .
In 1922 , various non - aligned groups and individuals established the Organization of General Zionists as a non - ideological party within the Zionist Organization ( later the World Zionist Organization ) at a time when the Zionist movement was becoming polarized between Labour Zionists and Revisionist Zionism .
The Steamship Historical Society of America ( SSHSA ) is a non - profit organization that was founded in 1935 as a means of bringing together amateur and professional maritime historians in the waning years of steamboat services in the northeastern United States .
The death metal band Wayd was founded in 1994 when thrash metal band MARION and death metal band DYSENTERY fused together .
The Lingerie Basketball League ( LBL ) is a women 's basketball league , created in 2011 .
Zhone Technologies , Inc. is a provider of telecommunications networking equipment founded in 1999 .
Preventice , Inc. , formerly known as Boost Information Systems , Inc. , was founded in 2007 by Jonathan Otterstatter , Scott Burrichter , Greg Wobig , and Dan Spors .
Viereck was founded in 1748 in the course of the repopulation policy under King Frederick II , the Great , of Prussia .
The SI Leeds Literary Prize is a biennial award founded in 2012 by Soroptimist International of Leeds ( SI Leeds ) -- a branch of the worldwide women 's organization Soroptimist International -- for unpublished fiction written by Black and Asian women resident in the UK .
The McConnell Center is an endowed institution created in 1991 by U.S. Senator Mitch McConnell , and the University of Louisville .
Pan Am International Flight Academy ( PAIFA ) is the only remaining division of the once iconic Pan American World Airways , which declared bankruptcy in January 1991 and shut down in December 1991 .
Radio Bremen began transmitting a daily programme on AM radio on 23 December 1945 under the post - war occupation of Germany by the Allied powers .
Essendon Keilor College was founded in 1992 from the amalgamation of Queens Park Secondary College ( formerly Essendon Technical School ) , Essendon High School , Niddrie High School and Keilor Heights Secondary College .
The Société française de photographie ( French Photographic Society ) is an association , founded on 15 November 1854 , devoted to the history of photography .
The opening of Eagles Meadow was Thursday 30 October 2008 at 10 am .
Blurtonia was a Canadian indie rock group , formed in May 1999 to play live shows in support of the well - received self - released debut Adventures in the Kingdom of Blurtonia , co - produced by Daryl Smith whose credits include Sloan , Tricky Woo , and Godspeed You !
The New Dominion is a Dutch death metal band from Tilburg , formed in 2006 .
Youngstown State University ( YSU ) , founded in 1908 , is an urban research university located in Youngstown , Ohio , United States .
The Queen signed a warrant on 13 August 1994 to allow formation of the Corps of Army Music .

Radiation City is an American indie rock band that began in Portland , Oregon , in 2010 .
Aaj News was initially started on March 23 , 2005 by the Business Recorder Group .
The Saudi Arabian Monetary Agency ( SAMA ) , established in 1952 , is the central bank of the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia .
Microland was started in Bangalore , India in August 1989 with a key focus on hardware and networking till date .
America 's Talking was an American cable television channel focused mainly on talk based programming , created by NBC and spun off from economic channel CNBC , that was launched on July 4 , 1994 and replaced on July 15 , 1996 .
After numerous lawsuits , BonairExel ( now called Bonaire Express ) and Curaçao Express merged to form Dutch Antilles Express , which started operations on April 30 , 2005 with flights between the Netherlands Antilles and Aruba .
The Bahrain Centre for Human Rights is a Bahraini non - profit non - governmental organisation which works to promote human rights in Bahrain , which was founded by a number of Bahraini activists in June 2002 .
Haliç University is a foundation university , which was founded in 1998 by the Children Leukemia Foundation in Turkey .

Malignus Youth was a hardcore punk band from Sierra Vista , Arizona that was active from 1987 - -1994 and again from 1999 - 2001 .

Virgin Sun Airlines , branded as Virgin Sun , was a British scheduled and charter airline owned by the Virgin Group , formed in 1998 .
The Independent Press Standards Organisation ( IPSO ) was established on Monday 8 September 2014 following the windup of the Press Complaints Commission ( PCC ) , which had been the main industry regulator of the press in the United Kingdom since 1990 .
The Austrian Empire ( Austrian German : Kaiserthum Oesterreich , modern spelling Kaisertum Österreich ) was an empire in Central Europe created out of the realms of the Habsburgs by proclamation in 1804 .
Omnivore Recordings is an independent record label founded in 2010 , specializing in CD and vinyl reissues of previously out - of - print albums by notable artists .
The United States Basketball Writers Association ( USBWA ) was founded in 1956 by National Collegiate Athletic Association director Walter Byers to serve the interests of journalists who cover college basketball .
CKJM - FM 's history stems back to 1991 , when the station was on the air intermittently on a special events license issued by the CRTC and Industry Canada , which allowed it to be on the air for only up to 28 days per event .

Harvey Mandel ( born March 11 , 1945 , in Detroit , Michigan , United States ) is an American guitarist known for his innovative approach to electric guitar playing .

Steve Lacy ( July 23 , 1934 -- June 4 , 2004 ) , born Steven Norman Lackritz in New York City , was a jazz saxophonist and composer recognized as one of the important players of soprano saxophone .

Charles Edward Montague , ( 1 January 1867 -- 28 May 1928 ) , was an English journalist , known also as a writer of novels and essays .

Juan Navarro Baldeweg ( 11 June 1939 , Santander ) is a Spanish architect and professor at the Superior Technical School of Architecture of Madrid ( ETSAM ) .

Doris Mary Stenton ( 1894 - -1971 ) was an English historian of the Middle Ages .
Georges Sagnac ( 14 October 1869 -- 26 February 1928 ) was a French physicist who lent his name to the Sagnac effect , a phenomenon which is at the basis of interferometers and ring laser gyroscopes developed since the 1970s .
Miguel Navarro Cañizares ( c. 1835 , Valencia - 23 October 1913 , Río de Janeiro ) was a Spanish painter and art teacher who worked in Venezuela and Brazil .

Francesco Ferruccio ( or Ferrucci ) ( 1489 -- August 3 , 1530 ) was an Italian captain from Florence who fought in the Italian Wars .
Walter Sedlmayr ( 6 January 1926 -- 14 July 1990 ) was a German stage , television , and film actor from Bavaria .
Nicholas Miklouho - Maclay ( Russian : Николай Николаевич Миклухо-Маклай , Ukrainian : Микола Миколайович Миклухо-Маклай ; 1846 - -1888 ) was a Russian explorer , ethnologist , anthropologist and biologist who became famous as the first scientist to settle among and study people who had never seen a European .
Charles Lacheroy ( 22 August 1906 -- 25 January 2005 ) was a French Army officer , theorist of Counter - insurgency warfare , and member of the Organisation de l'armée secrète .

Léon Bouveret ( 27 September 1850 -- 1929 ) was a French internist born in Saint - Julien - sur - Reyssouze , a community in the department of Ain .
Sayed Darwish ( Arabic : سيد درويش‎ , IPA : ( ˈsæjjed dæɾˈwiːʃ ) ; 17 March 1892 -- 15 September 1923 ) was an Egyptian singer and composer who was considered the father of Egyptian popular music and one of Egypt 's greatest musicians and its single greatest composer .
William Haughton ( died 1605 ) was an English playwright in the age of English Renaissance theatre .
Juan Antonio San Epifanio Ruiz ( `` Epi '' ) ( born 12 June 1959 ) is a retired Spanish professional basketball player , who is considered to be one of the greatest small forwards ever to play in Europe .
Massimo Bray ( born 11 April 1959 ) is an Italian intellectual and politician , who served as the minister of culture from 28 April 2013 to 22 February 2014 .
Fathallah Oualalou ( Arabic : فتح الله والعلو‎ ) ( born 1942 in Rabat ) is a Moroccan politician .
Jerónimo de la Gándara ( 1825 - -1877 ) was a Spanish architect who designed a number of public buildings during the reign of Isabella II of Spain .
Mykola Khvylovy ( Ukrainian : Микола Хвильовий , Ukrainian pronunciation : ( mɪ'kɔɫɐ xvɪlʲo'vɪj ) ) ( December 13 ( O.S. December 1 ) 1893 -- May 13 , 1933 ) was a Ukrainian writer and poet of the early Communist era Ukrainian Renaissance ( 1920 - -1930 ) .
Mario De Caro ( born 1963 ) is an Italian philosopher who teaches Moral Philosophy at the University of Rome III in Rome , Italy .
Thomas Tusser ( 1524 -- 3 May 1580 ) was an English poet and farmer , best known for his instructional poem Five Hundred Points of Good Husbandry , an expanded version of his original title , A Hundreth Good Pointes of Husbandrie , first published in 1557 .
Radoslav Katičić ( pronounced ( rǎdɔslaʋ kâtitʃitɕ ) ) ( born in Zagreb , July 3 , 1930 ) is a Croatian linguist , classical philologist , Indo - Europeanist , Slavist and Indologist , one of the most prominent Croatian scholars in the field of humanities .
Marcel Niedergang ( 1922 - 2001 ) was a French journalist and non - fiction author .
Jacqueline Joubert ( 29 March 1921 -- 8 January 2005 ) , born Jacqueline Annette Édith Pierre , was a French television continuity announcer , producer and director .
Abdelhamid Ben Badis ( Arabic : عبد الحميد بن باديس‎ , Ben Badis ; December 4 , 1889 -- April 16 , 1940 ) was an emblematic figure of the Islamic Reform movement in Algeria .
Father Ghevont Alishan ( Armenian : Ղևոնդ Ալիշան ) ( 1820 - 1901 ; also spelled Ghevond Alishan ) was an ordained Armenian Catholic priest , historian and a poet .
Charles Prévost was a French chemist .
Richard Rogler ( born 19 September 1949 in Selb ) is an award - winning German Kabarett artist and professor of Kabarett at the University of the Arts in Berlin .
Zi Zhongyun ( simplified Chinese : 资中筠 ; traditional Chinese : 資中筠 ; pinyin : Zī Zhōngyún ; born June 1930 ) is a Chinese translator and historian who is an expert on US studies with the Chinese Academy of Social Sciences .

John de Monins Johnson ( 1882 - -1956 ) was an English papyrologist , printer of the Oxford English Dictionary , and collector .
Hermann Cohen ( 4 July 1842 -- 4 April 1918 ) was a German Jewish philosopher , one of the founders of the Marburg School of Neo - Kantianism , and he is often held to be `` probably the most important Jewish philosopher of the nineteenth century '' .
Jean - Yves Mollier ( born 5 November 1947 ) is a French contemporary history teacher .
Francesco Provenzale ( 15 September 1624 -- 6 September 1704 ) was an Italian Baroque composer and teacher .
Esteban Maroto ( born 1942 ) is a Spanish comic book artist .
Eddy Marnay , the professional name of Edmond Bacri , ( Algiers , 18 December 1920 -- 3 January 2003 ) , was a French songwriter .

Abu Hena is an Indian National Congress politician , who was a cabinet minister and is a five - time MLA .
Gerhard Roßbach ( February 28 , 1893 -- August 30 , 1967 ) , also spelt Rossbach , was a German Freikorps leader and organizer of nationalist groups after World War I. He is generally credited with inventing the brown colored uniforms of the Nazi Party after supplying surplus tropical khaki shirts to early troops of the Sturmabteilung .
Marie Borge Refsum ( born 20 March 1927 ) is a Norwegian politician , who served as a member of the Conservative Party .
Rahul Shewale ( Marathi : राहुल शेवाळे)(born 1973 ) is an Indian politician from the Shiv Sena and the Lok Sabha member from the Mumbai South Central constituency .
Rossana Dinamarca ( born 2 January 1974 in Santiago , Chile ) is a Chilean exile and Swedish Left Party politician and student .
Henrika Juliana von Liewen ( 16 February 1709 -- 26 August 1779 ) was a Swedish noble , socialite and lady - in - waiting , politically active on behalf of the Hats ( party ) during the Age of liberty .
Antonio Hernández Mancha ( born April 1 , 1951 , Guareña , Badajoz ) is a former Spanish politician and former president of the People 's Alliance political party from 1987 - 1989 .
Bilal Ag Acherif ( born 1977 , last name alternatively spelled Cherif ) is the Secretary - General of the National Movement for the Liberation of Azawad ( MNLA ) and president of a briefly independent Azawad .
Winifred Ann Taylor , Baroness Taylor of Bolton , PC ( born 2 July 1947 ) is a British Labour Party politician , who was Minister for International Defence and Security , based at both the Ministry of Defence and the Foreign and Commonwealth Office , from October 2008 until 11 May 2010 .
Joseph J. Roberts , Jr. ( born July 14 , 1952 ) is an American Democratic Party politician who served in the New Jersey General Assembly from 1987 to 2010 , where he represented the 5th Legislative District .
Erhard Heiden ( 23 February 1901 -- c. April 1933 ) was an early member of the Nazi Party and the third commander of the paramilitary wing of Schutzstaffel ( SS ) , the Sturmabteilung ( `` Storm Detachment ; SA '' ) .
Lyonpo Sangay Ngedup , whose demonstrated leadership style is democratic , was unanimously elected as president and leader of the newly constituted People 's Democratic Party .
Luc Recordon ( born on 20 September 1955 in Pully ) is a Swiss politician , member of the Green Party of Switzerland , representing Vaud in the Swiss National Council and then in the Swiss Council of States .
Norma Violeta Dávila Salinas is a Mexican teacher and politician affiliated to the Institutional Revolutionary Party .
David Kimutai Too ( August 23 , 1968 -- January 31 , 2008 ) was a Kenyan politician affiliated to the Orange Democratic Movement ( ODM ) .
Murli Manohar ( born 15 December 1895 , date of death unknown ) was an Indian politician from Uttar Pradesh state , and the member of parliament in 1962 for the Ballia Lok Sabha constituency from Indian National Congress .

Admiral Sir Francis Laforey , 2nd Baronet , KCB ( 31 December 1767 -- 17 June 1835 ) was an officer of the British Royal Navy during the French Revolutionary and Napoleonic Wars , whose distinguished service record included numerous frigate commands in Home waters and in the West Indies .
Erbo Graf von Kageneck ( 2 April 1918 -- 12 January 1942 ) was a German fighter pilot and flying ace in the Luftwaffe from 1938 to 1942 .
Alexander Peters ( November 16 , 1869 -- June 11 , 1951 ) was a United States Navy sailor and a recipient of the United States military 's highest decoration , the Medal of Honor , for attempting to rescue a shipmate from drowning during a storm .
Michael J. Williams ( born July 12 , 1943 ) is a retired United States Marine Corps 4-star general .
General Nathaniel Stevenson ( 1840 - -1911 ) was a British Army officer who became Lieutenant Governor of Guernsey .
Brigadier - General Charles Ogston CB CMG DSO ( 14 September 1877 -- 10 November 1944 ) was a British Army staff officer .
Carson Abel Roberts ( September 4 , 1905 - December 19 , 1983 ) was a Lieutenant General in the United States Marine Corps .
Margaret of Hohenzollern - Nuremberg ( 1367 - 1406 ) was a daughter of Burgrave Frederick V of Nuremberg and his wife , Elisabeth of Meissen .
Her dam was the 1934 American Champion Two - Year - Old Filly Nellie Flag , and her sire was the 1930 Epsom Derby winner Blenheim , who had been imported to the United States in 1937 by a syndicate that included Mar - Kell 's breeder , Calumet Farm .
Princess Irene of Hesse and by Rhine ( Irene Louise Marie Anne Princess of Hesse and by Rhine , 11 July 1866 -- 11 November 1953 ) was the third child and third daughter of Princess Alice of the United Kingdom and Ludwig IV , Grand Duke of Hesse and by Rhine .
Judith of Bavaria , Duchess of Swabia ( 19 May 1100 -- 27 Aug 1130 ) was a member of the powerful German House of Welf , being the eldest daughter of Henry IX of Bavaria and Wulfhilde of Saxony .
Lady Sun was the only daughter of Sun Jian and Lady Wu .
George Roden was the presumed successor to his mother Lois Roden , who had become president of the Branch Davidians in 1978 , when her husband and group leader Benjamin Roden had died .
Lucia Visconti ( Milan , 1372 -- April 14 , 1424 ) was the daughter of Bernabò Visconti , Lord of Milan , and Beatrice Regina della Scala .
Sophie Augusta of Holstein - Gottorp ( 5 December 1630 in Gottorp -- 12 December 1680 in Coswig ) was a daughter van Frederick III , Duke of Holstein - Gottorp and Duchess Marie Elisabeth of Saxony .
Antoine Marie Jacob De la Gardie was born in Reval ( today Tallinn ) , Estonia ( then part of the Swedish Empire ) , as a son of Pontus De la Gardie and Sofia Johansdotter Gyllenhielm , the illegitimate daughter of king John III of Sweden .
Princess Elizabeth of the United Kingdom ( 22 May 1770 -- 10 January 1840 ) was the 7th child and 3rd daughter of King George III and Charlotte of Mecklenburg - Strelitz .
The Bagaduce River is a tidal river in the Hancock County , Maine that empties into Penobscot Bay near the town of Castine .
The Neglinnaya River ( Russian : Неглинная ) , also known as Neglinka , Neglinna , Neglimna ( Неглинка , Неглинна , Неглимна ) , is a 7.5-km long underground river in the central part of Moscow and a tributary of the Moskva River .
It preserves the historic Carillon Canal that was first built in the 1830s to facilitate travel on the Ottawa River .
Mand River is a tributary of Mahanadi and joins it in Chandrapur 28 km before Orissa border and before the river reaches Hirakud dam .
The Kiewa River flows generally north northwest , joined by eleven minor tributaries , towards its confluence with the Murray River , southeast of Albury and east of Wodonga .
It flows through Saint - Étienne - de - Tinée , Isola and Saint - Sauveur - sur - Tinée , and it flows into the Var near Utelle .
The Wallagaraugh River is a perennial river of the Genoa River catchment , with its headwaters located in the South Coast region of New South Wales and its lower reaches located in the East Gippsland region of Victoria , Australia .
San Paolo alle Tre Fontane ( Italian ) , in English , St Paul at the Three Fountains is a church dedicated to St Paul the Apostle , at the presumed site of his martyrdom in Rome .
The Theodor Körner Prize ( German : Theodor - Körner - Preis ) is a set of annual Austrian awards bestowed by the Theodor Körner Fund in recognition of cultural and/or scientific advances .
USS Mariano G. Vallejo ( SSBN-658 ) , was a Benjamin Franklin class fleet ballistic missile submarine , was named for Mariano Guadalupe Vallejo ( 1807 - -1890 ) , a key proponent of California statehood .
The G - spot , also called the Gräfenberg spot ( for German gynecologist Ernst Gräfenberg ) , is characterized as an erogenous area of the vagina that , when stimulated , may lead to strong sexual arousal , powerful orgasms and potential female ejaculation .
In papyrology , Maas 's law - named after classical scholar Paul Maas ( 1880 - -1964 ) - refers to the observation that columns in bookrolls often exhibit a forward tilt such that both edges of a column gradually move to the left as the column progresses .
The color indigo was named after the indigo dye derived from the plant Indigofera tinctoria and related species .
MusicBrainz Picard is named for Captain Jean - Luc Picard , a character in the US television series Star Trek :
The Farnese Gardens ( Orti Farnesiani sul Palatino or `` Gardens of Farnese upon the Palatine '' ) are a garden in Rome , central Italy , created in 1550 on the northern portion of Palatine Hill , by Cardinal Alessandro Farnese .
Mill 's Methods are five methods of induction described by philosopher John Stuart Mill in his 1843 book A System of Logic .
Ismoil Somoni Peak ( Tajik : Қуллаи Исмоили Сомонӣ , Qullai Ismoili Somonī ; Russian : пик Исмаила Самани pik Ismaila Samani ) is the highest mountain in Tajikistan and in the former Russian Empire and later in the Soviet Union , named after Ismail Samani , the greatest ruler of the Samanid dynasty .
Public Domain Day is an observance of when copyrights expire and works enter into the public domain .
The Dovzhenko Film Studios ( Ukrainian : Національна кіностудія художніх фільмів імені О. Довженка , translit . Natsional'na kinostudiya khudozhnikh filmiv imeni O. Dovzhenka ) is a former Soviet film production studios located in Ukraine that were named after the Ukrainian film producer , Alexander Dovzhenko , in 1957 .
The Bure kinship ( Swedish : Bureätten ) is a Scandinavian kinship , centered in the Skellefteå area , today 's Bureå in Northern Sweden .
It is usually thought that the first such camp in the general area of today 's Khabarovsk was the fortified winter camp named Achansk ( Ачанск ) or Achansky gorodok ( Ачанский городок ) , built by the Cossacks of Yerofey Khabarov in September 1651 after they had sailed to the area from the upper Amur .
The Letelier - Moffitt Human Rights Award commemorates Orlando Letelier and Ronni Moffitt , who in 1976 were assassinated in Washington , D.C. by agents of the Chilean secret service .

Dick and the Duchess is a 1950s CBS situation comedy filmed and set in London , England , and starring Patrick O'Neal and Hazel Court .
The Cult of Sincerity is an independent film about hipster culture and postmodernist irony set in Williamsburg in Brooklyn , New York .

Out of the Fire ( ISBN 0 - 8041 - 0104 - 3 ) is a Vietnam War novel by David Sherman published in 1987 by the Ivy Book imprint of Ballantine Books .
Tea with the Black Dragon is about Martha MacNamara , called west to San Francisco by a message from her daughter , Elizabeth , a computer programmer .

Antoine Joseph Gorsas ( March 24 , 1752 -- October 7 , 1793 ) was a French publicist and politician .

William McKendree ( July 6 , 1757 -- March 5 , 1835 ) was the fourth Bishop of the Methodist Episcopal Church , and the first Methodist bishop born in the United States .
Chris D. ( born Chris Desjardins ; January 15 , 1952 ) is a punk poet , rock critic , singer , writer , actor and filmmaker .
Juan Miguel de Guzman ( born September 9 , 1988 ) , popularly known by his screen name JM de Guzman , is a Filipino actor , mixed martial artist , model and singer .
Ryan Dunlap ( born October 21 , 1983 ) is an American independent film and short story actor , writer , and director .
Marija Knežević , a Serbian poet , fiction writer , essayist , literary translator and professor of literature was born in Belgrade , Serbia , in 1963 .
Kirsty MacColl was the daughter of folk singer Ewan MacColl and dancer Jean Newlove .
Fabián E. Bustamante is an Argentinian - American computer scientist specializing in distributed systems and computer networking .
William D. Chapple ( August 6 , 1868 -- ? ) was a Massachusetts lawyer and politician who served on the Salem City Council , in the Massachusetts House of Representatives ; and as a member , and President of , the Massachusetts Senate .
Lenin Arroyo ( born October 19 , 1979 in San José , Costa Rica ) is a professional boxer based in Miami , Florida , in the United States .
The Argentinean guitarist Pablo Márquez is considered today as one of the most accomplished and versatile virtuosi of his instrument .
Gordon H. Peck ( 1857 -- February 18 , 1921 ) was an American manufacturer and politician from New York .
František Antonín Nickerl ( December 4 , 1813 in Prague -- February 4 , 1871 in Prague ) was a Czech entomologist who specialised in Lepidoptera , especially those of the Riesengebirges .
Kim Goody ( born 19 February 1954 , London , England ) is an English actress , composer , singer and songwriter .
Luc Malo ( born November 2 , 1973 ) is a Canadian politician , who was a Member of Parliament for the riding of Verchères--
Shira Nayman ( born April 26 , 1960 ) is a novelist and short story writer best known for her collection Awake in the Dark , published in 2006 .
George Henry Corliss ( June 2 , 1817 -- February 21 , 1888 ) was an American mechanical engineer and inventor , who developed the Corliss steam engine , which was a great improvement over any other stationary steam engine of its time .
Timothy Ting Ting - yu ( 丁庭宇 , born 1954 ) is a Taiwanese politician and sociologist .
Patrick O'Hea ( born 1848 ) was an Irish nationalist politician and a Member of Parliament ( MP ) from 1885 to 1890 .
Nouraiz Shakoor ( Urdu , Punjabi : نوریز شکور ; born Chaudhry Nouraiz Shakoor Khan on October 19 , 1950 ) is a Pakistani politician from Sahiwal who has been a member of the National Assembly three times ( in the 1988 , 1993 and 2002 elections respectively ) .
Hanna Fahl ( born October 23 , 1978 ) is a Swedish music journalist and translator .
Roberto Iniesta Ojea ( Spanish pronunciation : ( roˈβeɾto iˈnjesta oˈxe.a ) ; May 16 , 1962 ) , also known as Robe ; is a Spanish songwriter , singer and guitarist .
Boris Sidis ( /ˈsaɪdɪs/ ; October 12 , 1867 -- October 24 , 1923 ) was a Ukrainian American psychologist , physician , psychiatrist , and philosopher of education .
Howard McCalebb ( b. Indianola , Mississippi , May 13 , 1947 ) is an African - American abstract sculptor .
Bryce Goggin is a record producer and sound engineer .
Alice Meichi Li ( 李美姿 ) is a Chinese - American , New York City - based visual artist and illustrator for comic books , magazines , and album covers .
Fred Sammartino is an American communications - industry engineer and executive , well known as the founding president and chairman of the board of the ATM Forum .
Roberto Juan Rodríguez ( Havana ) is a Cuban - American jazz musician who is known for fusion of Latin music and Jewish Klezmer elements .
Zvi Hercowitz ( Hebrew : צבי הרקוביץ‎ ) is an Israeli economist and economics professor .
Ameet Chana ( born 12 September 1975 in Epsom , Surrey , England ) is a British Indian actor .
Dabney Carr ( April 27 , 1773 -- January 8 , 1837 ) was a Virginia lawyer , writer and a justice of the Virginia Supreme Court of Appeals .
Ernst Mosch ( November 7 , 1925 -- May 15 , 1999 ) was a German musician , composer and conductor .
Anders Holm ( born May 29 , 1981 ) is an American actor , comedian and writer .
Earl Hurd ( September 14 , 1880 -- September 28 , 1940 ) was a pioneering American animator and film director .
Tim Hicks ( born August 22 , 1979 ) is a Canadian country music singer - songwriter from Niagara Falls , Ontario .
Zhou Lulu ( Chinese : 周璐璐 ; born March 19 , 1988 ) is a Chinese weightlifter .
Fred Federspiel is an American technology entrepreneur , nuclear physicist and inventor .
Clé Bennett is a Canadian television , film and stage actor .
Francisco Maria da Veiga , GCNSC , KCVO was a Portuguese judge and pro - monarchist .
Nonna Bella was a Turkish singer of Armenian descent , in the 1970s .
Shirley Kaneda is an abstract painter .
Sara Howard ( b. September 24 , 1981 ) is a politician from the U.S. state of Nebraska .
Sam Witt is an American poet and journalist who currently lives in Massachusetts and teaches at Framingham State University .
Charis Romas or Haris Romas ( Greek : Χάρης Ρώμας ) is a Greek actor , screenwriter , and lyricist .
Thomas Hecht ( born October 31 , 1960 in Baltimore , Maryland ) is an American pianist , composer and professor of piano , based at the Yong Siew Toh Conservatory of Music , National University of Singapore where he was appointed founding head of piano studies in 2003 .
Jack Epps Jr. ( born 1949 ) is an American screenwriter , known chiefly for such popular 80 's films as Top Gun , Legal Eagles and The Secret of My Success , which he wrote with longtime partner Jim Cash .
Michael Moriarty ( born April 5 , 1941 ) is an American - Canadian stage and screen actor and a jazz musician .
Sapna Mukherjee is a Bollywood playback singer who won the Filmfare Award for Best Female Playback Singer for the song `` Tirchi Topi Wale '' in Tridev ( 1989 ) .
William J. Ruane ( October 24 , 1925 -- October 4 , 2005 ) was an American businessman , investor , and philanthropist .
Janet Sternburg ( born January 18 , 1943 ) is an American writer of essays , poetry and memoir , as well as a fine art photographer .
Pascal Breland was a famous 19th - century Pre - confederation Canadian Métis farmer and politician .
Anas el - Fiqqi ( alternate spelling : Anas El Feki , Anas El - Feki , Anas Al - Faki , Anas al - Fiqi , Anas El - Fekky or el - Fiqi ) is an Egyptian politician .
Christopher Straub is a fashion designer who was a contestant on season 6 of the competitive reality show Project Runway and also appeared on season 1 of the competitive reality show Models of the Runway as the designer for the model Katie Sticksel , Celine Chua , and Matar Cohen .
William Boone Douglass was a lawyer , engineer , surveyor , genealogist , and founding President of the Boone Family Association .
Valeen Tippetts Avery ( December 22 , 1936 -- April 7 , 2006 ) was an American biographer and historian best known for her work on Western American and Latter Day Saint history .
Rose Aguilar is a progressive journalist and radio host from San Francisco , California .
Tricia Cooke is an American film editor who is married to director Ethan Coen .
Josefa Celsa Señaris or Señaris ( born 2 November 1965 ) is a Venezuelan herpetologist .
Susan Isaacs ( born December 7 , 1943 ) is an American novelist , essayist , and screenwriter .
Lynn Meredith is an American musician who was a founding member of Kansas .
Mark Angelo Cadaweng Cielo ( May 12 , 1988 -- December 7 , 2008 ) , better known as Marky Cielo , was a Filipino actor , dancer , and the first known Igorot in Philippine showbiz .
Richard John Neuhaus ( May 14 , 1936 -- January 8 , 2009 ) was a prominent Christian cleric ( first as a Lutheran pastor and later as a Roman Catholic priest ) and writer .
Terry Tufts ( William Terence Tufts born 1954 in Gasline , Ontario ) is a Canadian singer - songwriter writing in many different musical genres .
Andrew John Schofield ( Andy Schofield ) is a theoretical physicist and a professor at the University of Birmingham where he is a Pro - Vice - Chancellor and the Head of the College of Engineering and Physical Sciences ( EPS ) .
Patrick Cantlay ( born March 17 , 1992 ) is an American professional golfer who was the number one golfer in the World Amateur Golf Ranking for a record 55 weeks .
Carla van de Puttelaar ( born November 1 , 1967 ) is a Dutch fine art photographer .
Julius Stieglitz ( 1867 - -1937 ) was an American chemist of German Jewish origin .
Vera Sell - Ryazanoff ( born 1951 ) is a Russian - German painter and philosopher .
Larry Hovis ( February 20 , 1936 -- September 9 , 2003 ) was an American singer and actor best known for playing Sergeant Carter on the 1960s television sitcom Hogan 's Heroes .
Filbert Bayi Sanka ( born June 23 , 1953 ) is a former Tanzanian middle - distance runner of the 1970s who set the world records for 1500 metres in 1974 and the mile in 1975 .
Brady Hicks is a Philadelphia area journalist , radio personality , blogger , columnist , wrestling reporter , professional wrestling manager , play - by - play commentator , color analyst , and occasional Pro Wrestling Illustrated contributing writer .
Hobart Freeman ( October 17 , 1920 -- December 8 , 1984 ) was a charismatic preacher and author , who ministered in northern Indiana and actively promoted faith healing .
Felicitas Heyne is a German psychologist and book author .
Peter van Nieuwenhuizen ( Dutch : ( vɑn ˈniu̯əˌɦœyzə ) ; born October 26 , 1938 ) is a Dutch physicist .
Frank Bank ( April 12 , 1942 -- April 13 , 2013 ) was an American actor , particularly known for his role as Clarence `` Lumpy '' Rutherford on the 1957 - -1963 situation comedy television series Leave It to Beaver .
St. Margaret Mary Alacoque , V.H.M. ( French : Marguerite - Marie Alacoque ) ( 1647 - 1690 ) , was a French Roman Catholic nun and mystic , who promoted devotion to the Sacred Heart of Jesus in its modern form .
Adrian Grunberg is an American film director and screenwriter .
Ruth Brown ( January 12 , 1928 -- November 17 , 2006 ) was an American singer - songwriter and actress , sometimes known as the `` Queen of R&B '' .
Aster Yohannes is the wife of detained Eritrean politician Petros Solomon .
Arturo Soto Rangel ( March 12 , 1882 -- May 25 , 1965 ) was a Mexican film , television , and stage actor .
Alberto Arvelo Torrealba ( September 3 , 1905 - March 28 , 1971 ) , was a Venezuelan lawyer , educator and folklorical poet .
Joyce Haddelsey was an English Women 's Test cricketer .
Matt Jaffe ( born April 20 , 1995 ) is an American singer - songwriter , guitarist and founder of the band Matt Jaffe & The Distractions .
Hermann Bellinghausen ( born May 17 , 1953 ) is a Mexican physician , poet , writer , and editor .
Viera Tomanová ( born February 5 , 1948 ) is a Slovak politician , former Minister of Labour of Slovakia under Prime Minister Robert Fico .
Ishion Hutchinson is an award - winning Jamaican poet and essayist .
László Benedek ( Hungarian pronunciation : ( ˈlaːsloː ˈbɛnɛdɛk ) ; March 5 , 1905 -- March 11 , 1992 ; sometimes Laslo Benedek ) was a Hungarian - born film director and cinematographer , most notable for directing The Wild One ( 1953 ) .
Sidney Schwartz was a tennis player from the United States who competed in the mid-20th century .
Abdullah Dukuly ( Also known as Abdulai Dukuly , Abdoulaye W. Dukule ) is a Liberian journalist and news editor , formerly of The News , a Monrovia - based daily publication .
Abdullahi Ibrahim is a Nigerian lawyer , politician and administrator .
Joseph Percival Pollard ( January 29 , 1869 - December 17 , 1911 ) was an American literary critic , novelist and short story writer .
Harry Sawyerr was a Ghanaian politician and quantity surveyor .
Chen Wu - hsiung ( Chinese : 陳武雄 ; pinyin : Chén Wǔxióng ) is a politician in the Republic of China .
Mark Anthony Carpio is a choral conductor and a countertenor who is the present choirmaster of the Philippine Madrigal Singers , Kilyawan Boys Choir and Pansol Choir .
Guillaume IV de Melun , Count of Tancarville , Lord of Montreuil - Bellay , was a French politician , chamberlain and advisor to King Charles VI of France .
Basil Gill ( March 10 , 1877 -- April 23 , 1955 ) was a British stage actor and film actor .
Jeanne Lee ( January 29 , 1939 -- October 25 , 2000 ) was an American jazz singer , poet and composer .
William Bakewell ( May 2 , 1908 -- April 15 , 1993 ) , also known as Billy Bakewell , was an American actor , who achieved his greatest fame as one of the premiere juvenile performers of the late 1920s and early 1930s .
Jack Kilmer ( born June 6 , 1995 ) is an American actor best known for starring in the 2013 film Palo Alto .
Luther Severance ( October 26 , 1797 -- January 25 , 1855 ) was a United States Representative and diplomat from Maine .
Gogea Mitu ( born Goagă Stephen on September 23 , 1911 -- June 8 , 1936 ) was a Romanian boxer and the tallest Romanian in history ( followed by Ghiţă Mureșan ) .
Deandre Latimore ( born August 31 , 1985 ) is an American professional boxer and world title challenger .
Pieter Stoop is a Dutch painter of large abstract paintings .
Rex Bell , born George Francis Beldam ( October 16 , 1903 -- July 4 , 1962 ) , was an American actor and politician .
Glenn Firebaugh is an American sociologist ( born : Charleston , West Virginia ) and leading international authority on social science research methods .
Devin Vargas ( born December 25 , 1981 in Toledo , OH ) is a boxer who represented the United States at the 2004 Olympic Games in the heavyweight division .
Leigh Dragoon is a professional American comics writer and illustrator .
Erich Kobler was a German film editor and director .
Dr. Robert D. Maurer ( born July 20 , 1924 ) is an American industrial physicist noted for his leadership in the invention of optical fiber .
Ryley Walker ( born July 21 , 1989 ) is an American singer - songwriter and guitarist from Rockford , Illinois .
Christopher Atkins ( born Christopher Atkins Bomann ; February 21 , 1961 ) is an American actor , who became famous in his debut role with co - star Brooke Shields in the 1980 film The Blue Lagoon .
Margot Zemach ( November 30 , 1931 -- May 21 , 1989 ) was an American illustrator of more than forty children 's books , some of which she also wrote .
The Infinite Worlds of H. G. Wells is a four - hour miniseries conceived by Nick Willing and released in 2001 by the Hallmark Channel .
American Idol Extra is a television show that was shown on the Fox Reality Channel and Star ! and billed as `` the show that picks up right where American Idol leaves off '' .
ESPN Friday Night Fights ( last known as Friday Night Fights presented by Just for Men Haircolor for sponsorship reasons ) was a series of boxing events broadcast by ESPN2 .
The Gemma Factor is a BBC Three sitcom starring Anna Gilthorpe , Claire King and Gwyneth Powell .
Zapped is an American Disney Channel Original Movie .
Trial & Retribution is a feature - length ITV police procedural television drama series that began in 1997 .
MasterChef France is a French television series broadcast on TF1 in France .
Comics Britannia is a three - part documentary series from BBC Four which started on 10 September 2007 .
The Smothers Brothers Show is an American fantasy sitcom featuring the Smothers Brothers that aired on CBS on Friday nights at 9:30 p.m. ET from September 17 , 1965 to April 22 , 1966 , co - sponsored by Alberto - Culver 's VO5 hairdressing products and American Tobacco ( Tareyton ) .
Saved by the Bell is an American television sitcom that aired on NBC from 1989 to 1993 .
Codice rosso ( Code Red ) is an Italian television series produced in 2006 and broadcast on Canale 5 between 16 November and 15 December 2006 .
Late Night with Conan O'Brien is an American late - night talk show hosted by Conan O'Brien that aired 2,725 episodes on NBC between 1993 and 2009 .
Welcome to the Parker is an American reality television series on Bravo that premiered on July 26 , 2007 .
Murdoch Mysteries is a Canadian television drama series aired on both City and CBC Television , titled The Artful Detective on the Ovation cable TV network , featuring Yannick Bisson as William Murdoch , a police detective working in Toronto , Ontario , around the turn of the twentieth century .
Domenica in is an Italian Sunday long - running television show broadcast by Rai 1 since 1976 .
13 x 13 was a Catalan TV series which aired in TV3 .
Liquid Television is an animation showcase that appeared on MTV .
Acceptable . TV is a television program created by Dan Harmon and Rob Schrab that aired on VH1 from March 23 to May 11 , 2007 .
The Colgate Comedy Hour is an American comedy - musical variety series that aired live on the NBC network from 1950 to 1955 .
Ice Cold Gold is a reality television series that airs on Animal Planet .
Felicidade ( English : Happiness ) is a Brazilian telenovela produced and broadcast by Rede Globo from October 7 , 1991 to May 30 , 1992 .
Making the Band was an ABC / MTV reality television series that exists in separate iterations , each iteration focusing on a specific music act .
Boxing After Dark is an HBO boxing program , premiering in April 1996 , that usually shows fights between well - known contenders , but usually not `` championship '' or `` title '' fights .
Cash Bonanza is an Australian game show hosted by Larry Emdur , which was broadcast on the Nine Network in 2001 .
Tony Robinson 's Crime and Punishment is a British documentary for Channel 4 .
Oi Aparadektoi ( Greek : Οι Απαράδεκτοι , English : The Unacceptables ) is a comedy television series broadcast by Mega Channel from September 1991 to January 1993 .
Weekends with Alex Witt is a news program on MSNBC anchored by Alex Witt .
Piel salvaje is a Venezuelan telenovela produced by RCTV for Televen .
Goodnight , Beantown is an American sitcom that aired on CBS for two brief seasons in 1983 and 1984 .
Arka Sokaklar ( Turkish for `` back streets '' ) , a long - running television crime series on Turkish Kanal D , was first broadcast in July 2006 .
Through the Eyes of Tomorrow was a Canadian variety and public affairs television series for youth which aired on CBC Television from 1966 to 1969 .
The Glee Project is an American reality television series from Oxygen .
The PBA on Viva TV was a presentation of Philippine Basketball Association games on Intercontinental Broadcasting Corporation by VIVA Entertainment after the company absorbed Vintage Sports .
Deadly Women is a television series first aired in 2005 on the Discovery Channel , focusing on female killers .
Ktsarim ( Hebrew : קצרים‎ , lit . Shorts ) is an Israeli sketch comedy series , broadcast on Channel 2 , and based on the British comedy show The Sketch Show .
C'mon , Have A Go ! was an Australian television game show broadcast on the Seven Network in 1985 and 1986 .
Top Ground Gear Force is a one - off TV special , featuring the cast of BBC 's Top Gear , which originally aired on BBC Two at 22:00 GMT on 14 March 2008 as part of Sport Relief 2008 .
Brooklyn Kinda Love is an adult reality series currently airing on Playboy TV .
NFL Insiders is a National Football League studio show , currently airing Monday through Friday at 3:00 p.m. ET on ESPN .
Poor Nastya ( Russian : Бедная Настя , Bednaya Nastya ) is a Russian telenovela originally aired from 31 October 2003 to 30 April 2004 on the STS .
The Judy and Jim Show is a Canadian variety television miniseries which aired on CBC Television as separate runs in 1973 and 1977 .
Plats bruts ( Catalan pronunciation : ( ˈpɫats ˈβɾuts ) , meaning in English `` Dirty dishes '' ) is a sitcom issued for TV3 .
Peninta Peninta ( in English Fifty - Fifty ) is a Greek television series that was first aired from 2005 to 2007 by Mega Channel .
Pachybrachis is a genus of leaf beetles , Chrysomelidae , in the tribe Cryptocephalini of the subfamily Cryptocephalinae and belong to the group of casebearers called the Camptosomata .
The Tyrrhenian painted frog ( Discoglossus sardus ) is a species of frog in the Alytidae family ( formerly Discoglossidae ) .
Comocladia is a genus of flowering plants in the cashew family , Anacardiaceae .
Auroracetus , from Aurora ( the location the holotype was discovered , Aurora N.C. ) and the Latin cetus ( whale ) , is a genus of Pontoporiidae , the river dolphins , and contains one extinct species .
( 2010 ) showing the phylogenetic relationship of Cerrejonisuchus within Dyrosauridae :
Stiles 's tapaculo ( Scytalopus stilesi ) is a member of the tapaculos , a group of Neotropical birds .
Taiwanotrechus subglobosus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Taiwanotrechus .
Duabanga was traditionally included in the ditypic family Sonneratiaceae , but it is now classified in its own monotypic subfamily Duabangoideae of the Lythraceae .
Austropaxillus is a genus of fungi in the family Serpulaceae , containing nine species found in Australia , New Zealand and South America .
The Pacific angelshark ( Squatina californica ) is a species of angel shark , family Squatinidae , found in the eastern Pacific Ocean from Alaska to the Gulf of California , and from Ecuador to Chile , although those in the Gulf of California and southeastern Pacific may in fact be separate species .
Capraria is a genus of flowering plants in the figwort family , Scrophulariaceae .
The Cyphonocerinae are a subfamily of fireflies ( Lampyridae ) with only a few handful of species in ( presumably ) two genera found in North America and Eurasia .
The Radde 's accentor ( Prunella ocularis ) is a species of bird in the Prunellidae family .
Monneus longiventris is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Monneus .
The genus Eudyptula ( `` good little diver '' ) contains two species of penguin .
Gnaphalodes trachyderoides is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Gnaphalodes .
Mayaphaenops sbordonii is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Mayaphaenops .
Ramphotrigon is a genus of tyrant flycatchers in the Tyrannidae family .
The Beijing barbastelle ( Barbastella beijingensis ) , also known as the Beijing wide - eared bat , is a species of vesper bat endemic to Beijing Municipality , China .
Data based on nuclear DNA support Glires as a sister of Euarchonta to form Euarchontoglires ( Murphy et al . and Madsen et al . 2001 ) , but some genetic data from both nuclear and mitochondrial DNA have been less supportive ( Arnason et al . 2002 ) .
The Lentariaceae are a family of fungi belonging in what is classically known as the Gomphales order , or cladistically as the gomphoid - phalloid clade .
The Catophragmidae are a family of barnacles in the superfamily Chthamaloidea with eight shell wall plates ( rostrum , carina , paired rostrolatera , carinolatera I and carinolatera II ) , surrounded by several whorls of imbricating plates .
The Mount Oku hylomyscus ( Hylomyscus grandis ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Zoopagomycotina is a subphylum ( incertae sedis ) of the fungal phylum Zygomycota sensu lato .
Welleritidae is one of five families of the Schistocerataceae superfamily .
The Korean skate ( Hongeo koreana ) is a skate in the family Rajidae , and is the sole member of its genus .
Rooniella camerunica is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Rooniella .
Brosset 's big - eared bat ( Micronycteris brosseti ) is a bat species from South America .
Hortia is a genus of plants in family Rutaceae , with 10 species native to Central America and northern South America .
Pomatiopsis is a genus of amphibious snails with gills and an operculum , aquatic freshwater gastropod mollusks in the family Pomatiopsidae .
Navanax is a genus of sea slugs , marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusks in the family Aglajidae .
Peach latent mosaic viroid is a type species from the genus Pelamoviroid , which belongs to the family Avsunviroidae .
The Florida black bear ( Ursus americanus floridanus ) is a subspecies of the American black bear that has historically ranged throughout most of Florida and southern portions of Alabama , Georgia , and Mississippi .
The Texas heelsplitter , scientific name Potamilus amphichaenus , is a species of freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusk in the family Unionidae , the river mussels .
Malakichthys is a genus of fish in the family Acropomatidae , the temperate ocean - basses or lanternfishes .
Morierina is a genus of plant in family Rubiaceae first described as a genus in 1865 .
The Penang betta ( Betta pugnax ) is a species of gourami native to Southeast Asia and common in swiftly flowing forest streams of the Malay Peninsula , Cambodia , Thailand , Borneo , and Sumatra .
Lamiinae , commonly called flat - faced longhorns , are a subfamily of the longhorn beetle family ( Cerambycidae ) .
The Eritrea clawed frog or Peracca 's clawed frog ( Xenopus clivii ) is a species of frog in the Pipidae family found in Eritrea , Ethiopia , Kenya , and Sudan .
The King Kong grosbeak or giant grosbeak ( Chloridops regiskongi ) is a prehistoric species of Hawaiian honeycreeper , that was endemic to Hawaiʻi .
Mizotrechus novemstriatus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Mizotrechus .
The Ruspoli 's turaco ( Tauraco ruspolii ) , also known as Prince Ruspoli 's turaco or Touraco De Ruspoli , is a species of bird in the Musophagidae family .
The Kivu long - haired shrew ( Crocidura lanosa ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Neofelis diardi borneensis ( Wilting et al . , 2007 ) is a subspecies of the Sunda clouded leopard ( Neofelis diardi ) native to the island of Borneo .
Cleistesiopsis is an orchid genus in the tribe Pogonieae .
Fraxinus latifolia ( Oregon ash ) is a member of the ash genus Fraxinus , native to western North America .
The family Rallidae has traditionally been grouped with two families of larger birds , the cranes and bustards , as well as several smaller families of usually `` primitive '' mid - sized amphibious birds , to make up the order Gruiformes .
Zeaspora ( scientific name Diheterospora zeaspora ) is a rare medical condition and species of fungus .
The parotias are a genus , Parotia , of passerine birds in the bird - of - paradise family Paradisaeidae .
Cofana is a genus of leafhoppers belonging to the family Cicadellidae .
The Solomons cuckooshrike or black - bellied cicadabird ( Coracina holopolia ) is a species of bird in the Campephagidae family .
Dasyspora is a genus of rust fungi in the family Uropyxidaceae .
Stenorhynchus is a genus of marine crabs in the family Inachidae , containing the following species :
Netrostoma is a genus of true jellyfish in the family Cepheidae .
Dicoelia is a plant genus of the family Euphorbiaceae and the only genus of the tribe ( Dicoelieae ) .
Tmesisternini is a tribe of beetles in the subfamily Lamiinae containing the following genera :
The Tacarcuna bush tanager ( Chlorospingus tacarcunae ) is a species of bird traditionally placed in the family Thraupidae , but perhaps closer to Arremonops in the Emberizidae .
Lasiognathus is a genus of deep - sea anglerfish in the family Thaumatichthyidae , with six species known from the Atlantic and Pacific Oceans .
Paratylopus is an extinct genus of terrestrial herbivore the family Camelidae , endemic to North America from the Eocene through Oligocene 38.0 - -30.8 , existing for approximately 7.2 million years .
Varicellovirus ( var′i - sel′ō - vi′rŭs ) is a genus of viruses belonging to subfamily Alphaherpesvirinae , a member of family Herpesviridae .
Whitespotted conger ( Conger myriaster ) ( Japanese name : ma - anago ) is in the family of conger eels , widespread in the Northwest Pacific near the coasts of Japan , Korean Peninsula , and the East China Sea .
Hovenia is a small genus of deciduous trees or shrubs in the family Rhamnaceae .
Trichodrias esoterica is a species of beetle in the family Dermestidae , the only species in the genus Trichodrias .
The Archbold 's bowerbird ( Archboldia papuensis ) is a medium - sized , up to 37 cm long , dark grey songbird with brown iris , grey feet and black bill .
The Ipanema bat ( Pygoderma bilabiatum ) , is a bat species from South America .
Cinereomyces is a genus of resupinate ( crust - like ) fungi in the family Polyporaceae , circumscribed by Swiss mycologist Walter Jülich in 1981 .
Kiwitrechus karenscottae is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Kiwitrechus .
Scotonycteris is a small genus of bat in the family Pteropodidae .
Acanthochitona is a genus of chitons in the family Acanthochitonidae , of worldwide distribution .
The Schalow 's turaco ( Tauraco schalowi ) is a frugivorous bird in the Musophagidae family .
The Maracaibo tody - flycatcher ( Todirostrum viridanum ) , also known as the short - tailed tody - flycatcher , is a species of bird in the Tyrannidae family .
The Alagoas tyrannulet ( Phylloscartes ceciliae ) is a species of bird in the Tyrannidae family .
Plectopylidae is a taxonomic family of large air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Plectopyloidea .
Von der Decken 's hornbill ( Tockus deckeni ) is a hornbill found in East Africa , especially to the east of the East African Rift , from Ethiopia south to Tanzania .
Erinus is a genus of flowering plants in the family Plantaginaceae ( previously in the family Scrophulariaceae ) , native to stony mountainous sites in North Africa and southern Europe .
Oxyria is a genus of plants in the family Polygonaceae with two currently accepted species .
