Eocypraeidae is a small family of large sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the superfamily Cypraeoidea , the cowries and cowry allies .
Frieseomelitta is a stingless bee ( Meliponini ) genus in the family Apidae .
Neonida grandis is a species of squat lobster in a monotypic genus in the family Munididae .
Archinemapogon is a somewhat disputed genus of the fungus moth family , Tineidae .
Acanthion is a subgenus of Old World porcupines in the genus Hystrix .
Scortechinia is a family of fungi in the Ascomycota , of the family Nitschkiaceae .
Astrometis is a genus of sea star in the Asteriidae family .
Cisticolas ( pronounced sis - TIC - olas ) are a genus of very small insectivorous birds formerly classified in the Old World warbler family Sylviidae , but now usually considered to be in the separate family Cisticolidae , along with other southern warbler genera .
Parnips is a genus of the family Figitidae , order Hymenoptera .
The Tsinpa salamander ( Liua tsinpaensis ) is a species of salamander in the Hynobiidae family .
The Vespa simillima , including the subspecies known as the Japanese hornet or Japanese yellow hornet ( Vespa simillima xanthoptera ) ( キイロスズメバチ ) , is a common hornet species in the Eastern Hemisphere .
The Indian burrowing frog ( Sphaerotheca breviceps ) is a species of frog found in South Asia ( Pakistan , Nepal , India , Sri Lanka , Myanmar , and probably Bangladesh ) .
Rudd 's lark ( Heteromirafra ruddi ) is a species of lark in the Alaudidae family .
Triviella is a genus of small sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Triviidae , the trivias .
The Murphy 's crow ( Euploea caespes ) is a species of nymphalid butterfly in the Danainae subfamily .
The Maduran leaf - nosed bat ( Hipposideros madurae ) is a species of bat in the family Hipposideridae endemic to Indonesia .
Hemitoma is a genus of slit limpets , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets and slit limpets .
The Antarctic minke whale or southern minke whale ( Balaenoptera bonaerensis ) is a species of minke whale within the suborder of baleen whales .
The Armenian cucumber , Cucumis melo var . flexuosus , is a type of long , slender fruit which tastes like a cucumber and looks somewhat like a cucumber inside .
Spix 's yellow - toothed cavy , Galea spixii , is a rodent , a cavy species from South America .
The Gangetic whiting , Sillaginopsis panijus ( also known as the flathead sillago ) , is a species of inshore marine and estuarine fish of the smelt - whiting family , Sillaginidae .
Aphylax lyciformis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Aphylax .
The South American tern ( Sterna hirundinacea ) is a species of tern found in coastal regions of southern South America , including the Falkland Islands , ranging north to Peru ( Pacific coast ) and Brazil ( Atlantic coast ) .
Turkanillus strinatii is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Turkanillus .
Rhizangiidae is a family of stony corals in the order Scleractinia .
Aurantilaria is a monotypic genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Fasciolariidae , the spindle snails , the tulip snails and their allies .
Halimium ( rockrose , false sun - rose , or halimium ) is a genus of 12 species of evergreen or semi - evergreen subshrubs in the family Cistaceae , closely related to Cistus .
Ctenitis is a genus of large ferns in the Dryopteridaceae .
Tetradium is a genus of nine species of trees in the family Rutaceae , occurring in temperate to tropical east Asia .
Zeacolpus is a genus of medium - sized sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Turritellidae , known as the turritellas or tower shells .
Williamsoceras is an endocerid that Rousseau Flower ( 1968 ) added to his Allotrioceratidae ( Flower 1955 ) on the basis of having a vertical partition within the siphuncle , known as a ventral process , with inter - connecting tubule - like structures along its margin where intercepted by endocones .
Lactifluus corrugis ( formerly Lactarius corrugis ) , commonly known as the corrugated - cap milky , is a species of fungus in the family Russulaceae .
Hose 's frog ( Odorrana hosii , often misspelled as O. hosei ) is a true frog species with a wide range in Southeast Asia .
Cyphostemma is a flowering plant genus belonging to the family Vitaceae .
Because of the similarity , Harpactognathus was assigned to the subfamily Scaphognathinae of the family Rhamphorhynchidae .
The West Sepik tree frog ( Litoria leucova ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family .
Daiopterix is an extinct genus of moth within the family Eolepidopterigidae , containing two species .
Dhori virus ( DHOV ) is a species of the genus Thogotovirus and a member of the family Orthomyxoviridae .
George Myers ( 1931 ) synonymized Pseudotropichthys with Cranoglanis , as well as described the family Cranoglanididae .
The Terre - de - Haut racer ( Alsophis sanctonum ) is a species of snake found in the Caribbean , on the Lesser Antilles .
Seicercus is a genus of Old World warbler formerly in the Sylviidae family but now placed in Phylloscopidae .
The Gulf wobbegong or banded wobbegong ( Orectolobus halei ) is a species of carpet shark in the family Orectolobidae , found in southern Australia between Southport , Queensland and Norwegian Bay , Western Australia .
The Lake Rukwa suckermouth ( Chiloglanis rukwaensis ) is a species of upside - down catfish native to Tanzania and Zambia where it is found in the Lake Rukwa drainage .
Lognkosauria is a group of giant long - necked sauropod dinosaurs within the clade Titanosauria .
Artemidiconus is a monospecific genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Conorbidae .
Sibyllidae is a family of mantises in the order Mantodea .
Mice in the genus Dendromus are commonly referred to as African climbing mice or tree mice , although these terms are often used to describe all members of the subfamily Dendromurinae .
Chiniquodontoidea is a clade of cynodonts that is defined as including all probainognathians closer to mammals than to Probainognathus , which is the more primitive form in Probainognathia .
Chondrosteus is a genus of extinct actinopterygian fish belonging to the family Chondrosteidae .
The Franklin 's gull ( Leucophaeus pipixcan ) is a small gull .
Thomas 's nectar bat ( Lonchophylla thomasi ) is a bat species from South and Central America .
Carduoideae is the thistle subfamily of the Asteraceae , or sunflower family , of flowering plants .
The Antioquia wren ( Thryophilus sernai ) is a passerine from the wren family ( Troglodytidae ) .
Zacotus matthewsii is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Zacotus .
Discopyge is a small genus of fish , the apron rays , in the family Narcinidae .
The Antarctic starry skate ( Amblyraja georgiana ) is a species of fish in the Rajidae family .
The Arroyo of Paradise brucie ( Brucepattersonius paradisus ) is a South American rodent species of the family Cricetidae .
The New Zealand sprat , Sprattus muelleri , is a herring - like , marine fish in the family Clupeidae found in the subtropical southwest Pacific Ocean endemic to New Zealand .
The Japanese robin ( Erithacus akahige , formerly Luscinia akahige ) or komadori is a songbird .
Electromethes is an extinct genus of beetle closely resembling members of the family Omethidae .
Cedrela is a genus of several species in the mahogany family , Meliaceae .
The Macrocephalini are a tribe of ambush bugs , which are a subfamily ( Phymatinae ) of the assassin bug family ( Reduviidae ) .
Pissarrachampsinae is one of two subfamilies of Baurusuchidae , the other being Baurusuchinae .
The Brazilian skate ( Rajella sadowskii ) is a species of fish in the Rajidae family .
Calamphoreus inflatus is the only species of the flowering plant genus Calamphoreus in the family Scrophulariaceae .
The Bornean barbet ( Megalaima eximia ) is a species of bird in the Ramphastidae family .
Brevipalpus is a genus of mites in the family Tenuipalpidae , the flat mites .
Monortha is a genus of moths belonging to the family Tortricidae .
The Middle American indigo snake ( Drymarchon melanurus ) , also known as the blacktail cribo , is a large , nonvenomous , colubrid snake species found in the southwestern United States , Mexico , Central America , and northern South America .
Craticulina is a genus of true flies in the family Sarcophagidae .
Iphiclides is a genus of butterflies of the family Papilionidae .
Harpoceras is an extinct genus of cephalopod belonging to the family Hildoceratidae .
Zephyra is a genus of cormous plants in the Tecophilaeaceae , first described as a genus in 1832 .
The Tupana scythebill ( Campylorhamphus procurvoides gyldenstolpei ) , is a new subspecies of Brazilian scythebill in the genus Campylorhamphus in the woodcreeper subfamily ( Dendrocolaptinae ) .
Trichuris , often referred to as whipworms ( which typically refers to T. trichiura only in medicine , and to any other species in veterinary medicine ) , is a genus of parasite worms from the roundworm family Trichuridae , which is a type of helminth .
Reynoldsiella parallela is a species of beetle in the family Mordellidae , the only species in the genus Reynoldsiella .
The Hudsonian whiteface ( Leucorrhinia hudsonica ) is a species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae .
Emerald - striped slim or green - striped slim ( Aciagrion pinheyi ) is a damselfly described by Samways in 2001 .
Balsam woolly adelgids ( Adelges piceae ) are small wingless insects that infest and kill firs , especially balsam fir and Fraser fir .
Alauda is a genus of larks with four species found across much of Europe , Asia and in the mountains of north Africa , and one species ( the Raso lark ) endemic to the islet of Raso in the Cape Verde Islands .
The Hawaiian blackhead triplefin ( Enneapterygius atriceps ) , also known as the Hawaiian triplefin in Hawaii , is a species of triplefin blenny in the genus Enneapterygius .
Medinella is a genus of tachinid flies in the family Tachinidae .
Illiosentidae is a family of parasitic worms from the order Echinorhynchida .
The Pacific spoon - nose eel ( Echiophis brunneus , also known commonly as the Fangjaw eel in Mexico ) is an eel in the family Ophichthidae ( worm / snake eels ) .
Larsenia is a genus of extremely small sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks or micromollusks in the family Vanikoridae .
Pepinia is a genus of the botanical family Bromeliaceae , subfamily Pitcairnioideae .
Leptoclanis is a genus of moths in the Sphingidae family , containing one species Leptoclanis pulchra , it is known from Brachystegia woodland from Angola and Zimbabwe to Zambia , the Democratic Republic of the Congo and southern Tanzania .
The Menzbier 's marmot ( Marmota menzbieri ) is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
The Réunion olive white - eye ( Zosterops olivaceus ) is a species of bird in the Zosteropidae family .
Stygoporus oregonensis is a species of beetle in the family Dytiscidae , the only species in the genus Stygoporus .
Cranwell 's horned frog ( Ceratophrys cranwelli ) , also called the Chacoan horned frog , is a terrestrial frog endemic to the dry Gran Chaco region of Argentina , Bolivia , Paraguay and Brazil .
The Santarem marmoset ( Mico humeralifera ) , also known as a black and white tassel - ear marmoset is a marmoset endemic to Brazil .
The Atlantic weasel shark , Paragaleus pectoralis , is a weasel shark of the family Hemigaleidae , found in the Eastern Atlantic Ocean , from the surface to a depth of 100 m. It can reach a length of 1.4 m.
Redlichia is a genus of redlichiid trilobite in the family Redlichiidae , with large to very large species ( up to 35 centimetres or 14 inches long ) .
The Phaneropterinae are a subfamily of bush crickets or katydids belonging to the family Tettigoniidae ; nearly 2060 species in 85 genera throughout the world are known .
The Sillem 's mountain finch or tawny - headed mountain finch ( Carpodacus sillemi ) is a species of rosefinch in the finch family .
Abyssochrysoidea is a superfamily of deep - water sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Caenogastropoda .
The Micronesian starling ( Aplonis opaca ) is a species of starling in the family Sturnidae .
Euoplocyon is an extinct genus of the Borophaginae and a small terrestrial canine which inhabited most of North America during the Hemingfordian stage of the Early Miocene subepoch through the Barstovian stage of the Middle Miocene subepoch living 20.6 - -13.6 Mya , existing for about 7 million years .
The Australian sprat , Sprattus novaehollandiae , is a sprat fish whose habitat ranges in the waters surrounding Australia including Tasmania .
The New Caledonian barn owl ( Tyto letocarti ) , also referred to as Letocart 's barn owl , is an extinct species of owl in the barn owl family .
Dalmanitoidea is a superfamily of trilobites in the order Phacopida , containing the three families Dalmanitidae , Diaphanometopidae and Prosopiscidae .
Imaia is a fungal genus in the family Morchellaceae found in Japan , and in the Appalachian Mountains of the USA .
Shyrodes dohertyi is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Shyrodes .
The Ecuadorian cacique ( Cacicus sclateri ) is a species of bird in the family Icteridae .
Horseradish ( Armoracia rusticana , syn . Cochlearia armoracia ) is a perennial plant of the Brassicaceae family ( which also includes mustard , wasabi , broccoli , and cabbage ) .
Cassidulinacea is included in the suborder Rotaliina by Loeblich and Tappan , e.g. 1964 and 1988 , since redefined as the Rotaliida and since reassigned to the Buliminida in Sen Gupta 2002 .
The Samoa sawtooth eel , Serrivomer samoensis , is a sawtooth eel of the genus Serrivomer , found in the southwest Pacific at depths between 500 and 2,000 m. Their length is up to 75 cm .
The Xenopsyllini form a flea tribe ( or depending on classifications a subfamily called Xenopsyllinae ) in the family Pulicidae .
Polyceroidea is a taxonomic superfamily of sea slugs , specifically dorid nudibranchs , marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Doridacea .
The Caribbean reef octopus ( Octopus briareus ) is a coral reef marine animal .
The black geese of the genus Branta are waterfowl belonging to the true geese and swans subfamily Anserinae .
Philydrum is a genus of tufted , herbaceous , aquatic macrophyte plants , one of three genera constituting the plant family Philydraceae .
Anshunsaurus is a genus of thalattosaurs within the family Askeptosauridae .
Glaphyroptera insignis is a fossil species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Glaphyroptera .
Owl 's spiny rat , Carterodon sulcidens , is a rodent species from South America in the family Echimyidae .
The Nemestrinoidea are a small , monophyletic superfamily of flies , whose relationship to the remaining Brachycera is uncertain ; they are sometimes grouped with the Tabanomorpha rather than the Asilomorpha .
The Northern rock sole , Lepidopsetta polyxystra , is a flatfish of the family Pleuronectidae .
Bruchidius is a genus of beetles in the bean weevil subfamily ( Bruchinae ) of the leaf beetle family , Chrysomelidae .
Psilothrix is a genus of soft - winged flower beetles belonging to the family Melyridae , subfamily Dasytinae .
Sloggett 's vlei rat or ice rat ( Otomys sloggetti or Myotomys sloggetti ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Platyphora is a genus of broad - shouldered leaf beetles belonging to the Chrysomelidae family .
Guaranobunus guaraniticus is a species of harvestmen in a monotypic genus in the family Sclerosomatidae .
Chilostoma is a genus of medium - sized , air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Helicidae , the true snails .
Xyloolaena is a genus within Sarcolaenaceae family .
Ipsa is a genus of small or medium - sized sea snails , cowries , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Brace 's emerald ( Chlorostilbon bracei ) is an extinct species of hummingbird which was endemic to the main island of the Bahamas , New Providence .
The Vanuatu flying fox or white flying fox ( Pteropus anetianus ) is a species of flying fox in the family Pteropodidae .
Tito Nordio was a sailor from Italy , who represented his country at the 1928 Summer Olympics in Amsterdam , Netherlands .
Velimir Valenta ( April 21 , 1929 -- November 27 , 2004 ) was a Yugoslav / Croatian rower who competed in the 1952 Summer Olympics .
Ludovic Valborge ( born 1889 , date of death unknown ) was an Olympic sport shooter who was part of the team won Haiti 's first ever Olympic medal , a bronze in team free rifle at the 1924 Summer Olympics .
Erik Hochstein ( born October 1 , 1968 in Düsseldorf , North - Rhine Westphalia ) is a former swimmer from Germany , who won the bronze medal in the 4×200 m freestyle relay at the 1988 Summer Olympics .
Birgit Heeb - Batliner ( born 14 October 1972 ) is a Liechtenstein former alpine skier who competed in the 1992 Winter Olympics , 1994 Winter Olympics , 1998 Winter Olympics , and 2002 Winter Olympics .
LaTanya Sheffield ( born October 11 , 1963 in El Cajon , California ) is a retired hurdler from the United States , who finished in eight place in the women 's 400 metres hurdles final at the 1988 Summer Olympics ( Seoul , South Korea ) .
Gábor Balogh ( born August 5 , 1976 in Budapest , Hungary ) is a former Hungarian modern pentathlete who won silver medal at the 2000 Summer Olympics in Sydney , Australia .
Damir Dugonjič ( born 21 February 1988 ) is a Slovenian swimmer who competed for his native country at the 2008 Summer Olympics .
Mariette Rix ( born 8 April 1981 ) is a South African field hockey player who competed in the 2008 Summer Olympics and 2012 Summer Olympics .
Yumiko Ishiguro ( born 31 October 1983 ) is a Japanese synchronized swimmer who competed in the 2008 Summer Olympics .
Shawn Dulohery ( born May 4 , 1965 in Kansas City , Missouri ) is an American sport shooter who represented the United States at the 2004 Summer Olympics .
Uschi Keszler qualified to represent the Unified Team of Germany at the 1964 Winter Olympics in Innsbruck and finished 24th .
Aleksei Barkalov ( Ukrainian : Олексій Степанович Баркалов , Russian : Алексей Степанович Баркалов ; 18 February 1946 -- 9 September 2004 ) was a Ukrainian water polo player who competed in the 1968 , 1972 , 1976 and 1980 Summer Olympics and won two gold and one silver medals for the Soviet Union team .
Uwe Steingross ( born 19 April 1951 ) is a German sailor who competed in the 1976 Summer Olympics and 1980 Summer Olympics .
Vasyl Kovalchuk ( born April 18 , 1973 ) is a Ukrainian sports - shooter who won a gold medal in Shooting at the 2012 Summer Paralympics in the Mixed 10 metre air rifle prone SH2 .
Anthony Douglas ( born 22 November 1985 ) is a former British short track speed skater who competed at the 2010 Winter Olympics .
Ronald Serugo ( born 5 September 1984 ) is an Ugandan amateur boxer who qualified for the 2008 Summer Olympics in the junior flyweight division .
Giulio Cacciandra ( July 15 , 1884 -- January 28 , 1970 ) was an Italian horse rider who competed in the 1920 Summer Olympics .
Chan Yun To ( Chinese : 陳潤韜 ; Jyutping : can4 jeon6 tou1 ; born 21 February 1966 ) is a bodybuilder from Hong Kong who won a gold medal at the 2006 Asian Games in the men 's -75 kg class .
Ulrike Tauber ( born 16 June 1958 ) is a retired medley and butterfly swimmer from East Germany , who won the gold medal in the women 's 400 m individual medley at the 1976 Summer Olympics in Montreal , Canada .
Karl Schwegler ( born September 17 , 1902 , date of death missing ) was a Swiss rower who competed in the 1928 Summer Olympics .
Christl Haas ( 19 September 1943 -- 8 July 2001 ) was an Austrian alpine skiing champion at the 1964 Winter Olympics .
Mirko Sandić ( Serbian Cyrillic : Мирко Сандић ; May 9 , 1942 in Belgrade -- December 24 , 2006 ) was a Serbian water polo player who led the Yugoslav team to gold at the 1968 Summer Olympics and silver at the 1964 Summer Olympics .
Sándor Cséfai ( July 13 , 1904 in Budapest -- September 2 , 1984 in Budapest ) was a Hungarian field handball player who competed in the 1936 Summer Olympics .
Valdemaras Venckaitis ( born September 4 , 1983 in Vilnius ) is a Greco - Roman wrestler from Lithuania , who competed for the men 's 74 kg ( middleweight division ) at the 2008 Summer Olympics in Beijing .
In the Women 's 400 m individual medley at the 2010 Asian Games , Ye Shiwen , aged 14 , swam 4:33.79 .
Mehrullah Lassi ( born November 24 , 1979 , Karachi , Sindh ) is a former Pakistani amateur boxer best known to win a gold medal at the 2002 Asian Games .
Sirop Arslanian ( born 27 November 1966 ) is a former Lebanese racing cyclist who competed at the 1984 Summer Olympics in the individual road race .
Hamdy Awad El Safi ( Arabic : حمدي عوض الصافي‎ ) ( born April 14 , 1972 ) is an Egyptian indoor volleyball player , who played with the Egypt national team at the 2008 Summer Olympics .
Eva - Maria ten Elsen ( born 14 September 1937 ) is a German former swimmer who won a bronze medal in the 200 m breaststroke event at the 1956 Summer Olympics .
Hans Matthiae ( born December 22 , 1884 - died ? ) was a Germany rower who competed in the 1912 Summer Olympics .
Dalia Henry ( born 14 June 1965 ) is a Cuban former basketball player who competed in the 1992 Summer Olympics , in the 1996 Summer Olympics , and in the 2000 Summer Olympics .
Ulderico Sergo ( Rijeka , 4 July 1913 -- Cleveland , 20 February 1967 ) was a bantamweight professional boxer from Italy , who won the gold medal at the 1936 Summer Olympics in Berlin .
Edsel Martis ( born December 22 , 1961 ) is a Dutch baseball player who represented the Netherlands at the 1996 Summer Olympics .
Kiyomi Takahashi ( born 3 March 1966 ) is a Japanese former swimmer who competed in the 1984 Summer Olympics and in the 1988 Summer Olympics .
Kate Hooper ( born 26 February 1978 in Auckland , New Zealand ) is an Australian water polo player from the gold medal squad of the 2000 Summer Olympics .
Ragnar Olsen ( 13 March 1914 -- 9 July 1990 ) was a Norwegian racewalker who competed in the 1952 Summer Olympics .
Željko Nimš ( born 22 April 1950 ) is a Croatian handball player who competed in the 1976 Summer Olympics for Yugoslavia .
Gian Bazzi ( 1 April 1931 -- 12 January 2016 ) was a Swiss professional ice hockey player who competed for the Swiss national team at the 1952 Winter Olympics .
Nancy Merki ( June 1 , 1926 -- October 7 , 2014 ) , also known by her married names Lees , Cory and Boland , was an American competition swimmer who represented the United States at the 1948 Summer Olympics in London .
Franz Pitschmann ( born 16 December 1954 in Hall in Tirol ) is an Austrian former wrestler who competed in the 1976 Summer Olympics , in the 1980 Summer Olympics , in the 1984 Summer Olympics , and in the 1988 Summer Olympics .

Giacomo Panizza ( 27 March 1804 -- 1 May 1860 ) was a conductor at La Scala , Milan for 13 years , during which time , he composed two operas and thirteen ballets .
Rolf Kauka ( 9 April 1917 in Markranstädt , Saxony -- 13 September 2000 in Thomasville , Georgia ) was a comic artist , most famous for the series Fix and Foxi .

Trinity Loren ( born Joyce Evelyn McPherson ; August 21 , 1964 in La Jolla , California -- October 25 , 1998 ) was a pornographic film actor , model , and stripper .
Alice Gurschner ( née Pollak , 8 October 1869 , Vienna -- 26 March 1944 , Vienna ) was an Austrian writer .
Frans Anneessens ( in Dutch ) or in French François Anneessens ( Brussels , 25 February 1660 -- Brussels , 19 September 1719 ) was dean of a Brussels guild .
Lazarus Spengler ( March 13 , 1479 in Nuremberg -- September 7 , 1534 in Nuremberg ) was a prominent supporter of Martin Luther and leader of the Protestant Reformation in Nuremberg , as well as a famous hymnwriter .
Antoniotto di Montaldo ( 1368 - 25 July 1398 ) was the doge of Genoa on two occasions between 1392 and 1394 .
Russell Lee Smith ( February 6 , 1947 -- May 24 , 1975 ) was an American spree killer who killed two people and wounded nine others in Dayton , Ohio , United States on May 24 , 1975 .
Susan Paul ( 1809 - -1841 ) was an African - American abolitionist from Boston , Massachusetts .
Hanns In der Gand was the pen name of Ladislaus Krupski ( born 25 February 1882 in La Vernaz , France ( formerly Savoy ) ; died 24 May 1947 in Zumikon , canton of Zurich ) was a Swiss folklorist and collector of traditional and military songs .
Samuel Earnshaw ( 1 February 1805 , Sheffield , Yorkshire -- 6 December 1888 , Sheffield , Yorkshire ) was an English clergyman and mathematician , noted for his contributions to theoretical physics , especially `` Earnshaw 's Theorem '' .
Maung Khin was born to Kya Hnaing and Po Kyaw in Rangoon ( Yangon ) in 1872 , twenty years after the British had captured Lower Burma .
José de Bustamante y Guerra ( Corvera de Toranzo , Cantabria 1 April 1759 -- Madrid 10 March 1825 ) , sometimes referred to simply as Bustamante , was a Spanish naval officer , explorer , and politician .
Pedro Pablo Figueroa Luna ( born December 25 , 1857 in Copiapó , Chile ; died 1906 in Santiago ) was a Chilean writer and researcher .
Theodoret of Cyrus or Cyrrhus ( Greek : Θεοδώρητος Κύρρου ; c. AD 393 -- c. 458/466 ) was an influential theologian of the School of Antioch , biblical commentator , and Christian bishop of Cyrrhus ( 423 - -457 ) .
Albert M. Bender ( 1866 - -1941 ) was a leading patron of the arts in San Francisco in the 1920s and 1930s , who played a key role in the early career of Ansel Adams and was one of Diego Rivera 's first American patrons .
Nicolas René Berryer , comte de La Ferrière ( 4 March 1703 , Paris -- 15 August 1762 , Versailles ) was a French magistrate and politician .
Leung Sheung ( Chinese : 梁相 ; 1918 - 1978 ) was a Chinese martial artist who studied Wing Chun Kung Fu who is known as the senior - most student of Yip Man ( 葉問 ) in Hong Kong .
Arthur Lennox Ochse ( 11 October 1899 in Graaff - Reinet , Cape Province -- 5 May 1949 in Middelburg , Cape Province ) was a South African cricketer who played in three Tests in 1927 - -28 and 1929 .
Eduard Van De Walle ( 12 July 1932 -- 6 February 2016 ) , known by his stage name Eddy Wally , was a Belgian singer from Zelzate , East Flanders , and the once self - proclaimed `` Voice of Europe '' .
René Carmille ( born Trémolat , Dordogne , 1886 ; died Dachau , Bavaria , January 25 , 1945 ) was a punched card computer expert and comptroller general of the French Army in the early 20th century .
Simón Bajour also Szymsia Bajour ( born Szymon Bachórz ) ( April 4 , 1928 , Nasierowo Górne or Nasielsk , Poland - February 8 , 2005 , Buenos Aires , Argentina ) was a Jewish Polish - Argentine violinist who was known for both his popular and classical repertoires .
Ippolita Trivulzio ( 1600 -- 20 June 1638 ) was the wife of Honoré II of Monaco and was the first Monegasque consort to bear the title of Princess .
Cornelis Kiliaan ( 1528 , Duffel -- 1607 , Antwerp ) , was a 16th - century lexicographer , linguist , translator and poet of the Southern Netherlands .

Cosme Damián de Churruca y Elorza ( Mutriku , 27 September 1761 -- Battle of Trafalgar , 21 October 1805 ) was a Basque Spanish noble , an Admiral of the Royal Spanish Armada , scientist and Mayor of Mutriku , who died at the Battle of Trafalgar while commanding the ship of the line San Juan Nepomuceno .
Hans Hartmann - MacLean ( born Hans Rudolf Hartmann ; 20 May 1862 in Dresden -- 28 December 1946 in Dresden ) was a German sculptor .
Paul Petiet ( 24 July 1770 in Châtillon - sur - Seine -- 20 December 1849 in Limoux ) was a French adjutant - general during the Napoleonic Wars .
Steven Blankaart ( 24 October 1650 , Middelburg -- 23 February 1704 , Amsterdam ) , was a Dutch physician , Iatrochemist , and entomologist , who worked on the same field as Jan Swammerdam .
Cangrande II della Scala ( 8 June 1332 -- 14 December 1359 ) was Lord of Verona from 1351 until his death .
František Sušil ( 14 June 1804 in Rousínov , Moravia - 31 May 1868 in Bystřice pod Hostýnem ) was a Moravian Roman Catholic priest most noted for his published collection of traditional Moravian folk music , Moravské národní písně , which contained 2091 songs and 2361 texts .
Job Charnock ( c. 1630 - -1692 ) was an employee and an administrator of the English East India Company , and traditionally regarded as the founder of the city of Calcutta , now Kolkata .
William Gibson Sloan ( 4 September 1838 in Dalry , North Ayrshire , Scotland -- 4 September 1914 in Tórshavn , Faroe Islands ) , was a Plymouth Brethren evangelist to the Faroe Islands and Shetland .
Cansignorio della Scala ( 5 March 1340 -- 19 October 1375 ) was Lord of Verona from 1359 until 1375 , initially together with his brother Paolo Alboino .
Walter Masing ( born 22 June 1915 in Petrograd -- died 29 March 2004 in Erbach ) was a German physicist and honorary president of the German Association for Quality .
Sibylle of Bavaria ( 16 June 1489 -- 18 April 1519 in Heidelberg ) was a member of the House of Wittelsbach was a princess of Bavaria - Munich and by marriage Electress Palatine .
Alceu Amoroso Lima ( Petrópolis , December 11 , 1893 -- Rio de Janeiro , August 14 , 1983 ) was a writer , journalist , activist from Brazil and founder of the Brazilian Christian Democracy .
Leonhard Beck ( c. 1480 -- 1542 ) was a painter and designer of woodcuts in Augsburg , Germany .
Lon Nol fled from Cambodia to Indonesia and then to the United States ; first settling in Hawaii and in 1979 in Fullerton , California .

Fadil Paçrami ( born Shkodër , May 25 , 1922 -- died Tirana , January 16 , 2008 ) was an Albanian politician , writer and playwright .
Robert Pötzelberger ( 9 June 1856 , Vienna -- 2 August 1930 , Reichenau , Baden - Württemberg ) was an Austrian painter , sculptor and lithographer .
Johann Nobis ( born 16 April 1899 , St. Georgen bei Salzburg , Austria ; died 6 January 1940 , Plötzensee Prison , Berlin , Germany ) was an Austrian conscientious objector .
Jules - Léopold Renouard ( 27 January 1833 -- 7 March 1910 ) was a stock broker , financier and banker from Paris .
Jakub Ignacy Łaszczyński ( 24 July 1791 - -18 September 1865 ) was a Polish regional administrator who , between 1831 and 1837 , held the post of President of Warsaw .
Edward Fitzsimmons Dunne ( October 12 , 1853 -- May 24 , 1937 ) was an American politician who was the 24th Governor of Illinois from 1913 to 1917 and previously served as the 38th mayor of Chicago from April 5 , 1905 to 1907 .
Dan Dodd is a former Democratic member of the Ohio House of Representatives who represented the 91st District from 2007 to 2010 .
Rajendrasinh Ghanshyamsinh Rana ( born 22 May 1956 ) was a member of the Lok Sabha of India from 1996 to 2014 .
Romanzo E. Davis ( April 8 , 1831 - October 31 , 1908 ) was a farmer and merchant from Middleton , Wisconsin who served as a member of the Wisconsin State Senate from Dane County .
Simon - Pierre Saint - Hillien ( July 6 , 1951 -- July 22 , 2015 ) was a Roman Catholic bishop .
Orso Ipato ( Latin Ursus ) was the third traditional Doge of Venice ( 726 - -737 ) and the first historically known .
Bonaventure Giffard ( 1642 - -1734 ) was a Roman Catholic bishop who served as the Vicar Apostolic of the Midland District of England from 1687 to 1703 and Vicar Apostolic of the London District of England from 1703 to 1734 .
Nestor Assogba ( born February 21 , 1929 in Abomey ) is a retired Beninese Roman Catholic archbishop .
Liam Cosgrave ( born 13 April 1920 ) is a former Irish Fine Gael politician who served as Taoiseach ( 1973 - -77 ) and as Leader of Fine Gael ( 1965 - -77 ) .
Joseph McIlvaine ( October 2 , 1769 -- August 19 , 1826 ) was a United States Senator from New Jersey from 1823 until his death .
Eusebio Ayala ( August 14 , 1875 -- June 4 , 1942 ) was President of Paraguay from 7 November 1921 to 12 April 1923 and again from 15 August 1932 to 17 February 1936 .
Teophilus Seremi ( also spelled Szeremi ; died July 1697 ) was an Orthodox bishop and metropolitan of Bălgrad ( of Transylvania ) between 1692 and 1697 .
Mohammed Abdul Khalek Hassouna ( Arabic : محمد عبد الخالق حسونة‎ ) ( October 28 , 1898 -- January 20 , 1992 ) was an Egyptian diplomat who served as the second Secretary - General of the Arab League from 1952 to 1972 .
Rémi Gaulin ( 30 June 1787 -- 8 May 1857 ) was a Roman Catholic priest and bishop who spent time in the service of Bishop Joseph - Octave Plessis .
Maryon Pittman Allen ( born November 30 , 1925 ) is an American journalist who served as United States Senator from Alabama for five months in 1978 , after her husband , Senator James B. Allen , died in office .
Littleton Waller Tazewell ( December 17 , 1774 -- May 6 , 1860 ) was a U.S. Representative , U.S. Senator from and the 26th Governor of Virginia .
Christopher Del Sesto ( March 10 , 1907 -- December 23 , 1973 ) was a United States politician and a member of the Republican Party , who served as 64th Governor of Rhode Island .
Bernardo Navagero ( Venice 1507- Verona 1565 ) was a Venetian ambassador and a cardinal of the Roman Catholic Church .
Lieutenant General Sir Henry Pottinger , 1st Baronet , GCB , PC ( Chinese : 砵甸乍 ; 3 October 1789 -- 18 March 1856 ) , was an Anglo - Irish soldier and colonial administrator who became the first Governor of Hong Kong .
Lucius Calpurnius Piso ( also known to contemporaries as Lucius Calpurnius Piso the Augur ) ( died AD 24 ) was a Roman senator who was appointed Roman consul in 1 BC , and an augur .
Fernando de Toledo Oropesa ( 1520 - -1590 ) was a Spanish Roman Catholic priest who was made a cardinal but who refused the honor .
Basil of Amasea ( Basileus or Basilius ) was a fourth - century Christian bishop and martyr .
Jaime de Casanova ( died 1504 ) ( called Cardinal Casanova ) was a Spanish Roman Catholic cardinal .
Pierre de Langle ( 6 March 1643 , Evreux- 12 April 1724 , Boulogne - Sur - Mer ) was a French bishop and Jansenist theologian .
Edward Henry Durell ( July 14 , 1810 -- March 29 , 1887 ) was the 25th mayor of New Orleans , and later a United States federal judge .
Louis Payette ( 25 December 1854 -- 19 March 1932 ) was a Canadian construction contractor and politician , the Mayor of Montreal , Quebec between 1908 and 1910 .
Peter of Aquila , O.F.M. , ( Scotellus ) ( d. 1361 ) was an Italian Friar Minor , theologian and bishop .
Pierre Bürcher ( born on December 20 , 1945 in Fiesch , Switzerland ) is a Swiss prelate of the Roman Catholic Church , he was bishop of Diocese of Reykjavík , Iceland .
Devji M Patel is a member of the Lok Sabha , which is the lower house of parliament of India .
William Meade Fishback ( November 5 , 1831 -- February 9 , 1903 ) was the 17th Governor of Arkansas and U.S. Senator - Elect for Arkansas .
Isaac Coleman Lindsey , known as Coleman Lindsey ( October 2 , 1892 -- November 15 , 1968 ) , was a Democratic member of the Louisiana State Senate , a district judge , and from 1939 to 1940 , the lieutenant governor under Governor Earl Kemp Long .
Alessandro Cesarini ( died February 13 , 1542 ) , bishop of Pistoia , was an Italian cardinal of the Roman Catholic Church .
Frank Pace , Jr. ( July 5 , 1912 -- January 8 , 1988 ) was the 3rd United States Secretary of the Army and a business executive .
General Sir Reginald Alexander Dallas Brooks GCMG KCB KCVO DSO KStJ ( 22 August 1896 -- 22 March 1966 ) was a British military commander who went on to become the 19th and longest - serving Governor of Victoria , Australia .
Gaius Flaminius Nepos was a politician and consul of the Roman Republic in the 3rd century BC . He was the greatest popular leader to challenge the authority of the Senate prior to the Gracchi a century later .
DeWitt Clinton ( March 2 , 1769 -- February 11 , 1828 ) was an American politician and naturalist who served as a United States Senator and was the sixth Governor of New York .
Farzad Nazem ( Persian : فرزاد ناظم‎ ) ( born 1961 ) , also known as Zod Nazem , was Yahoo ! 's chief technology officer and one of its longest - serving executives .
William Livingston ( November 30 , 1723 -- July 25 , 1790 ) served as the Governor of New Jersey ( 1776 - -1790 ) during the American Revolutionary War and was a signer of the United States Constitution .
Pablo Abeita ( 1871 - -1940 ) was the governor of Isleta Pueblo in New Mexico , United States , during the decades that Father Anton Docher , known as `` The Padre of Isleta , '' served there .
Roy Clyde Clark ( July 24 , 1920 - May 27 , 2014 ) is a retired American bishop of the United Methodist Church , elected in 1980 .
Varyon Cullie Shannon , known as V. C. Shannon ( May 2 , 1910 - June 1 , 1989 ) , was a Democratic member of the Louisiana House of Representatives from Shreveport in Caddo Parish in northwestern Louisiana .
John Kemp ( c. 1380 -- 22 March 1454 ) was a medieval English cardinal , Archbishop of Canterbury , and Lord Chancellor of England .
John Alan Berthelot , known as Johnny Berthelot ( born November 1951 ) , is a Republican member of the Louisiana House of Representatives from District 88 , based in his hometown of Gonzales in eastern Ascension Parish near Baton Rouge , Louisiana .
José de la Cruz Porfirio Díaz Mori ( Spanish pronunciation : ( porˈfiɾjo ði.as ) ; 15 September 1830 -- 2 July 1915 ) was a Mexican soldier and politician , who served seven terms as President of Mexico ; a total of three and a half decades from 1876 to 1911 .
Emmanuel Marie Louis de Noailles , marquis de Noailles ( 1743 - -1822 ) was a French diplomat and ambassador to Hamburg from 1768 to 1770 , to Amsterdam from 1770 to 1776 , to London 1776 - -1783 , and to Vienna 1783 - -1792 .
Abuzed Omar Dorda ( Arabic : أبو زيد عمر دوردة‎ ) ( born 4 April 1944 ) was General Secretary of the People 's Committee ( Prime Minister ) of Libya from 7 October 1990 to 29 January 1994 , and as Libya 's Permanent Representative to the United Nations from 1997 to 2003 .
Nebka is the birth name of an Ancient Egyptian king ( pharaoh ) who ruled during the 3rd dynasty of the Old Kingdom .
James Anthony Goolsby , known as Tony Goolsby ( born November 9 , 1933 ) , is a businessman in Dallas , Texas , who was from 1993 to 2009 a Republican member of the Texas House of Representatives from District 102 in northeastern Dallas County .
Giovanni Francesco Ugolini was a Captain Regent of San Marino together with Andrea Zafferani for the semester from 1 October 2010 to 1 April 2011 .
Thomas Joseph Byrnes ( 11 November 1860 -- 27 September 1898 ) was Premier of Queensland from April 1898 until his death in October of the same year , having previously served in several ministerial positions in his parliamentary career .
Dee Dee Myers ( born Margaret Jane Myers , September 1 , 1961 ) , a political analyst , was the White House Press Secretary during the first two years of the Clinton administration , from January 1993 to December 1994 .
Frederick Holbrook ( February 15 , 1813 -- April 28 , 1909 ) was an agriculturist , politician , and the 27th Governor of Vermont .
Ahmet Davutoğlu ( Turkish pronunciation : ( ahˈmet daˈvutoːɫu ) ; born 26 February 1959 ) is a Turkish academic , politician and former diplomat who has been the Prime Minister of Turkey since 28 August 2014 and the leader of the Justice and Development Party ( AKP ) since 27 August 2014 .

Helen Björk ( born 9 July 1965 , as Helen Johansson ) is a Swedish former association football forward who won 88 caps and scored 23 goals for the Sweden women 's national football team .
John Ryan Murphy ( born May 13 , 1991 ) , also known as J. R. Murphy is an American professional baseball catcher for the Minnesota Twins of Major League Baseball ( MLB ) .
Brienne of Tarth is a fictional character in George R. R. Martin 's A Song of Ice and Fire series of fantasy novels .
Chris Keller is a fictional character on the HBO series Oz , portrayed by Christopher Meloni from 1998 to 2003 .
Lemuel Gulliver ( /ˈɡʌlɪvər/ ) is the fictional protagonist and narrator of Gulliver 's Travels , a novel written by Jonathan Swift , first published in 1726 .
Severus Snape is a fictional character in J. K. Rowling 's Harry Potter series .
The Graboid is a fictional species of sandworm that acts as the primary antagonist of the Tremors franchise .
The Girls of Old Town are fictional characters in Frank Miller 's Sin City .
The Firecons are a group of three fictional Decepticons in the Transformers toyline .
Boxey is a fictional character from the original Battlestar Galactica television series portrayed by Noah Hathaway .
Johnny Cage is a fictional character from the Mortal Kombat fighting game franchise .
The End of Eden is a 1986 environmental documentary in which the South African filmmaker Rick Lomba ( 1950 - -1994 ) showed the rapid degradation of Africa 's ecosystems .
Up in the Wind ( Chinese : 等风来 ) is a 2013 Chinese romance - comedy film directed by Teng Huatao and starring Ni Ni and Jing Boran .

The Sea Change is a 1998 British - Spanish comedy film directed by Michael Bray and starring Maryam d'Abo , Sean Chapman and Ray Winstone .

Days of Dreams ( Serbian : Дани од снова , translit . Dani od snova ) is a 1980 Yugoslav drama film directed by Vlatko Gilic .

The Journal of Applied Electrochemistry is a peer - reviewed scientific journal published by Springer Science+Business Media covering electrochemistry , focusing on technologically oriented aspects .
Why Did n't They Ask Evans ? is a work of detective fiction by Agatha Christie , first published in the United Kingdom by the Collins Crime Club in September 1934 and in the United States by Dodd , Mead and Company in 1935 under the title of The Boomerang Clue .

Science Software Quarterly was founded in 1984 by executive editor Diana Gabaldon , who at the time was an assistant professor in the Center for Environmental Studies at Arizona State University .
Trading Futures is a BBC Books original novel written by Lance Parkin and based on the long - running British science fiction television series Doctor Who .

The 1981 Women 's Hockey World Cup , held in Buenos Aires , Argentina , was the fourth edition of the Women 's Hockey World Cup field hockey tournament .

The Northern Sharks is a former Fijian rugby union team that had a franchise area coverering Vanua Levu , Taveuni , Ovalau , and Island Zone .
The Volvo Cross Country Challenge was an unofficial women 's professional golf event on the Ladies European Tour .
The International Gymnastics Hall of Fame , located in Oklahoma City , USA , is a hall of fame dedicated to honoring the achievements and contributions of the world 's greatest competitors , coaches and authorities in artistic gymnastics .

The Scotland Sevens was a rugby union sevens tournament that was part of the Sevens World Series .

Smith 's Ballpark ( formerly known as Franklin Quest Field , later Franklin Covey Field , and most recently Spring Mobile Ballpark ) is a baseball park in Salt Lake City , Utah .

PlunderChess is a chess variant in which the capturing piece is allowed to temporarily take the moving abilities of the piece taken .

Ezio Bertuzzo ( 23 July 1952 -- 23 February 2014 ) was an Italian association football coach and player , whose career as a striker spanned from the mid-1960s until 1987 .

The Dapper Dan Open was a professional golf tournament on the PGA Tour that was played intermittently in the 1930s and 1940s .

Ron Thomas ( born November 19 , 1950 in Louisville , Kentucky ) played basketball at both the college and professional level in the United States .

Buckleya is a genus of hemiparasitic shrubs in the sandalwood family .

Alternaria alternata is a fungus which has been recorded causing leaf spot and other diseases on over 380 host species of plant .
Androlaelaps fahrenholzi is a species of mite in the genus Androlaelaps of the family Laelapidae .
Senecio integerrimus is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names lambstongue ragwort and tall western groundsel .
Rubus tardatusis a rare North American species of flowering plant in the rose family .
Melibe viridis is a species of sea slug , a nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Tethydidae .
Erigeron lanatus is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name woolly fleabane .
Ornithomimoides ( `` bird mimic - like '' ) is a dubious genus of small theropod dinosaur , from the Late Cretaceous period ( Maastrichtian stage , sometime between 70 - -66 mya ) of India .
Nothobranchius kirki , the redfin notho , is a species of African rivuline endemic to Malawi where it occurs in the drainages of Lake Malawi and Lake Chilwa .
The only species is Ikakogi tayrona , or the Magdalena giant glass frog .
Vriesea amethystina is a species of tropical epiphyte of the genus Vriesea .

Acanthophoenix crinita is a species of palm which is endemic to Réunion .
The species name Venerupis decussata ( Linnaeus , 1758 ) is considered valid by the World Register of Marine Species ( WoRMS ) with a range limited to the north east Atlantic Ocean .
Lasiancistrus tentaculatus is a species of armored catfish found in the Orinoco River basin of Colombia and Venezuela .
Stictoleptura deyrollei is a species of beetle in the Cerambycidae family that is endemic to Turkey and North Iran .
The Icaleptidae are a small family of neotropical harvestmen within the suborder Laniatores .
Emoia atrocostata , commonly known as the mangrove skink , is a species of lizard in the family Scincidae .
Asteracmea suteri is a species of sea snail or true limpet , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Lottiidae .
Bifidobacterium dentium is a species of bacteria in the genus Bifidobacterium , branched anaerobic bacteria from the Bifidobacteriaceae family .
Felimida socorroensis is a species of colourful sea slug , a dorid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Chromodorididae
Euphorbia myrsinites , the myrtle spurge , blue spurge , or broad - leaved glaucous - spurge , is a succulent species of the spurge ( family Euphorbiaceae ) .
Orientopsaltria is a genus of cicadas from Southeast Asia .
Ziziphus parryi is a species of flowering plant in the buckthorn family known by the common name Parry 's jujube .
Epitonium minora is a species of small predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Epitoniidae , the wentletraps .
Macquarie perch are a relatively placid native fish species with the bulk of their diet consisting of aquatic invertebrates such as caddisfly , stonefly and mayfly species , with a small quantity of terrestrial insects taken as well .
Schoenoplectus americanus ( syn . Scirpus americanus ) is a species of flowering plant in the sedge family known by the common names chairmaker 's bulrush and Olney 's three - square bulrush .
Colostethus fraterdanieli ( common name : Santa Rita rocket frog ) is a species of frog in the Dendrobatidae family .
Oiceoptoma is a genus of carrion beetles .
Atriplex amnicola , commonly known as river saltbush or swamp saltbush , is a species of shrub in the Amaranthaceae family .
Acer chaneyi is an extinct maple species in the family Sapindaceae described from a number of fossil leaves and samaras .
Polistes gallicus ( also historically referred to as Polistes foederatus ) is a fairly common species of paper wasp found in various parts of Europe , excluding England , Denmark , and Scandinavia , from warmer climates to cooler regions north of the Alps .
Chiloglanis lukugae is a species of upside - down catfish endemic to the Democratic Republic of the Congo where it is found in the Luvua River drainage .
Raphia australis , the giant palm or rafia , is a species of raffia palm in the Arecaceae family .
Labrisomus guppyi , the Mimic blenny , is a species of labrisomid blenny native to the western Atlantic Ocean and the Caribbean Sea from south Florida to Fernando de Noronha where it inhabits such areas as reefs , near shore areas with rock or rubble covered in algae and beds of seagrass .
Absconditella amabilis is a species of fungi within the Stictidaceae family , first found in inland rainforests of British Columbia .
Eriogonum vimineum is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name wickerstem buckwheat .
Arctosa stigmosa is a wolf spider species found in Europe ( France , Norway to Ukraine ) .
Drummond 's onion ( Allium drummondii ) , also known as Wild garlic and the Prairie onion , is a North American species of onion native to the southern Great Plains of North America .
Partulina variabilis ( Lanai tree snail ) is a species of tropical air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Achatinellidae .
Creobroter nebulosus is a species of praying mantis in the genus Creobroter in the order Mantodea .
Zodarion ludibundum is a spider species found in Corsica , Sicily and Algeria .
Simocetus ( from simus , `` pug - nosed '' , and cetus , `` whale '' ) is an extinct genus of toothed whale that lived during the Oligocene period , approximately 32 million years ago , making it the oldest named toothed whale , although older unnamed toothed whales exist .
The fungal order Agaricales , also known as gilled mushrooms ( for their distinctive gills ) or euagarics , contains some of the most familiar types of mushrooms .
Hypancistrocerus is a rather small neotropical genus of potter wasps which is very close to the Genus Stenodynerus .
The family Proteidae is a group of aquatic salamanders found today in the Balkan Peninsula and North America .
Yanornithiformes is an order of ornithuromorph birds from the early Cretaceous Period of China .
Chthonius minotaurus is a species of pseudoscorpion in the Chthoniusidae family that is endemic to Crete .
Channa burmanica is an endemic species of snakehead from northern Burma .
Pachycondyla petrosa is an extinct species of ants in the formicid subfamily Ponerinae described from a fossil found in Europe .
Epidendrium billeeanum , commonly known as the Yellow sea snail or the Golden wentletrap , is a species of small predator and ectoparasite sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Epitoniidae , the wentletraps .
Diadophis punctatus edwardsii , commonly known as the Northern ringneck snake , is a subspecies of Diadophis punctatus .
Allium callimischon is a plant species native to southwestern Turkey and to southern Greece ( including Peloponnese and the Island of Crete ) .
Hyphalosaurus ( meaning `` submerged lizard '' ) is a genus of freshwater aquatic reptiles which represent a major part of the Jehol Biota .
Banksia kingii is an extinct species of tree or shrub in the plant genus Banksia .
Qatranilestes is an extinct genus of afrosoricid which existed in Fayum , Egypt during the earliest Oligocene period ( Rupelian age ) .
The Candrena Eighty - eight or Number Eighty ( Diaethria candrena ) is a species of butterfly of the Nymphalidae family .
Pupinella rufa is a species of land snail with an operculum , a terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the superfamily Cyclophoroidea ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Hedyscepe canterburyana , the big mountain palm or umbrella palm , is the sole species in the genus Hedyscepe of the Arecaceae family .
Polybia rejecta is a species of social wasp found in the Neotropics region of the world .
Veronica formosa is a flowering plant species of the family Plantaginaceae , endemic to Tasmania in Australia .
Orthotylus junipericola is a species of bug from the Miridae family that can be found on Azores , and in countries like Bulgaria , France , Greece , Spain , and Dodecanese Islands .
Otopharynx tetrastigma is a species of cichlid native to Lake Malawi , Lake Malombe and the upper reaches of the Shire River .
Caulokaempferia is a group of plants in the ginger family described as a genus in 1964 .
Festuca gautieri , commonly known as spiky fescue or bearskin fescue , is a species of flowering plant in the grass family , Poaceae , native to the Pyrenees .
Rhinella chavin is a species of toad from family Bufonidae that is endemic to Peru .
Streptomyces glauciniger is a mesophilic bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil in south China .
Abantiades latipennis , known as the Pindi moth , is a species of moth in the Hepialidae family .
Diloma is a genus of medium - sized sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Chrysothamnus stylosus called pillar false gumweed , or resinbush , is a species of flowering plants in the aster tribe within the sunflower family .
Codonanthe is a New World genus , consists of a dozen or more species of evergreen epiphytic compact creeping vines with rooting along their stems , and scandent herbs or subshrubs with woody , upright stems from Brazil , Guiana , Central America and West Indies .
Selenicereus grandiflorus is a cactus species originating from the Antilles , Mexico and Central America .
Neodiprion sertifer , the European pine sawfly , is a sawfly species in the genus Neodiprion .
Mimepaphra borneana is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Mimepaphra .
Adetomyrma is a genus of ants endemic to Madagascar .
Basilicum is a genus of plants in the Lamiaceae , first described in 1802 .
Psidium guineense is a species of guava .
The yellow spear - winged fly or Lonchoptera lutea , is the type species of the genus Lonchoptera .

Pseudegalicia tetrops is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudegalicia .
Jameson 's firefinch ( Lagonosticta rhodopareia ) is a common species of estrildid finch found in Southern Africa .
Helluoherpia is a genus of pholidoskepian solenogasters , shell - less , worm - like marine mollusks .
Pugnus is a genus of very small sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks or micromollusks in the family Marginellidae .
Thalasseus , the crested terns , is a genus of six species of seabirds in the tern family .
Phelsuma comorensis Boettger , 1913 is a species of geckos that lives on the island Grande Comore and typically dwells on trees .
Agastache foeniculum ( blue giant hyssop ; syn . Agastache anethiodora ( Nutt . ) Britton ) , commonly called anise hyssop , blue giant hyssop , Fragrant giant hyssop , or the lavender giant hyssop , is a species of perennial plant in the mint family , ( Lamiaceae ) .
Schizopygopsis younghusbandi is a species of ray - finned fish endemic to Tibet .
Pseudomulleria dalyi is a species of bivalve in the Etheriidae family .
Acinos arvensis , known commonly as basil thyme and spring savory , is a species of plant of the genus Acinos .
Phyllostachys edulis , moso bamboo , or tortoise - shell bamboo , or mao zhu ( Chinese : 毛竹 ; pinyin : máozhú ) , ( Japanese モウソウチク(孟宗竹 ) ) is a temperate species of giant timber bamboo native to China and Taiwan and naturalised elsewhere .
Coryphopterus glaucofraenum , the Bridled goby , is a species of goby native to the Western Atlantic Ocean and the Caribbean Sea from North Carolina to Brazil .
Stemonitis axifera is a species of slime mold .
Epidendrum polyanthum ( gloss : `` many flowers upon a tree '' ) is a species of orchid in the genus Epidendrum .
Lappula squarrosa is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by several common names , including European stickseed , bur forget - me - not , bluebur , and bristly sheepbur .
Ippitoides uniformis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Ippitoides .
Elymus canadensis is a species of wild rye known by the common name Canada wild rye .
Lineus is a genus of nemertine worms , including the bootlace worm , arguably the longest animal alive .
Zosimus aeneus is a species of crab that lives on coral reefs in the Indo - Pacific from East Africa to Hawaii .
Erigeron schmalhausenii is an Asian species of flowering plants in the daisy family .
Chorizanthe angustifolia is a species of flowering plant in the buckwheat family known by the common name narrowleaf spineflower .
Halictus ligatus is a species of sweat bee from the family Halictidae , characterized by those bees that mine or burrow into the ground to create their nests .
Festuca occidentalis is a species of grass known by the common name western fescue .
In taxonomy , the Methanopyrales are an order of the methanopyri .
Lygosoma veunsaiensis is a species of skink that is endemic to northeastern Cambodia .
Gilia latiflora is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common names hollyleaf gilia and broad - flowered gilia .
Cimolomys is a mammal genus from the Upper Cretaceous of North America .
Azteca aragua is a species of ant in the genus Azteca .
Cotoneaster pannosus ( commonly known as silverleaf cotoneaster ' ) is a species of cotoneaster known by the common name silverleaf cotoneaster .
Turbo exquisitus , common name the exquisite turban , is a species of sea snail , marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae .
Drosophila hydei is a species of Diptera , or the order of flies , in the family Drosophilidae .
Dodonaea triquetra , known as common hop bush or large leaf hop bush , is a species of shrub occurring in eastern Australia .
Staurocumites is an extinct genus of sea cucumber which existed in Europe during the Triassic and Jurassic periods .
Cenchrus biflorus is a species of annual grass in the Poaceae family .
Rosa anemoniflora is a species of rose found in France .
The family Scarabaeidae as currently defined consists of over 30,000 species of beetles worldwide , often called scarabs or scarab beetles .
The Cross River bushbaby ( Sciurocheirus cameronensis ) is a species of primate in the family Galagidae found in northwestern Cameroon and southeastern Nigeria .
Erythroxylum echinodendron was a species of plant in the Erythroxylaceae family .
Phyciodes , commonly but ambiguously called the `` crescents '' or `` crescentspots '' ( like some related genera ) is a genus of butterflies of the subfamily Nymphalinae in the family Nymphalidae .
Guiomys is an extinct genus of cavioid rodent which existed in west central Patagonia of Argentina , during the middle Miocene .
Graus nigra is a species of sea chub endemic to the Pacific waters off the coast of Chile .
Dioryctria reniculelloides , the spruce coneworm , is a species of moth of the family Pyralidae .
Bathocyroe fosteri is a species of lobate ctenophore found at intermediate depths in all the world 's oceans .
The common hippopotamus ( Hippopotamus amphibius ) , or hippo , is a large , mostly herbivorous mammal in sub - Saharan Africa , and one of only two extant species in the family Hippopotamidae , the other being the pygmy hippopotamus ( Choeropsis liberiensis or Hexaprotodon liberiensis ) .
Ewartia is a genus of daisies native to New Zealand and Australia .
Leptotyphlops tricolor , or the Three - colored blind snake , is a species of snake in the Leptotyphlopidae family .
Salix hultenii is a species of willow native to Hokkaidō ( Japan ) , ( South Korea ) , Kuriles , Sakhalin and Kamchatka ( Russia ) .
Gerrardanthus is a genus of flowering plants native to tropical Africa and South Africa , first described by William Henry Harvey ( 1811 - -1866 ) , and named in honor of William Tyrer Gerrard ( died 1866 in Mahavelona , Madagascar ) , botanical collector in Natal and Madagascar in the 1860s .
Olpogastra lugubris , the slender bottletail , is a monotypic species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae .
Georissa biangulata is a species of minute cave snails that have an operculum .
Mesodmops is a genus of small mammal from the Eocene of China .
†Anoptychiidae is an extinct taxonomic family of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the informal group Lower Heterobranchia .
Holasteroida is an order of irregular sea urchins .
Wolffia globosa is a species of flowering plant known by the common name Asian watermeal .
Helochares is a genus of hydrophilid beetles with over 180 species in five subgenera worldwide .
Brachycephalus pitanga is a species of frog of the family Brachycephalidae .
Eucephalus tomentellus is a North American species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name Brickellbush aster or rayless aster .
Causus rhombeatus is a venomous viper species endemic to subsaharan Africa .
Palinurus mauritanicus ( common name : pink spiny lobster ) is a species of spiny lobster .
It contains only one known species , Pentapleura subulifera , native to southeastern Turkey and northern Iraq .
Aceria erinea is a species of mites belonging to the family Eriophyidae , the gall mites .
Acicula palaestinensis is a species of very small land snail with an operculum , a terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Aciculidae .
Utricularia delicatula is a terrestrial species of bladderwort and is unique within its genus in being endemic to New Zealand .
Neonoemacheilus is a genus of Asian stone loaches .
Bolma persica , common name the peach bolma , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae , the turban snails .
Liobagrus anguillicauda is a species of catfish in the Amblycipitidae family ( the torrent catfishes ) endemic to the province of Fujian in China .
Pardosa drenskii is a wolf spider species in the genus Pardosa found in Bulgaria .
Artemisia alaskana , the Alaskan sagebrush or Alaskan wormwood or Siberian wormwood , is a North American species of plants in the sunflower family .
Opuntia diploursina is a species in the Cactaceae family , that grows near the Grand Canyon and Lake Mead National Recreation Area .
Ponera is a genus of ponerine ants .
Gymnogyps varonai , sometimes called the Cuban condor , is an extinct species of large New World vultures in the family Cathartidae .
Myrmecia flavicoma is an ant species native to Australia .
Durbaniopsis is a genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae . The single species is endemic to the Afrotropics .
Reedbuck is a common name for African antelopes from the genus Redunca .
Microstrophia nana is a species of small , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Streptaxidae .
The Flores crow ( Corvus florensis ) is a species of bird in the family Corvidae .
Metriorhynchoidea is an extinct superfamily of thalattosuchian crocodyliforms from the early Middle Jurassic to the Early Cretaceous ( Aalenian - Valanginian ) of Europe , North America and South America .
Pedostibes kempi is a species of toad found in India .
Farlowella gracilis is a species of armored catfish endemic to Colombia where it is found in the Caqueta River basin .
Lemuridae is a family of strepsirrhine primates native to Madagascar , and the Comoro Islands .
Ammotrechidae are a family of solifuges distributed in the Americas and the Caribbean Islands .
Laternea pusilla is a species of fungi in the Phallaceae family .
Lambertella is a genus of fungi in the family Rutstroemiaceae .
Mesolenellus is an extinct genus of trilobites that lived during the lower Cambrian ( Botomian ) , found in Greenland and Spitsbergen .
Gobiceratops is a genus of ceratopsian dinosaur from the Upper Cretaceous of Mongolia .
Hedruris spinigera are widely distributed within New Zealand , scientists found that the distribution appears to be limited within the coastal area , especially in brackish waters . The prevalence of Hedruris spinigera depends on species of fishes .
Ranunculus populago is a species of buttercup known by the common names popular buttercup and mountain buttercup .
Pygmaleptostylus pygmaeus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Pygmaleptostylus .
Phylloporus arenicola is a species of bolete mushroom in the family Boletaceae .
Polarella is a genus of Alveolata .
Hebomoia is a genus of butterflies in the family Pieridae . There are two widespread , strong - flying southeast Asian species that are among the largest pierids .
Cyrtodactylus phongnhakebangensis ( Vietnamese : Thằn lằn Phong Nha - Kẻ Bàng ) is a species of gecko native to Phong Nha - Kẻ Bàng National Park , Quảng Bình Province , North Central Coast , Vietnam .
Pinus oocarpa is a species of pine tree native to Mexico and Central America .
Luzula nivea , commonly known as snow - white wood - rush , snowy wood - rush and lesser wood - rush , is a species of perennial plant in Juncaceae family .
Chaerophyllum elegans is a flowering plant species in the genus Chaerophyllum found in the Alps from Switzerland , France and Italy .
Agyneta palgongsanensis is a species of sheet weaver found in China , Korea and Russia .
Leshansaurus is a genus of theropod dinosaur from the Mid to Late Jurassic Dashanpu Formation of what is now China .
Paraneetroplus is a genus of cichlids native to rivers in Central America .
Amorphospermum is a genus of plants in the Sapotaceae family described as a genus in 1870 .
Streblote cristata is a species of moth in the family Lasiocampidae , the so - called eggars , snout moths or lappet moths .
Cattleya intermedia ( `` The Intermediate Cattleya '' ) is a bifoliate Cattleya species of orchid .
The genus 's lone - described species , Orvilleus crassus , is found only in Panama .
Cryptomonas is the name - giving genus of the cryptomonads .
Swietenia mahagoni , commonly known as the West Indian mahogany , is a species of Swietenia native to southern Florida in the United States and islands in the Caribbean including the Bahamas , Cuba , Jamaica , and Hispaniola .
Grindelia integrifolia , common name Puget Sound gumweed , is a plant species known only from Oregon , Washington and British Columbia .
Panagaeus robustus is a species of ground beetle in the Panagaeinae subfamily that can be found in Japan and Maritime province of Russia .
Whereas the species usually has one anther , Prosthechea cochleata var . triandra is an endangered variety that has three anthers and is autogamous , allowing its existence in Florida where no appropriate pollinators appear to be present .
Orcuttia tenuis ( slender Orcutt grass ) is a species of grass which is endemic to northern California .
The Eurotiales are an order of sac fungi , also known as the green and blue molds .
Paramuricea clavata , the violescent sea - whip , is a species of colonial soft coral in the family Plexauridae .
Cyrtodesmus humerosus is a species of millipede in the family Cyrtodesmidae that is endemic to San Vito , Costa Rica , where it was found on April 19 , 1972 .
Alveopora fenestrata is a species of stony coral that is found in the Red Sea , the Gulf of Aden , the southwest and northern Indian Ocean , the central Indo - Pacific , Australia , Southeast Asia and the oceanic west Pacific Ocean .
Dinoderus minutus is a species of wood - boring beetle .
Pseudochromis fridmani is a species of fish in the family Pseudochromidae , the dottybacks .
Sternarchorhamphus muelleri is a species of ghost knifefish that occurs in the Amazon River Basin .
Crypsis vaginiflora is a species of grass known by the common name modest pricklegrass .
Ranunculus andersonii is a species of buttercup known by the common name Anderson 's buttercup .
Samaris is a genus of crested flounders native to the Indo - Pacific .
The sablefishes are a family , Anoplopomatidae , of scorpaeniform fishes .
The Junaluska salamander ( Eurycea junaluska ) is a species of lungless salamander native to the Southeastern United States .
Dioscorea trifida is a species of flowering plant in the family Dioscoreaceae .
Leptotyphlops leptepileptus , or the Haitian border thread snake , is a species of snake in the Leptotyphlopidae family .
Amorpha californica is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name California false indigo .
The Tymovirales are a newly established order of viruses in the 2009 classification with four families .
Chimaerasuchidae ( `` Chimera crocodiles '' ) is a family of mesoeucrocodylians .
Lumbricus rubellus is a species of earthworm that is related to Lumbricus terrestris .
Hoplocorypha carli is a species of praying mantis found in Rwanda .
Drepanolepis is an extinct genus of thelodont which lived in Canada during the Early Devonian period .
Tropicoritus ruwenzorii is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Tropicoritus .
†Neptunea angulata is an extinct species of large fossil sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Buccinidae .
Orrorin tugenensis is a postulated early species of Homininae , estimated at 6.1 to 5.7 million years ( Ma ) and discovered in 2000 .
Psychotria minimicalyx is a species of plant in the Rubiaceae family .
Lentigo pipus , common name : the Elegant Conch , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Strombidae , the true conchs .
Tonna melanostoma is a species of large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Tonnidae , the tun shells .
Sthenomerus is an extinct genus of Diprotodontia .
Silurus is a genus of catfishes native to Europe and Asia .
Saccoloma is a fern genus in family Saccolomataceae .
Rhytisma is a genus of fungi in the Rhytismataceae family commonly known as ' tar spot ' .
The Cyanophyllum Scale , Abgrallaspis cyanophylli ( Signoret ) , is one of nine species of the Abgrallaspis genus of armored scale insects .
The Mesopotamian crow is a subspecies of the hooded crow ( Corvus cornix ) , but is also sometimes distinguished as its own species of crow , as it is characterized by its pied coloration .
Thomas 's langur ( Presbytis thomasi ) is a species of primate in the family Cercopithecidae .
Hemipsilichthys papillatus is a species of loricariid catfish endemic to Brazil , where it is restricted to the Rio Preto , a tributary of the Paraíba do Sul , in the southeastern states of Minas Gerais , Rio de Janeiro and São Paulo .
Iva asperifolia , the Pensacola marsh elder , is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family .
Pygidicranidae is a family of earwigs , formerly placed in the suborder Forficulina , now in the suborder Neodermaptera .
Orchis italica , commonly known as the naked man orchid or the Italian orchid , is a species of orchid native to the Mediterranean .
The Central Mexican broad - clawed shrew ( Cryptotis alticola ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Wannchampsus ( `` Wann Langston , Jr. 's crocodile '' ) is an extinct genus of paralligatorid neosuchian , close to but not a true crocodilian .
Hemiphractus scutatus ( Spix 's horned treefrog ) is a species of frog in the Hemiphractidae family .
Micropterix amsella is a species of moth belonging to the family Micropterigidae that was described by Heath in 1975 , and is endemic to Croatia .
Raorchestes ghatei ( common name : Ghate 's shrub frog ) is a species of shrub frog from the Western Ghats of Maharashtra .
Gomphocerini is a tribe of grasshoppers of the family Acrididae .
Nebria jeffreyi is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to US state of Oregon .
Erythronium oregonum is a North American species of flowering plant in the lily family which is known by the common name giant white fawnlily or Oregon fawn - lily .
Litoceras is a trocholitid ( Tarphycerida ) genus that has been found in the Lower and Middle Ordovician of Newfoundland .
Helcionopsis radiatum is an extinct species of paleozoic monoplacophoran in the family Tryblidiidae .
Huerteales is the botanical name for an order of flowering plants .
Malacoctenus aurolineatus , the Goldline blenny , is a species of labrisomid blenny native to the western Atlantic Ocean , including the Gulf of Mexico and the Caribbean Sea from southern Florida to northern South America .
Dryptosauroides ( meaning `` similar in form to Dryptosaurus '' ) is the name given to a genus of dinosaur from the Late Cretaceous .
Enigmatichthys is a genus of extinct semionotiformid bony fish that lived during the Middle Triassic epoch of what is now Australia .
Stenopelix ( meaning `` narrow pelvis '' ) is a genus of small ornithischian dinosaur from the Early Cretaceous of Germany .
Lebia humeralis is a species of ground beetles in the Harpalinae subfamily that can be found in Austria , Bulgaria , Czech Republic , Greece , Hungary , Italy ( including Sardinia and Sicily ) , Moldova , Romania , Slovakia , Switzerland , Ukraine , and in all Yugoslavian states and southern part of Russia .
Eucalyptus elaeophloia , commonly known as Nunniong Gum or Olive Mallee , is a mallee or tree species that is endemic to a restricted area in south - eastern Australia .
Petaloptyon is a genus known from the Middle Cambrian Burgess Shale .
Phymatocarpus is a genus of flowering plants in the family Myrtaceae and is endemic to the south - west of Western Australia .
All terete leaved Dendrobium species from Australia and Papua New Guinea have been moved into a newly created genus , Dockrillia , named after Alick Dockrill , a contemporary Australian orchidologist .
†Elimia lachryma was a species of freshwater snails with an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Pleuroceridae .
Amsonia tharpii is a species of flowering plant in the dogbane family known by the common names Tharp 's bluestar and feltleaf bluestar .
Phrynoidis juxtasper , also known as the giant river toad or Borneo river toad , is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Leptodactylus is a genus of leptodactylid frogs .
Pterula is a genus of fungi in the Pterulaceae family .
Byturidae , also known as Fruitworms is a family of beetles , in the suborder Polyphaga .
Crabs are decapod crustaceans of the infraorder Brachyura , which typically have a very short projecting `` tail '' ( abdomen ) ( Greek : βραχύς / brachys = short , οὐρά / οura = tail ) , usually entirely hidden under the thorax .
Pilosella schultesii ( not to be confused with the Mexican P. schultzii ) is a European plant species in the dandelion tribe within the sunflower family .
Oniscoidea is a superfamily of isopod crustaceans , which includes most of the land - living woodlice .
Masdevallia goliath is a species of epiphytic orchid native to northeastern Peru and southeastern Ecuador but is cultivated as an ornamental elsewhere .
Ulmus americana , generally known as the American elm or , less commonly , as the white elm or water elm , is a species native to eastern North America , occurring from Nova Scotia west to Alberta and Montana , and south to Florida and central Texas .
Phacelia procera is a species of phacelia known by the common name tall phacelia .
Peteinosaurus ( /pɛˌtaɪnəˈsɔːrəs/ pe - TY - nə - SAWR - əs meaning `` winged lizard '' ) was a prehistoric reptile genus belonging to the Pterosauria .
Trachyandra erythrorrhiza is a species of plant which is endemic to the province of Gauteng in South Africa .
The Kauaʻi ʻakialoa , like all the other ʻakialoa subspecies , were rare even when they were first discovered in the 18th century .
Triatoma dominicana is an extinct species of assassin bug in the subfamily Triatominae , the kissing bugs known from early Miocene Burdigalian stage Dominican amber deposits on the island of Hispaniola .
Costus spicatus , also known as spiked spiralflag ginger or Indian head ginger , is a species of herbaceous plant in the Costaceae family ( also sometimes placed in Zingiberaceae ) .
Agkistrodon is a genus of venomous pit vipers found in North America from the United States south to northern Costa Rica .
Paramisgurnus dabryanus is a species of loach occurring in East Asia from Russia to China and Taiwan .
Haplochromis nigricans is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Victoria where it is know only known with certainty from Entebbe , Uganda , other populations now placed in H. rufocaudalis .
The New Caledonian friarbird ( Philemon diemenensis ) is a species of bird in the Meliphagidae family .

Acantopsis spectabilis is a species of fish found in Thailand .
Cophixalus ateles ( common name : Papua rainforest frog ) is a species of frog in the Microhylidae family .
Collinsia corymbosa is a species of flowering plant in the plantain family known by the common name round - headed Chinese houses .
The Yucatán box turtle ( Terrapene carolina yucatana ) is a subspecies of box turtle endemic to Mexico .
Lycodon mackinnoni , commonly known as Mackinnon 's wolf snake , is a species of colubrid snake , which is endemic to Asia .
Deroceras invadens is a species of air - breathing land slug , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Agriolimacidae .

Embothrium is a genus of two to eight species ( depending on taxonomic interpretation ) in the plant family Proteaceae , native to southern South America , in Chile and adjacent western Argentina and southern Peru ; the genus occurs as far south as Tierra del Fuego .
Arachnitis uniflora , the sole species in the genus Arachnitis , is a non - photosynthetic species of plant .
Sibynophis bistrigatus , commonly known as Günther 's many - toothed snake , is a nonvenomous species of colubrid snake found in Myanmar ( formerly called Burma ) and India ( Nicobar Islands ) , but snakes collected in Myanmar and the Nicobar Islands might actually not refer to the same species .
Agathis , commonly known as kauri or dammar , is a relatively small genus of 21 species of evergreen tree .
Fungia scutaria is a species of plate or mushroom coral in the family Fungiidae .
Amitostigma lepidum is a species of plant in the Orchidaceae family found on Kyushu Island in Japan , and in Nansei - shoto ( Ryukyu Islands ) to the south .
Hall 's babbler is a small species of bird in the Pomatostomidae family most commonly found in dry Acacia scrubland of interior regions of eastern Australia .
Marmornectes was first named by Hilary F. Ketchum and Roger B. J. Benson in 2011 and the type species is Marmornectes candrewi .
Parochetus communis , known in English as shamrock pea or blue oxalis , is a species of legume , and the only species in the genus Parochetus and in the subtribe Parochetinae .

Pyroteuthis addolux is a species of squid in the family Pyroteuthidae .
Stenolemus is a genus of thread - legged bug ( Emesinae ) .
Phenacolepas crenulata is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Phenacolepadidae .
Leptobrachium montanum is a species of amphibian from the Megophryidae family .

Fissurella maxima , common name : the giant keyhole limpet , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets .
Diomus is a genus of ladybirds .
It was first named by Sean P. Modesto , Diane M. Scott , and Robert R. Reisz in 2009 , and the type species is Australothyris smithi .
Oedicarena persuasa is a species of tephritid or fruit flies in the genus Oedicarena of the family Tephritidae .
Theora mesopotamica is a species of saltwater and brackish water clam , a bivalve mollusk in the family Semelidae .
The subfamily Deomyinae consists of four genera of mouse - like rodents that were placed in the subfamilies Murinae and Dendromurinae until very recently .
Bats of the genus Chalinolobus are commonly known as pied , wattled , or long - tailed bats .
