Coradion melanopus , known commonly as the Twospot coralfish , is a species of marine fish in the family Chaetodontidae .
Encephalartos cycadifolius is a species of cycad that is native to the Winterberg mountains to the north of Bedford in the Eastern Cape province , South Africa .
Orthetrum taeniolatum , also known as Libellula taeniolata , Orthetrum brevistylum , Orthetrum garhwalicum or Orthetrum hyalianum is an Asian freshwater dragonfly species .

Dromius is a genus of ground beetle native to the Palearctic ( including Europe ) , the Nearctic , the Near East , and North Africa .

Zabrus sublaevis is a species of black coloured ground beetle in the Pelor subgenus that is endemic to Ankara , Turkey .

Modulidae , common name modulids , is a family of small sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the superfamily Cerithioidea .
Allopeas clavulinum , common name the spike awlsnail , is a species of small , tropical , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Subulinidae .
Aureoboletus moravicus , commonly known as the tawny bolete , is a species of bolete fungus in the family Boletaceae that is found in Europe .
Jasus paulensis , also commonly known as the St Paul rock lobster , is a species of spiny lobster found in the waters around Saint Paul Island in the southern Indian Ocean and around Tristan da Cunha in the southern Atlantic Ocean .
Pagurus samuelis , the blueband hermit crab , is a species of hermit crab from the west coast of North America , and the most common hermit crab in California .
Trichotropis conicus is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Capulidae , the cap snails .
Myristica sinclairii is a species of nutmeg .
Deinobacterium is a genus in the Deinococcus - Thermus group ( Bacteria ) .
Minuartia douglasii is a species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common name Douglas ' stitchwort .
Hesperolinon drymarioides is a rare species of flowering plant in the flax family known by the common names drymary dwarf flax and drymaria - like western flax ; it is named for its resemblance to genus Drymaria .
Duffichthys is a genus of prehistoric lobe - finned fish which lived during the Late Devonian period .
Xeromphalina campanelloides is a species of Tricholomataceae fungus .
Artemisia spiciformis is a North American species in the sunflower family , with the common name Snowfield sagebrush .
Specula styliformis is a species of minute sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs or micromolluscs in the family Cerithiopsidae .
Flueggea neowawraea , Mēhamehame , is a species of flowering tree in the Bignay family , Phyllanthaceae , that is endemic to Hawaii .
Lythrum tribracteatum is a species of flowering plant in the loosestrife family known by the common name threebract loosestrife .
Bolitotherus cornutus is a North American species of darkling beetle known as the forked fungus beetle .
Pilargidae is a family of polychaetes .
Gorgoniidae is a family of soft corals , a member of the subclass Octocorallia in the phylum Cnidaria .
Pachypanchax playfairii , the golden panchax , is a species of Aplocheilid killifish , the only species of freshwater fish endemic to the Seychelles , a group of islands in the Indian Ocean directly east of Tanzania and the only member of its genus found outside of Madagascar .
Acer negundo is a species of maple native to North America .
Trifolium lemmonii is a species of clover known by the common name Lemmon 's clover .
Othnocerus aethes is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Othnocerus .
Aeonium ( tree houseleek ) is a genus of about 35 species of succulent , subtropical plants of the family Crassulaceae .
Hyalobagrus ornatus is a species of bagrid catfish found in Indonesia , Malaysia and Thailand .
Sea turtles ( superfamily Chelonioidea ) , sometimes called marine turtles , are reptiles of the order Testudines .
Sporobolus is a nearly cosmopolitan genus of plants in the grass family .
Psilorhynchus arunachalensis is a species of mountain carp .
Leucocoprinus cepistipes ( often spelled cepaestipes ) , is a species of fungus in the family Agaricaceae .
The Mahenge toad or Loveridge 's forest toad , Mertensophryne loveridgei , is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
The Ogoveidae are a family of harvestmen with three described species in one genus , Ogovea , which is found in tropical rain forests of equatorial West Africa .
Helleborus foetidus , known variously as stinking hellebore /ˈhɛlɪbɔːr/ , dungwort , setterwort and bear 's foot , is a species of flowering plant in the buttercup family Ranunculaceae , native to the mountainous regions of Central and Southern Europe , Greece and Asia Minor .
Acanthodraco dewitti is a species of Antarctic dragonfish native to the Southern Ocean including the Ross Sea and the southeastern Pacific Ocean .
Lactobacillus delbrueckii is a species of bacteria in the family Lactobacillaceae .
Lunella coronata , common name the crowned turban shell or the coronate moon turban , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae , the turban snails .
Juncus rigidus is a species of rush known by the common name sea rush .
Schizodon is a genus of headstander from South America .
Bromus alopecuros is a species of brome grass known by the common name weedy brome .
Mycena sanguinolenta , commonly known as the bleeding bonnet , the smaller bleeding Mycena , or the terrestrial bleeding Mycena , is a species of mushroom in the Mycenaceae family .
Sceloporus merriami , commonly known as the canyon lizard , is a species of phrynosomatid lizard native to the southwestern United States and northern Mexico .
Sicyos albus ( sometimes spelled Sicyos alba ) is a species of flowering plant in the gourd family known by the common names anunu and white bur - cucumber .
Scotobleps is a monotypic frog genus in the family Arthroleptidae ; its sole species is Scotobleps gabonicus , sometimes known as the Gaboon forest frog .
Phyllodontosuchus ( Ancient Greek , meaning `` leaf tooth crocodile '' , in reference to the shape of the middle and posterior teeth ) is a genus of sphenosuchian , a type of basal crocodylomorph , the clade that comprises the crocodilians and their closest kin .
Ostorhinchus brevispinis is a species of deep - water cardinalfish .
Aloe camperi is a species of aloe indigenous to Africa , specifically the regions of Ethiopia and Eritrea .
Downingia pulchella is a species of flowering plant in the bellflower family known by the common names flatface calicoflower and valley calicoflower .
Synemosyna is a genus of ant - like jumping spiders that occurs from Argentina to the northern United States .
Aalenirhynchia is an extinct subgenus of brachiopod found in Aalenian strata in Gloucestershire , England .
The Garniidae are a family of parasitic protozoa in the phylum Apicomplexia .
Argiope aetherea is a common , large orb - web spider This species is commonly known as the St Andrew 's Cross spider due to the characteristic cross - shaped web decorations often included in their webs by female spiders .
Lloydolithus is a genus of trilobite from the Late Ordovician of Europe .
Brachiopods , phylum Brachiopoda , are marine animals that have hard `` valves '' ( shells ) on the upper and lower surfaces , unlike the left and right arrangement in bivalve molluscs .
Symphyotrichum campestre ( formerly Aster campestris ) is a species of aster known by the common name western meadow aster .
Recilia hospes is a species of bugs from Cicadellidae family that can be found in Fiji , Hawaii , New Zealand .
Saxifraga hirculus is a species of saxifrage , commonly called marsh saxifrage , yellow marsh saxifrage , or bog saxifrage .
Myrmica aloba is a species of ant that can be found in France , Portugal , and Spain .
Polyspilota griffinii , common name Griffin mantis , is a species of praying mantis native to Cameroon that grows to about 5 inches in length .
Butomus umbellatus is the Old World Palearctic and Asian plant species in the family Butomaceae .
Dilambdogale is an extinct genus of afrosoricid which existed in Fayum , Egypt during the latest Eocene ( earliest Priabonian age ) .
Wolf spiders are members of the family Lycosidae , from the Ancient Greek word `` λύκος '' meaning `` wolf '' .
Agyneta resima is a species of sheet weaver found in Eastern Europe .
Exerpes asper , the Sargassum blenny , is a species of labrisomid blenny native to the Gulf of California and the Pacific coast of Baja California .
Tetraodon waandersii is a species of freshwater pufferfish endemic to Indonesia .
The silk floss tree ( Ceiba speciosa , formerly Chorisia speciosa ) , is a species of deciduous tree native to the tropical and subtropical forests of South America .
Cernaysia is an extinct genus of mammal from the Paleocene of France and the United States .
Hypopygus lepturus is a species of bluntnose knifefish and is commonly found in Northern South America .
Bothriomyrmex pubens is a species of ant in the genus Bothriomyrmex .
The Balsas screech owl ( Megascops seductus ) is a species of owl in the family Strigidae .
Eubacterium oxidoreducens is a Gram positive bacterium species in the genus Eubacterium .
Chauliognathus is a genus of soldier beetles in the family Cantharidae .
Acanthobrama microlepis , called the blackbrow bleak or the Caucasian bream , is a species of freshwater fish in the Cyprinidae family .
Fossarus bellus is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Planaxidae .
Lotus formosissimus is a species of legume known by the common name seaside bird's - foot trefoil .
Zoellnerallium is a genus of perennial herbaceous geophytes in the flowering plant family Amaryllidaceae .
Sialis is a genus of alderfly belonging to the order Megaloptera family Sialidae .
Corollonema is a species of plants in the Apocynaceae first described as a genus in 1914 .
Lithospermum molle , the softhair marbleseed , is a species of flowering plant in the forget - me - not family .
Dictyna armata is spider species found in Ukraine and Georgia .
Croton lechleri is a species of flowering plant in the spurge family , Euphorbiaceae , that is native to northwestern South America .
Hypleurochilus springeri , the Orange - spotted blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the western Atlantic ocean .
Pallas 's leaf warbler is named after the German zoologist Peter Simon Pallas , who discovered it on the Ingoda River in Siberia in 1811 ; the species name proregulus derives from its similar size to the goldcrest Regulus regulus .
Puccinia oxalidis is a fungus species in the genus Puccinia .
Aeluropus is a genus of Eurasian and African plants in the grass family , found primarily in desert regions .
Dolichogenidea is a genus of Braconid wasp .
The Tawitawi brown dove ( Phapitreron cinereiceps ) is a threatened species of bird in the family Columbidae .
Undaria is a genus of kelp that includes Undaria pinnatifida ( wakame ) .
Poa bolanderi is a species of grass known by the common name Bolander 's bluegrass .
Lasmigona alabamensis , common name Alabama heelsplitter , is a species of freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusk in the family Unionidae .
The family Ichthyodectidae ( literally `` fish - biters '' ) is an extinct family of marine actinopterygian fish .
The Euchromiina are a subtribe of tiger moths in the Erebidae family .
Macrocybe spectabilis is a species of mushroom - forming fungus .
Hydropessum is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish that lived during the Early Triassic epoch .
Axitectum is an extinct genus of bystrowianid reptiliomorph from lower Triassic deposits of Nizhni Novgorod and Kirov Regions , Russia .
Allium oleraceum ( field garlic ) is a Eurasian species of wild onion .
Leiocephalus carinatus , commonly known as the northern curly - tailed lizard , is a species of lizard in the family Leiocephalidae ( curly - tailed lizards ) .
Dicranaceae is a family of mosses in class Bryopsida .
Hypoxylon is a genus of Ascomycetes commonly found on dead wood , and usually one of the earliest species to colonise dead wood .
Cardioglossa oreas ( common name : Mount Okou long - fingered frog ) is a species of frog in the Arthroleptidae family .
Tangasaurus is an extinct genus of aquatic basal tangasaurid neodiapsid known from the Late Permian period ( late Changhsingian stage ) of Tanga , northeastern Tanzania .
Treubia scapanioides is a species of liverwort in the family Treubiaceae .
Marmosops is a genus of Neotropic opossums of the family Didelphidae .
Heliconia hirsuta ( syn . , ) is a species of flowering plant in the Heliconiaceae family .
The Chaetonotida is an order of gastrotrichs .
Apodolirion is a genus of herbaceous , perennial and bulbous plants in the Amaryllis family ( Amaryllidaceae , subfamily Amaryllidoideae ) .
Streptanthus glandulosus is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name bristly jewelflower .
Phenagoniates macrolepis is a species of characin found in Colombia , Panama and Venezuela .
Pristolepis pentacantha is a species of the family Pristolepididae described from Kabani River of Kerala , India .
Phaeoceros laevis , the smooth hornwort , is a species of hornwort of the genus Phaeoceros .
Opuntia robusta , wheel cactus , nopal tapon , or camuesa , is a species of cactus in the Cactaceae family .
Geastrum lloydianum is a species of fungus belonging to the genus Geastrum , or earthstar fungi .
Within the Orchidaceae , Hormidium was originally a subgenus of the genus Epidendrum , but was later raised to a full genus .
Nerita albicilla , common name the blotched nerite , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Neritidae .
Nebria rufescens is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that can be found everywhere in Europe , except for Benelux , Bosnia and Herzegovina , Denmark , Monaco , San Marino , Vatican City , and various European islands .
Streptomyces griseiniger is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated in Australia .
Proterorhinus marmoratus is a species of gobiid fish , a tubenose goby native to the brackish water parts of the Black Sea and the Sea of Azov , near the coasts of Bulgaria , Georgia , Romania , Ukraine and Russia .
Chamaecrista is a genus of flowering plants in the pea family , Fabaceae , subfamily Caesalpinioideae .
Fockea is a genus of succulent scrubs native to southern Africa , known collectively as water roots , a reference to their characteristic bulbous caudex , which is edible in at least some species .
Leiocephalus carinatus armouri , commonly known as the Little Bahama curly - tailed lizard , is a subspecies of Leiocephalus carinatus , the northern curly - tailed lizard .
Chamaepsila is a genus of flies in the family Psilidae .
The Astor markhor or flare - horned markhor ( Capra falconeri falconeri ) is a subspecies of the endangered markhor , native to Kashmir and northern Pakistan .
Pseudodynerus is a small neotropical genus of potter wasps ( Hymenoptera : Vespidae : Eumeninae ) currently containing 16 species .
Eupatorium semiserratum , commonly called Smallflower thoroughwort , is a North American plant species in the sunflower family .
Nebria agilis is a species of ground beetle from Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Yunnan , province of China .
Caiuajara is an extinct genus of tapejarid pterosaur from the Late Cretaceous of Brazil .
Uropteryginae is a subfamily of moray eels .
Lythrurus , the finescale shiner , is a genus of cyprinid fish found in North America .
Seimatosporium mariae is a fungus genus .
Unlike most other placoderm orders , such as the Antiarchs , or the Arthrodires , Gemuendina and its four other known relatives ( or seven , if the three species of the ichthyolith genus Ohioaspis are confirmed to be rhenanids ) had armor made up of a mosaic of unfused bony plates and scales .
Unlike many Inocybe species , Inocybe hystrix is densely covered in brown scales , a characteristic that aids in identification .
Bufo cristinae ( Beaked frog ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Nemapteryx is a genus of sea catfishes found mostly in coastal marine and brackish waters from South Asia to Australia with one species ( N. augusta ) occurring exclusively in fresh waters of the Fly River in Papua New Guinea .
Aprosphylosoma darceneae is a species of cylindrical julidan millipede found only in the U.S. state of Oregon and comprising the sole species of the family Aprosphylosomatidae .
Gavialis is a genus of crocodylians that includes the living gharial Gavialis gangeticus and several extinct species , including Gavialis bengawanicus , Gavialis breviceps , Gavialis browni , Gavialis curvirostris , Gavialis hysudricus , Gavialis leptodus , Gavialis lewisi , and Gavialis pachyrhynchus .
The Indian desert jird , Meriones hurrianae , is a species of jird found mainly in the Thar Desert in India .
Nielsenoceras is a Paraceltitid genus of from the lower Upper Permian , known from sediments in west Texas .
Hechtia marnier - lapostollei is a species in the genus Hechtia .
Denticetopsis sauli is a species of whale catfish endemic to Venezuela , where it is only known from the Pamoni River in the Casiquiare River basin of the upper Rio Negro system .
Interjectio denticulella is a species of snout moth in the genus Interjectio .
Streptomyces djakartensis is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil from Djakarta on Java in Indonesia .
Caymanabyssia spina is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Caymanabyssiidae , the false limpets .

Foerschichthys flavipinnis is a species of African rivuline native to the western African nations of Ghana , Togo , Benin and Nigeria .
Parachanna is a genus of snakeheads native to tropical Africa .
Aeschynanthus longicaulis is a species of perennial plant in the family Gesneriaceae , native to Vietnam , Thailand and Malaysia .
Mimulus gemmiparus is a rare species of flowering plant in the family Phrymaceae , known by the common name Rocky Mountain monkeyflower .
Eleocharis parvula is a species of spikesedge known by the common names dwarf spikerush , small spikerush and hairgrass in aquaria .
Erymidae is a family of decapod crustaceans known only from fossils .
Ampullariidae , common name the apple snails , is a family of large freshwater snails , aquatic gastropod mollusks with a gill and an operculum .
Urticina columbiana , common names crusty red anemone , columbia sand anemone , sand anemone , and the sand - rose anemone , is a species of sea anemone in the family Actiniidae .
The floss silk tree ( Ceiba chodatii ) , is a species of deciduous tree native to the tropical and subtropical forests of South America .
Linckia is a genus of sea stars found mainly in the Indo - Pacific region .
Deschampsia is a genus of plants in the grass family , commonly known as hair grass or tussock grass .
Chaetonotus elegans is a gastrotrich species in the genus Chaetonotus .
Rhytida citrina is a species of medium - sized , air - breathing predatory land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the eponymous family Rhytididae .
Gobio holurus or the Caspian gudgeon is a freshwater fish species in the Cyprinidae family .
Rossioglossum grande ( tiger orchid ) is an epiphytic species of orchid native to the area from Chiapas to Costa Rica .
Mystacernis alphesta is a moth in the Xyloryctidae family , and the only species in the genus Mystacernis .
Hypohippus ( `` Low Horse '' ) is an extinct genus of three - toed horse , which lived 17 - 11 million years ago .
Allium diabolense , common name serpentine onion or devil 's onion is a species of wild onion endemic to central California , where it is known from the Coast Ranges and the Transverse Ranges .

Pison is a cosmopolitan genus of wasps within the family Crabronidae .
Pogonopoma is a genus of armored catfish native to rivers in south and southeast Brazil .
Homaloptera orthogoniata is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Homaloptera found in Thailand , Laos and Indonesia .
Hudson 's canastero ( Asthenes hudsoni ) is a species of bird in the Furnariidae family .
Allonautilus perforatus is a species of nautilus native to the waters around Bali , Indonesia .

Dendrocopos is a widespread genus of woodpeckers from Asia and Europe and Northern Africa .
Glossogobius intermedius is a species of goby endemic to Sulawesi , Indonesia where it is only known to occur in Lake Towuti and Lake Mahalona .
Ciliopagurus vakovako is a species of hermit crab native to the Marquesas Islands .

Arctaspis is an extinct genus of placoderm fish , which lived during the Devonian period in Norway .
Cryptococcus skinneri is species of yeast which forms white and cream colored colonies which are smooth with a mucoid texture .
Banksia dallanneyi var . dallanneyi is a variety of Banksia dallanneyi subsp .
Agonum placidum is a species of black coloured ground beetle in the Platyninae subfamily that can be found in woodlands , thickets , and open fields of southern Canada and northeastern United States .
Gasteropelecus is a genus of freshwater hatchetfishes found in Central and South America .
Crocodylus raninus is an enigmatic species of freshwater crocodile endemic to the Southeast Asian island of Borneo .
Brachysuchus is an extinct genus of phytosaur known from the late Triassic period ( Carnian stage ) of Dockum Group in Texas , USA .
Scenedra umbrosalis is a species of snout moth in the genus Scenedra .
Leptophilypnus is a genus of small sleeper gobies native to fresh and brackish water in Central America .
Pteraspidiformes is an extinct order of heterostracan vertebrates known from extensive fossil remains primarily from Early Devonian strata of Europe and North America , and from Upper Silurian Canada .

Pomacea paludosa , common name the Florida applesnail , is a species of freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Ampullariidae , the apple snails .
Bouchardina is a genus of North American crayfish , containing a single species , Bouchardina robisoni ( Bayou Bodcau Crayfish ) which is named after one of the scientist who found it Henry W. Robison .
Sophora toromiro , commonly known as Toromiro , is a species of flowering tree in the legume family , Fabaceae , that is endemic to Easter Island .
Hydnophytum is a genus of epiphytic myrmecophytes ( ant plants ) native to Southeast Asia , the Pacific region and also extending into Queensland in northern Australia .
Epsilon 15 ( or ε15 ) is a virus , specifically a bacteriophage , known to infect species of Salmonella bacteria including Salmonella anatum .
Megacephala femoralis is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae that was described by Perty in 1830 , and can be found in Argentina , Brazil , and Paraguay .
Sarcocornia blackiana , commonly known as Thick - head Glasswort , is a species of succulent halophytic shrub .
Allium scorzonerifolium is a yellow - flowered species of wild onion native to Spain , Portugal , and Morocco .
Scytothamnales is an order of brown algae ( class Phaeophyceae ) .
Onchidiopsis groenlandica is a species of relatively large sea snail with a transparent internal shell , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Velutinidae .
Colpophyllia natans , known as boulder brain coral and large - grooved brain coral , is a species of stony coral found primarily in the Caribbean Sea and the Gulf of Mexico .
Anomalopus is the genus of worm - skinks , smallish smooth - scaled burrowing skinks ( family Scincidae ) from the eastern half of Australia .
Daphnia barbata is a species of water flea within the family Daphniidae .
Kaliphora madagascarensis is a species of evergreen shrub or small tree .
Agonum fidele is a species of ground beetle from Platyninae subfamily , that can be found in United States and Canada .
Eriogonum hookeri is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name Hooker 's buckwheat .
Parapuzosia is an extinct genus of desmoceratid ammonites from the Cenomanian to the Campanian of Africa , Europe , and North America .
Skythrenchelys macrostoma , also known as the Large - mouth angry worm eel is a species of eel in the family Ophichthidae .
The Ophiceratidae is a family in the ammonoid order Ceratitida from the Lower Triassic , previously included in the Otocerataceae but now placed in the Noritiaceae as revised .
Brickellia pringlei ( Pringle 's brickellbush ) is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family .
Thermarces cerberus is a species of ray - finned fish in the family Zoarcidae .
Cyathea baileyana , also known as the wig tree fern , is a species of tree fern native to northeastern Queensland in Australia , where it grows in wet gullies and forest at an altitude of 850 - 1200 m. It is a rare species that is seldom found in the wild .
Parastratiosphecomyia sphecomyioides is a species of fly in the soldier fly family .
Phloeomana is a bark - inhabiting agaric fungal genus that produces fuscous - colored to whitish mycenoid to omphalinoid fruit bodies in temperate forests .
Tetraneuris torreyana is a North American species of plants in the sunflower family , known by the common name Torrey 's four - nerve daisy .
Caulerpa taxifolia is a species of seaweed , an alga of the genus Caulerpa .
The San Gabriel slender salamander ( Batrachoseps gabrieli ) is a species of salamander .
Buccinum leucostoma , common name the yellow - mouth Buccinum , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Buccinidae , the true whelks .
Galaxias globiceps is a species of fish in the Galaxiidae family endemic to Chile .
The Centrosaurinae is a subfamily of ceratopsid dinosaurs named by paleontologist Lawrence Lambe , in 1915 , with Centrosaurus as the type genus .
Araeomerus hubbardi is a species of earwigs , in the genus Araeomerus , family Hemimeridae , the suborder Hemimerina , and the order Dermaptera .
Othonocheirodus eigenmanni is a species of characin endemic to Peru , where it is found in the Amazon River basin .
Owenetta is an extinct genus of owenettid procolophonian parareptile .
Maui 's dolphin or popoto ( Cephalorhynchus hectori maui ) is the world 's rarest and smallest known subspecies of dolphin .
Vorticella convallaria is a protozoan , the type species of the genus Vorticella .
Staffordia toruputuensis is a species of air - breathing land snail , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Staffordiidae .
Arcobacter is a genus of Gram - negative , spiral - shaped bacteria in the epsilonproteobacteria class .
Desulfovirgula is a genus of sulfate reducing aerobic endospore - forming Gram - positive thermophilic motile rod - shaped bacteria , isolated from a geothermally active underground mine .
Barbus brichardi is a species of cyprinid fish native to the Republic of the Congo and Gabon .
Cyanea kolekoleensis ( formerly Delissea kolekoleensis ) is a rare species of flowering plant in the bellflower family known by the common names ` Oha and Kolekole cyanea .
Lactarius rufulus , commonly known as the rufous candy cap , is a species of fungus in the Russulaceae family .
Atheris ceratophora is a venomous viper species endemic to a few mountain ranges in Tanzania .
Dioscorea hamiltonii is a species of Dioscorea native to southern China ( including Taiwan ) , northern Indochina ( Thailand , Vietnam , Myanmar ) and the Himalayas ( Nepal , Sikkim , Bhutan , Assam ) .

The Ecnomidae are a family of caddisflies comprising 9 genera with a total of 1337 species .
Hatena arenicola is a species of single - celled eukaryotes discovered in 2000 , and first reported in 2005 , It was discovered by Japanese biologists Noriko Okamoto and Isao Inouye at the University of Tsukuba , and they gave the scientific description and formal name in 2006 .
Reiszerpeton is an extinct genus of dissorophid temnospondyl known from the Early Permian Archer City Formation of Texas .
Calliostoma adspersum , common name the spotted Brazilian top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calliostomatidae .
Rupertia rigida is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name Parish 's California tea , or Parish 's rupertia .
Streptomyces cellulolyticus is a cellulolytic bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces .

Larutia is a genus of limbless skinks in the family Scincidae .
Ropicella antennalis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Ropicella .

Teucridium is a genus of flowering plant in the Lamiaceae family , first described as a genus in 1853 .
Juglans sigillata , known as the Iron Walnut , is a species of walnut tree .
Drosophyllum ( /ˌdrɒsoʊˈfɪləm/ , rarely /drəˈsɒfɪləm/ ) is a genus of carnivorous plants containing the single species Drosophyllum lusitanicum ( Portuguese sundew or dewy pine ) .
Feroxodon multistriatus , known as the manystriped blowfish , manystriped pufferfish , scribbled toadfish , or ferocious pufferfish , is a species in the pufferfish family , Tetraodontidae , distributed in the Indo - West Pacific .

Amphisbaena bakeri , known commonly as Baker 's worm lizard , is a worm lizard species in the genus Amphisbaena .

Stonogobiops dracula , the Dracula shrimpgoby , is a species of goby native to reef environments around the Seychelles and the Maldives .

Mantoida brunneriana is a species of praying mantis inhabiting Bolivia , Brazil , French Guiana , Paraguay , and Venezuela .

Arctomecon humilis is a rare species of poppy called Bearclaw Poppy or Dwarf Bearclaw - poppy .

The Arabian jird ( Meriones arimalius ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Acoelorrhaphe is a genus of palms , comprising the single species Acoelorrhaphe wrightii ( Paurotis palm , also known as the Everglades palm and Madeira palm ) .
Aliciella sedifolia ( formerly Gilia sedifolia ) is a rare species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name stonecrop gilia .
Sphaerius is a genus of beetles , comprising 23 species , which are the only members of the family Sphaeriusidae .
Rock tripe is the common name for various lichens of the genus Umbilicaria that grow on rocks .
Ramanella anamalaiensis ( Anamalai dot frog , Anamalai ramanella , or reddish - brown microhylid frog ) is a species of narrow - mouthed frog found in South India .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Phycomelaina laminariae .
Limonium australe is a species of sea lavender known by the common name Native Sea Lavender .
Prakasha amariformis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Prakasha .
Epidendrum embreei ( `` Embree 's Epidendrum '' ) is a species of orchid in the genus Epidendrum .
Homalanthus nutans , known locally as the mamala tree , is a species of plant in the Euphorbiaceae family .
The family Oplophoridae is a taxon of pelagic shrimp and the only subtaxon of the superfamily Oplophoroidea .
Lennooideae is a subfamily of parasitic flowering plants of south - western North America and north - western South America .
Ericameria lignumviridis , common name Greenwood 's goldenbush or heath - goldenrod , is a plant species endemic to Sevier County , Utah .
Genioliparis is a genus of snailfishes .
Palmadusta diluculum , the day - break cowry , is a species of sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
The Australian prowfishes form a family , Pataecidae , of scorpaeniform fishes .
It contains the single species Condylodon audouini , first described from a single specimen by Lund ( 1831 ) in a paper on Brazilian ants .
Lygosoma vosmaeri ( Vosmer 's writhing skink ) is a species of skink endemic to South Asia ( India . A second specimen was discovered in 2009 in an open scrub jungle in rocky habitat near Jaggayapet , Andhra Pradesh , some 170 years after the collection of the holotype .
Tillandsia ariza - juliae , the wand airplant , is a species in the genus Tillandsia .
Eocaecilia is an extinct genus of caecilian ( limbless amphibian ) from the early Jurassic Kayenta Formation of Arizona , USA .
Elasmias cernicum is a species of tropical , tree - living , air - breathing , land snail , arboreal pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Achatinellidae .
Trifolium pratense , the red clover is a herbaceous species of flowering plant in the bean family Fabaceae , native to Europe , Western Asia and northwest Africa , but planted and naturalised in many other regions .
The six species in the genus Didelphis , commonly known as large American opossums , are members of the order Didelphimorphia .
Aglaspoides is an extinct genus of aglaspid arthropod .
Gymnocarpium is a small genus of ferns , called oak ferns .
Patera clarki nantahala , the noonday globe , is a subspecies of Patera clarki , a land snail in the family Polygyridae .
Aulonocara korneliae , known in the aquarium fish trade as the Aulonocara Chizumulu , Aulonocara blue gold or blue orchard Aulanocara , is a species of freshwater fish in the Cichlidae family .
Opilio lepidus is a species of harvestman in the Phalangiidae family .
Michelia coriacea is a species of flowering plant in the family Magnoliaceae .
Diabantia is a genus of praying mantises .
Barbulifer is a genus of gobies native to the tropical Atlantic coast of the Americas as well as the Gulf of California on the Pacific coast .
Erigeron karvinskianus is a species of flowering plant in the family Asteraceae known by the common names Mexican fleabane , Latin American fleabane , Santa Barbara daisy or Spanish daisy Karwinsky 's fleabane , Bony - tip Fleabane .
Dendrocnide meyeniana is a species of tree in the Urticaceae family , native to the thickets and secondary forests of Taiwan and the Philippines .
Aulonocara nyassae , known as the emperor cichlid , is a species of freshwater fish in the Cichlidae family that is endemic to Lake Malawi .
Goodfellow 's tree - kangaroo ( Dendrolagus goodfellowi ) also called the ornate tree - kangaroo , belongs to the family Macropodidae , which includes kangaroos , wallabies and their relatives , and the genus Dendrolagus , with eleven other species .
Amphisbaena silvestrii , also known as Silvestri 's worm lizard , is a worm lizard species in the genus Amphisbaena .
Drosophila ambigua is a European species of fruit fly .
Porroglossum ( from Greek `` far off '' and `` tongue '' , referring to the position of the lip ) is a genus of orchids native to the Andes of South America .
Gymnogeophagus is a genus of cichlid fishes from South America , where they are known from various river basins ( notably Rio de la Plata and Lagoa dos Patos -- Mirim ) in southern Brazil , Paraguay , Uruguay and northern Argentina .
Baeomyces is a genus of lichens .
Oscularia is a genus of succulent flowering plants in the family Aizoaceae , native to semi - arid and rocky habitats in the Western Cape of South Africa .
Platycranium pustulosum is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Platycranium .
Rubus aboriginum is a North American species of dewberry , known as the garden dewberry and aboriginal dewberry .
Cyphocleonus achates is a species of true weevil known as the knapweed root weevil .
Leucochrysum albicans , commonly known as hoary sunray , is a species in the family Asteraceae .
Erigeron salishii is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names Salish fleabane and Star Peak fleabane .
Lyngbya is a genus of cyanobacteria , multicellular autotrophs that form the basis of the oceanic food chain .
Melicope knudsenii , commonly known as Olokele Valley melicope or Knudsen 's melicope , is a species of flowering plant in the citrus family , Rutaceae , that is endemic to Hawaii .
Alrausuchus is an extinct genus of biarmosuchian therapsid from Russia .
Ranzania ( Japanese : トガクシショウマ ) is a monotypic genus of perennial herbs in the family Berberidaceae , the only species is Ranzania japonica .
Nosferatu steindachneri , Steindachner 's cichlid , is a species of cichlid endemic to Mexico where it is found in the Tamasopo , Gallinas and Ojo Frio Rivers of the Panuco River basin .
Thunnus tonggol is a species of tuna of tropical Indo - West Pacific waters .
Metriacanthosauridae is an extinct family of carnivorous allosauroid theropod dinosaurs .
Pogogyne douglasii is a species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common names Douglas ' mesamint and Douglas ' beardstyle .
Dendrobium gibsonii is a species of orchid native to China ( Guangxi and Yunnan provinces ) , the Himalayas ( Nepal , Bhutan , India , Assam ) , and northern Indochina ( Myanmar , Thailand , Laos , Vietnam ) .
Ophioblennius macclurei , the Redlip blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the western Atlantic ocean .
Paraclinus is a genus of labrisomid blennies native to eastern Pacific Ocean and the western Atlantic Ocean .
Vitis californica , with common names California wild grape , Northern California grape , and Pacific grape , is a wild grape species widespread across much of California as well as southwestern Oregon .
Garnotia is a genus of Asian , Australian , and tropical island plants in the grass family .
Meroles ctenodactylus , also known as Smith 's sand lizard or Smith 's desert lizard , is a species of sand - dwelling lizard in the family Lacertidae .
Didymoplexis is a genus of 17 species of leafless , achlorophyllous orchids , native to Africa , Madagascar , Southeast Asia , Australia and various islands of the Pacific .
The Culex vishnui Theobald mosquito species belongs to a sub - type that also includes two other carriers of the Japanese encephalitis virus - Culex tritaeniorhynchus Giles and Culex pseudovishnui Colless .
Nemoderma is the only genus in the family Nemodermataceae and order Nemodermatales of the brown algae ( class Phaeophyceae ) .
Ononis repens or common restharrow is a plant species of the genus Ononis .
The White and Blood - red Dendrobium ( Dendrobium albosanguineum ) is a species of orchid , native to Thailand and Myanmar .
Colletes marginatus is a species of solitary bee of the family Colletidae .
Festuca psammophila is a species of grass which is endemic to Central Europe .
Crataegus submollis , known as the northern downy hawthorn , northern red haw , Quebec hawthorn , or hairy cockspurthorn , is a species of hawthorn that grows to about 7 m in height and typically carries large crops of red fruit .
Myrmecia hilli is a species of ant native to Australia .
Parasimulium is a genus of black flies containing two subgenera and four species .
Beyeria subtecta , commonly known as the Kangaroo Island Turpentine Bush , is a species of plant in the family Euphorbiaceae .
Exapion fuscirostre ( formerly Apion fuscirostre ) is a species of straight - snouted weevil known by the general common name Scotch broom seed weevil .
Semirossia patagonica is a species of bobtail squid native to the southwestern Atlantic Ocean and southeastern Pacific Ocean ; it occurs around the southern part of South America and has been recorded from waters off Chile , Anegada Bay , Tierra del Fuego , Argentina , and the Falkland Islands .
Bagauda zetteli is a species of assassin bug in the subfamily Emesinae found in Borneo .
Brittle stars or ophiuroids are echinoderms in the class Ophiuroidea closely related to starfish .
Diadectidae is an extinct family of early tetrapods that lived in what is now North America and Europe during the Late Carboniferous and Early Permian , and in Asia during the Late Permian .
Matthiola longipetala , known as Night - scented Stock or Evening Stock ( syns Cheiranthus longipetalus , Matthiola bicornis , Matthiola longipetala subsp . bicornis , and Matthiola oxyceras ) , is a species of ornamental plant .
Aulaconotopsis fimbriatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Aulaconotopsis .
Acromyrmex subterraneus is a species of leaf - cutter ant , a New World ant of the subfamily Myrmicinae of the genus Acromyrmex .
Editha is a small genus of large , brightly colored sand wasps , restricted to South America .
Filippovia knipovitchi , the smooth hooked squid , is a species of squid in the family Onychoteuthidae and the sole member of the genus Filippovia .
Camponotus japonicus , more often known under the common name Japanese carpenter ant , is a species of ant native to East Asia .
Adam Flowers is an American lyric tenor who is based in San Francisco , California .
Erna Berger ( 19 October 1900 -- 14 June 1990 ) , was a German coloratura lyric soprano .
Albert Reiss ( 22 February 1870 -- 19 June 1940 ) was a German operatic tenor who had a prolific career in Europe and the United States during the first third of the twentieth century .
Anna Leese ( born 7 March 1981 ) is a New Zealand born soprano opera singer based in Tuscany .
Violeta Urmana , ( born Violeta Urmanavičiūtė ) is a Lithuanian soprano and mezzo - soprano .
Andrea Gruber ( born 1966 ) is an award winning American dramatic soprano particularly admired for her interpretations of the works of Puccini , Verdi , and Wagner .
Gloria Davy ( March 29 , 1931 , Brooklyn -- November 28 , 2012 , Geneva ) was a Swiss soprano of American birth who had an active international career in operas and concerts from the 1950s through the 1980s .
Joan Cross ( 7 September 1900 -- 12 December 1993 ) was an English soprano , closely associated with the operas of Benjamin Britten .
Octave Dua ( 28 Feb 1882 , Ghent - 8 March 1952 , Brussels ) was a Belgian operatic tenor .
Elizabeth Frances Ingram ( 5 November 1888 -- 12 April 1974 ) was an American operatic contralto of English birth who had an active career in North America during the 1910s and 1920s .
Taryn Fiebig ( born 1 February 1972 ) is an Australian opera and musical theatre soprano and cellist .
Cecilia Bartoli , Cavaliere OMRI ( Italian : ( tʃeˈtʃiːlja ˈbartoli ) ; born 4 June 1966 ) is an Italian coloratura mezzo - soprano opera singer and recitalist .
Pollione Ronzi ( before 1835 - after 1912 ) was an Italian operatic tenor , composer , conductor , and voice teacher .
Edwina Eustis Dick ( 1 September 1908 -- 3 March 1997 ) was an American classical contralto and pioneer in the field of music therapy .
Niels Juel Simonsen ( born May 16 , 1846 in Copenhagen , died May 25 , 1906 also in Copenhagen ) was Danish baritone opera singer , who made his debut in 1874 .
Richard Edgar - Wilson is an English tenor who has had an international career on the concert platform and the opera stage .
Caroline Unger ( sometimes `` Ungher '' ) ( 28 October 1803 -- 23 March 1877 ) was an Austro - Hungarian contralto , alternatively known as Karoline , Carolina , and Carlotta .
Blake Stern ( 1917 -- 22 December 1987 ) was an American tenor , best known as an oratorio singer , and a professor emeritus of music at Yale University , where he taught voice .
Ruxandra Donose ( born in Bucharest ) is a Romanian operatic mezzo - soprano .
Alessandro Corbelli ( born September 21 , 1952 ) is an Italian baritone opera singer .
Dodi Protero ( March 13 , 1931 - -April 22 , 2007 ) was a Canadian operatic soprano who had a prolific international career from 1955 through 1980 .
Hans Jörg Mammel ( born in Stuttgart ) is a German tenor in opera and concert .
Kathryn Elizabeth Smith ( May 1 , 1907 -- June 17 , 1986 ) , known professionally as Kate Smith and The First Lady of Radio , was an American singer , a contralto , best known for her rendition of Irving Berlin 's `` God Bless America '' .
Otakar Mařák ( 5 January 1872 Esztergom , Hungary -- 2 July 1939 Prague ) was a tenor Czech opera singer , and a nephew of Julius Mařák who perfected his vocal skills at Prague 's School of Applied Arts as well as at the Czech Academy of Arts .
Jane Barbier ( d ? London , ? will proved 9 Dec 1757 ) was an English contralto of the 18th century , best known for her performances in the operas of George Frederic Handel .
Alwina Valleria ( October 12 , 1848 -- February 17 , 1925 ) was an American - born soprano .
